complex: Micro black holes, also called quantum mechanical black holes or mini black holes, are hypothetical tiny black holes, for which quantum mechanical effects play an important role. <s> The concept that black holes may exist that are smaller than stellar mass was introduced in 1971 by Stephen Hawking.
simple: Micro black holes are very small black holes. <s> They may exist in nature as primordial black holes.

title: Del Rio, Texas
complex: Del Rio is a city and the county seat of Val Verde County in southwestern Texas, United States. <s> The city is 152 miles west of San Antonio.
simple: Del Rio is a border city in and the county seat of Val Verde County, Texas, United States.

title: Orphan
complex: An orphan (from the ) is someone whose parents have died, are unknown, or have permanently abandoned them. <s> In common usage, only a child who has lost both parents due to death is called an orphan.
simple: An orphan is a child who has lost either or both parents.

title: Joe P. Tolson
complex: Joe Pat Tolson (April 15, 1941 – February 3, 2019) was a Democratic member of the North Carolina General Assembly representing the state's twenty-third House district, including constituents in Edgecombe and Wilson counties. <s> A retired educator from Pinetops, North Carolina, Tolson retired after the 2013-2014 session, serving his ninth term in the state House. <s> He was replaced by Shelly Willingham. <s> Tolson died in 2019 from respiratory failure at a hospital in Tarboro, North Carolina.
simple: Joe Pat Tolson (April 15, 1941 – February 3, 2019) was an American Democratic politician. <s> Tolson died on February 3, 2019 from respiratory failure at a hospital in Tarboro, North Carolina, aged 77.

title: AD 31
complex: AD 31 (XXXI) was a common year starting on Monday (link will display the full calendar) of the Julian calendar. <s> At the time, it was known as the Year of the Consulship of Tiberius and Sejanus (or, less frequently, year 784 "Ab urbe condita"). <s> The denomination AD 31 for this year has been used since the early medieval period, when the Anno Domini calendar era became the prevalent method in Europe for naming years.
simple: It was a common year starting on Monday of the Julian calendar. <s> At the time, it was known as the Year of the Consulship of Augustus and Seianus.

title: Kariapatti taluk
complex: Kariapatti taluk is a taluk of Virudhunagar district of the Indian state of Tamil Nadu. <s> The headquarters of the taluk is the town of Kariapatti. <s> According to the 2011 census, the taluk of Kariapatti had a population of 105,329 with 52,875 males and 52,454 females. <s> There were 992 women for every 1000 men. <s> The taluk had a literacy rate of 68.46. <s> Child population in the age group below 6 was 5,736 Males and 5,513 Females.
simple: Kariapatti taluk is a taluk of Virudhunagar district of the Indian state of Tamil Nadu. <s> The headquarters of the taluk is the town of Kariapatti. <s> According to the 2011 census, the taluk of Kariapatti had a population of 105,329 with 52,875 males and 52,454 females. <s> There were 992 women for every 1000 men. <s> The taluk had a literacy rate of 68.46. <s> Child population in the age group below 6 was 5,736 Males and 5,513 Females.

title: Marjoram
complex: Marjoram ( ; Origanum majorana) is a somewhat cold-sensitive perennial herb or undershrub with sweet pine and citrus flavors. <s> In some Middle Eastern countries, marjoram is synonymous with oregano, and there the names sweet marjoram and knotted marjoram are used to distinguish it from other plants of the genus "Origanum". <s> It is also called pot marjoram, although this name is also used for other cultivated species of "Origanum".
simple: Whoa Black Betty Marjoram ("Origanum majorana", Lamiaceae) is a somewhat cold-sensitive perennial herb or undershrub with sweet pine and citrus flavours. <s> In some middle-eastern countries, marjoram is synonymous with oregano, and there the names sweet Black Betty had a child marjoram and the damn thing gone wild knotted marjoram are used to distinguish it from other plants.

title: Laura Chinchilla
complex: Laura Chinchilla Miranda (] ; born 28 March 1959) is a Costa Rican politician who was President of Costa Rica from 2010 to 2014. <s> She was one of Óscar Arias Sánchez's two Vice-Presidents and his administration's Minister of Justice. <s> She was the governing PLN candidate for President in the 2010 general election, where she won with 46.76% of the vote on 7 February. <s> She was the eighth woman president of a Latin American country and the first woman to become President of Costa Rica. <s> She was sworn in as President of Costa Rica on May 8, 2010. <s> Chinchilla was born in Carmen Central, San José in 1959. <s> She is the daughter of Rafael Ángel Chinchilla Fallas, a former comptroller of Costa Rica, and Emilce Miranda Castillo. <s> She married Mario Alberto Madrigal Díaz on 23 January 1982 and divorced on 22 May 1985. <s> Chinchilla met her second husband, José María Rico Cueto, a Spanish lawyer who held Canadian citizenship, in 1990 while both were working as consultants for the Center for the Administration of Justice at the University of Florida in Miami, Florida. <s> The couple had a son, José María Rico Chinchilla, in 1996. <s> Chinchilla married Rico on 26 March 2000. <s> Chinchilla graduated from the University of Costa Rica and received her master's degree in public policy from Georgetown University. <s> Prior to entering politics, Chinchilla worked as an NGO consultant in Latin America and Africa, specializing in judicial reform and public security issues. <s> She went on to serve in the José María Figueres Olsen administration as vice-minister for public security (1994–1996) and minister of public security (1996–1998). <s> From 2002 to 2006, she served in the National Assembly as a deputy for the province of San José. <s> Chinchilla was one of two vice-presidents elected under the second Arias administration (2006–2010). <s> She resigned the vice-presidency in 2008 in order to prepare her run for the presidency in 2010. <s> On 7 June 2009 she won the Partido Liberación Nacional (PLN) primary with a 15% margin over her nearest rival, and was thus endorsed as the party's presidential candidate.
simple: Laura Chinchilla Miranda (born 28 March 1959) served as the President of Costa Rica from 2010 to 2014. <s> She was one of Óscar Arias Sánchez's two vice presidents. <s> She was his administration's Minister of Justice. <s> She was the governing PLN candidate for President in the 2010 general election. <s> She won with 46.76% of the vote. <s> She is Costa Rica's first female president. <s> She is the sixth woman to be elected president of a Latin American country. <s> Chinchilla was born in Carmen Central, San José in 1959. <s> Her father was Rafael Ángel Chinchilla Fallas. <s> Her mother was Emilce Miranda Castillo. <s> She married Mario Alberto Madrigal Díaz on 23 January 1982 and divorced on 22 May 1985. <s> She had a son in 1996 with José María Rico Cueto, a Spanish lawyer who has a Canadian citizenship; Chinchilla married him on 26 March 2000. <s> Chinchilla graduated from the University of Costa Rica. <s> She received her master's degree in public policy from Georgetown University. <s> Before politics, Chinchilla worked as a NGO consultant in Latin America and Africa. <s> She specialized in judicial reform and public security. <s> She served in the José María Figueres Olsen administration as vice-minister for public security (1994–1996) and minister of public security (1996–1998). <s> From 2002 to 2006, she served in the National Assembly as a deputy for the province of San José. <s> Chinchilla was one of two vice-presidents elected under the second Arias administration (2006–2010). <s> She resigned the vice-presidency in 2008 in order to prepare her run for the presidency in 2010. <s> On 7 June 2009 she won the Partido Liberación Nacional (PLN) primary with a 15% margin over her nearest rival, and was thus endorsed as the party's presidential candidate.

title: Odd Future Records
complex: Odd Future Records was an American record label founded by rapper and producer Tyler, the Creator of Odd Future in 2011. <s> It operated as a division of Sony Music Entertainment.
simple: Odd Future Records is a record label founded by Tyler The Creator in 2011.

title: Fractional distillation
complex: Fractional distillation is the separation of a mixture into its component parts, or fractions. <s> Chemical compounds are separated by heating them to a temperature at which one or more fractions of the mixture will vaporize. <s> It uses distillation to fractionate. <s> Generally the component parts have boiling points that differ by less than 25 C from each other under a pressure of one atmosphere. <s> If the difference in boiling points is greater than 25 °C, a simple distillation is typically used. <s> Fractional distillation is the most common form of separation technology used in petroleum refineries, petrochemical and chemical plants, natural gas processing and cryogenic air separation plants. <s> In most cases, the distillation is operated at a continuous steady state.
simple: Fractional distillation is a process of separating a mixture of chemical compounds. <s> Fractional distillation is done by heating the mixture so that each fraction evaporates and then condenses in its own compartment. <s> Generally, the component parts boil at less than 25°C from each other under a pressure of one atmosphere (atm). <s> If the difference in boiling points is greater than 25°C, a simple distillation is used. <s> Fractional distillation is the main activity of oil refineries.

title: Jack Markell
complex: Jack Alan Markell (born November 26, 1960) is an American former businessman and politician who served as the 73rd Governor of Delaware from 2009 to 2017. <s> He is a member of the Democratic Party.
simple: Jack A. Markell (born November 26, 1960) is an American politician. <s> In 2009, he became the Governor of Delaware.

title: Parliamentary opposition
complex: Parliamentary opposition is a form of political opposition to a designated government, particularly in a Westminster-based parliamentary system. <s> This article uses the term "government" as it is used in Parliamentary systems, i.e. meaning "the administration" or "the cabinet" rather than "the state". <s> The title of "Official Opposition" usually goes to the largest of the parties sitting in opposition with its leader being given the title "Leader of the Opposition".
simple: Parliamentary opposition is a political position. <s> It is a type of opposition to the government. <s> They are called the "Official Opposition" sometimes.

title: Graphical user interface
complex: Graphical user interface (GUI) wrappers find a way around the command-line interface versions (CLI) of (typically) Linux and Unix-like software applications and their text-based user interfaces or typed command labels. <s> While command-line or text-based application allow users to run a program non-interactively, GUI wrappers atop them avoid the steep learning curve of the command-line, which requires commands to be typed on the keyboard.
simple: Computers can display information and let the user give commands to it using two methods: a command line interface (CLI) or a graphical user interface (GUI).

title: NCIS (TV series)
complex: NCIS is an American action police procedural television series, revolving around a fictional team of special agents from the Naval Criminal Investigative Service. <s> The concept and characters were initially introduced in two episodes of the CBS series "JAG" (season eight episodes 20 and 21: "Ice Queen" and "Meltdown"). <s> The show, a spin-off from "JAG", premiered on September 23, 2003, on CBS. <s> To date it has aired sixteen full seasons and has gone into broadcast syndication on the USA Network.
simple: NCIS (also called NCIS: Naval Criminal Investigative Service) is a crime-drama television series on CBS. <s> It is about a team of special agents from the Naval Criminal Investigative Service in Washington, D.C. <s> The series is a spin-off from "JAG" and has a spin-off called "".

title: Don Edwards (cowboy singer)
complex: Don Edwards (born March 20, 1939 in Boonton, New Jersey) is a cowboy singer and guitarist who performs Western music. <s> He has recorded several albums, two of which, "Saddle Songs" and "Songs of the Cowboy", are included in the Folklore Archives of the Library of Congress. <s> Edwards also recorded the album "High Lonesome Cowboy" with Peter Rowan and Tony Rice. <s> Edwards played the character Smokey in Robert Redford's "The Horse Whisperer". <s> Edwards also performs the song "Coyotes" that plays during the final minutes of the documentary "Grizzly Man". <s> In 2005, Don Edwards was inducted into the Western Music Association Hall of Fame.
simple: Don Edwards (born March 20, 1939 in Boonton, New Jersey) is an American singer and guitarist. <s> He performs Western music. <s> Edwards has recorded several albums, two of which, "Saddle Songs" and "Songs of the Cowboy", are included in the Folklore Archives of the Library of Congress. <s> Edwards also performs the song "Coyotes" that plays during the final minutes of the documentary "Grizzly Man". <s> In 2005, Edwards was inducted into the Western Music Association Hall of Fame.

title: Information commissioner
complex: In the United Kingdom, the Information Commissioner's Office is responsible for regulating compliance with the Data Protection Act 1998, Freedom of Information Act 2000 and the Environmental Information Regulations 2004. <s> The Freedom of Information (Scotland) Act 2002 is the responsibility of the Scottish Information Commissioner.
simple: In the United Kingdom these are laws such as the Data Protection Act.

title: Čejov
complex: Čajev is a small village near Humpolec in the Pelhřimov District, Vysočina Region of the Czech Republic. <s> 473 people live there and it covers 7,98 km2 of land.
simple: Čajev is small village near Humpolec in the Havlíčkův Brod District, Vysočina Region of the Czech Republic. <s> 473 people live there and it has 7,98 km2.

title: The Osmonds
complex: The Osmonds are an American family music group who reached the height of their fame in the early-1970s. <s> The group consists of siblings who are all members of the Osmond family, a family of musicians from Ogden, Utah, who have been in the public eye since the 1960s.
simple: The Osmonds are an American family singing group.

title: Anti-capitalism
complex: Anti-capitalism encompasses a wide variety of movements, ideas and attitudes that oppose capitalism. <s> Anti-capitalists, in the strict sense of the word, are those who wish to replace capitalism with another type of economic system.
simple: Anti-capitalism describes a wide variety of movements, ideas, and attitudes which oppose capitalism, toward social equality or environmentalism. <s> Anti-capitalists, in the strict sense of the word, are those who wish to completely replace capitalism with another system; however, there are also ideas which can be characterized as "partially" anti-capitalist in the sense that they only wish to replace or abolish certain aspects of capitalism rather than the entire system.

title: Holyrood Abbey
complex: Holyrood Abbey is a ruined abbey of the Canons Regular in Edinburgh, Scotland. <s> The abbey was founded in 1128 by King David I. <s> During the 15th century, the abbey guesthouse was developed into a royal residence, and after the Scottish Reformation the Palace of Holyroodhouse was expanded further.
simple: Holyrood Abbey is in Edinburgh, Scotland. <s> It is a ruined Augustine Abbey and was built by David I of Scotland in 1128.

title: Hans Persson
complex: Hans Persson, born 18 January 1959, is a Swedish former cross-country skier, specialized at long-distance races. <s> In 1984, he won Vasaloppet. <s> Representing at Åsarna IK, he won the Swedish national relay championship with that club in 1980-1983 and again in 1988.
simple: Hans Persson, born 18 January 1959, is a Swedish former cross-country skier. <s> He was specialized at long-distance races. <s> In 1984, he won Vasaloppet. <s> With that club, he won the Swedish national relay championship in 1980-1983 and again in 1988.

title: Volatiles
complex: In planetary science, volatiles are the group of chemical elements and chemical compounds with low boiling points that are associated with a planet's or moon's crust or atmosphere. <s> Examples include nitrogen, water, carbon dioxide, ammonia, hydrogen, methane and sulfur dioxide. <s> In astrogeology, these compounds, in their solid state, often comprise large proportions of the crusts of moons and dwarf planets.
simple: In planetary science, volatiles are the group of chemical elements and compounds with a low boiling point. <s> Examples of volatiles are nitrogen, water, and ammonia.

title: UK Albums Chart
complex: The Official Albums Chart is a list of albums ranked by physical and digital sales and (from March 2015) audio streaming in the United Kingdom. <s> It was published for the first time on 22 July 1956 and is compiled every week by the Official Charts Company (OCC) on Fridays (previously Sundays).
simple: The UK Albums Chart is a list of albums ranked by sales in the United Kingdom.

title: Beaurainville
complex: Beaurainville is a commune in the Pas-de-Calais department in the Hauts-de-France region in northern France.
simple: Beaurainville is a commune.

title: Photios I of Constantinople
complex: Photios I ( "Phōtios"), (c. 810/820 – 6 February 893), also spelled Photius or Fotios, was the Ecumenical Patriarch of Constantinople from 858 to 867 and from 877 to 886; He is recognized in the Eastern Orthodox Church as Saint Photios the Great. <s> Photios is widely regarded as the most powerful and influential church leader of Constantinople subsequent to John Chrysostom's archbishopric around the turn of the fifth century. <s> He is also viewed as the most important intellectual of his time – "the leading light of the ninth-century renaissance". <s> He was a central figure in both the conversion of the Slavs to Christianity and the Photian schism, and is considered "the great systematic compiler of the Eastern Church, who occupies a similar position to that of Gratian in the West," and whose "collection in two parts...formed and still forms the classic source of ancient Church Law for the Greek Church." <s> The Eastern Orthodox Church venerates Photios as a saint; his feast day is February 6.
simple: Photios I was born c. 810 or 820 in Constantinople and died 891 in Bordi (Armenia). <s> He was the Ecumenical Patriarch of Constantinople from 858 to 867 and from 877 to 886. <s> In the Eastern Orthodox churches he is called St. Photios the Great. <s> Photios a powerful and influential Patriarch of Constantinople. <s> He was a leading intellectual of his time, "the leading light of the ninth-century renaissance". <s> He was a central figure in both the religious conversion of the Slavs to Christianity and the Photian schism.

title: Nudibranch
complex: Nudibranchs are a group of soft-bodied, marine gastropod molluscs which shed their shells after their larval stage. <s> They are noted for their often extraordinary colours and striking forms, and they have been given colourful nicknames to match, such as "clown," "marigold," "splendid," "dancer," "dragon," or "sea rabbit." <s> Currently, about 3,000 valid species of nudibranchs are known. <s> The word "nudibranch" comes from the Latin "naked" and the Ancient Greek "gills". <s> Nudibranchs are benthic animals, found crawling over the substrate. <s> The only exceptions to this are the neustonic "Glaucus" nudibranchs, which float upside down just under the ocean's surface, and the pelagic nudibranchs "Cephalopyge trematoides", which swim in the water column and "Phylliroe bucephalum." <s> The body forms of nudibranchs vary a great deal, but because they are opisthobranchs, unlike most other gastropods, they are apparently bilaterally symmetrical externally (but not internally) because they have undergone secondary detorsion. <s> In all nudibranchs, the male and female sexual openings are on the right side of the body, reflecting their asymmetrical origins. <s> They lack a mantle cavity. <s> Some species have venomous appendages (cerata) on their sides, which deter predators. <s> Many also have a simple gut and a mouth with a radula. <s> In the course of their evolution, nudibranchs have lost their shells, while developing alternative defence mechanisms. <s> Some species evolved an external anatomy with textures and colours that mimicked surrounding sessile invertebrate animals (often their prey sponges or soft corals) to avoid predators (camouflage). <s> Other nudibranchs, as seen especially well on chromodorids, have an intensely bright and contrasting colour pattern that makes them especially conspicuous in their surroundings. <s> Nudibranch molluscs are the most commonly cited examples of aposematism in marine ecosystems, but the evidence for this has been contested, mostly because few examples of mimicry are seen among species, many species are nocturnal or cryptic, and bright colours at the red end of the spectrum are rapidly attenuated as a function of water depth. <s> For example, the Spanish dancer nudibranch (genus "Hexabranchus"), among the largest of tropical marine slugs, potently chemically defended, and brilliantly red and white, is nocturnal and has no known mimics. <s> Other studies of nudibranch molluscs have concluded they are aposematically coloured, for example, the slugs of the family Phylidiidae from Indo-Pacific coral reefs. <s> Nudibranchs that feed on hydrozoids can store the hydrozoids' nematocysts (stinging cells) in the dorsal body wall, the cerata. <s> These stolen nematocysts, called kleptocnidae, wander through the alimentary tract without harming the nudibranch. <s> Once further into the organ, the cells are assimilated by intestinal protuberances and brought to specific placements on the creature's hind body. <s> Nudibranchs can protect themselves from the hydrozoids and their nematocysts; the specific mechanism is yet unknown, but special cells with large vacuoles probably play an important role. <s> Similarly, some nudibranchs can also take in plant cells (symbiotic algae from soft corals) and reuse these to make food for themselves. <s> The related group of sacoglossan sea slugs feed on algae and retain just the chloroplasts for their own photosynthetic use, a process known as kleptoplasty. <s> Another method of protection is the release of an acid from the skin. <s> Once the specimen is physically irritated or touched by another creature, it will release the mucus automatically. <s> Nudibranchs are hermaphroditic, thus have a set of reproductive organs for both sexes, but they cannot fertilize themselves. <s> Mating usually takes a few minutes, and involves a dance-like courtship. <s> Nudibranchs typically deposit their eggs within a gelatinous spiral, which is often described as looking like a ribbon. <s> The number of eggs varies; it can be as few as just 1 or 2 eggs ("Vayssierea felis") or as many as an estimated 25 million ("Aplysia fasciata"). <s> The eggs contain toxins from sea sponges as a means of deterring predators. <s> After hatching, the infants look almost identical to their adult counterparts, albeit smaller. <s> Infants may also have fewer cerata. <s> The lifespan of nudibranchs can range from a few weeks to a year, depending on the species. <s> All known nudibranchs are carnivorous. <s> Some feed on sponges, others on hydroids (e.g. "Cuthona"), others on bryozoans (phanerobranchs such as "Tambja", "Limacia, Plocamopherus" and "Triopha"), and some eat other sea slugs or their eggs (e.g. "Favorinus") or, on some occasions, are cannibals and prey on members of their own species. <s> Other groups feed on tunicates (e.g. "Nembrotha", "Goniodoris"), other nudibranchs ("Roboastra", which are descended from tunicate-feeding species), barnacles (e.g. "Onchidoris bilamellata"), and anemones (e.g. the Aeolidiidae and other Cladobranchia). <s> The surface-dwelling nudibranch, "Glaucus atlanticus", is a specialist predator of siphonophores, such as the Portuguese man o' war. <s> This predatory mollusc sucks air into its stomach to keep it afloat, and using its muscular foot, it clings to the surface film. <s> If it finds a small victim, "Glaucus" simply envelops it with its capacious mouth, but if the prey is a larger siphonophore, the mollusc nibbles off its fishing tentacles, the ones carrying the most potent nematocysts. <s> Like some others of its kind, "Glaucus" does not digest the nematocysts; instead, it uses them to defend itself by passing them from its gut to the surface of its skin. <s> However, according to the taxonomy by Bouchet & Rocroi (2005), currently the most up-to-date system of classifying the gastropods, the Nudibranchia are a subclade within the clade of the Nudipleura.
simple: Nudibranchs are a widespread and successful group of marine Gastropod molluscs. <s> They are "opisthobranchs", a clade which shed their shells after the larval stage. <s> The name means 'naked gills'. <s> Nudibranchs are one of the groups which are informally known as sea slugs. <s> The body forms of nudibranchs vary greatly. <s> Unlike most other gastropods they are "bilaterally symmetrical". <s> They have undergone secondary detorsion. <s> Unusually for molluscs, they lack a mantle cavity. <s> Most species have venomous appendages on their sides. <s> Many also have a simple gut and a mouth with a radula. <s> In the course of evolution, sea slugs have lost their shell, and have developed other defense mechanisms. <s> Their anatomy may resemble the texture and color of the surrounding plants, giving them camouflage ("crypsis"). <s> Nudibranchs that feed on hydroids can store the hydroids' nematocysts (stinging cells) in the dorsal body wall. <s> The nematocysts wander through the alimentary canal without harming the nudibranch. <s> Then, the cells are brought to specific places on the creature's hind body. <s> Nudibranches can protect themselves from the hydroids and their nematocysts. <s> It is not yet clear how, but special cells with large vacuoles probably play an important role. <s> They can also take in plants' chloroplasts (plant cell organelles used for photosynthesis) and use them to make food for themselves. <s> Another method of protection is the release of a sour liquid from the skin. <s> Once the specimen is physically irritated or touched by another creature, it will release the slime automatically. <s> Nudibranchs are hermaphrodite, and thus have a set of reproductive organs for both sexes, but they rarely fertilize themselves. <s> Most nudibranchs are carnivorous. <s> Some feed on sponges, others on polyps, others on bryozoans, and some eat other sea slugs, or, on some occasions, members of their own species. <s> Other groups feed on tunicates, barnacles, or anemones. <s> The surface dwelling nudibranch, "Glaucus atlanticus" is a specialist predator of jellyfish, such as the Portuguese Man o' War. <s> This predatory mollusc sucks air into its stomach to keep it afloat and using its muscular foot it clings to the surface film. <s> If it finds a small victim "Glaucus" simply envelops it with its large mouth, but if the prey is a larger siphonophore the mollusc nibbles off its fishing tentacles, the ones carrying the most potent nematocysts. <s> Like some others of its kind "Glaucus" does not digest the nematocysts; instead, it uses them to defend itself by passing them from its gut to the surface of its skin. <s> The taxonomy of the Nudibranchia is still under investigation.

title: Alexander Mosaic
complex: The Alexander Mosaic, dating from circa 100 BC, is a Roman floor mosaic originally from the House of the Faun in Pompeii, that is allegedly an imitation of Apelles' painting. <s> It depicts a battle between the armies of Alexander the Great and Darius III of Persia and measures 2.72 x . <s> The original is preserved in the Naples National Archaeological Museum. <s> The mosaic is believed to be a copy of an early 3rd-century BC Hellenistic painting. <s> The mosaic illustrates a battle in which Alexander faced and attempted to capture or kill Darius. <s> Alexander defeated him at the Battle of Issus and two years later at the Battle of Gaugamela. <s> The work is traditionally believed to show the Battle of Issus. <s> Despite being damaged, the two main figures are easy to recognize. <s> The Persian soldiers behind him have expressions of determination and consternation. <s> The mosaic was rediscovered on October 24, 1831, in Pompeii, and was moved to Naples in September 1843, where it is currently preserved on a wall ("not" on a floor as it was found) in the Museo Archeologico Nazionale. <s> The mosaic is featured on 1,000 Greek drachma banknotes from 1956. <s> In 2003 the "International Center for the Study and Teaching of Mosaic" (CISIM) in Ravenna, Italy, proposed to create a copy of the mosaic. <s> When they had received approval, the mosaic master Severo Bignami and his eight-person team took a large photograph of the mosaic, made a tracing of the image with a dark marker and created a negative impression of the mosaic. <s> The project took 22 months and a cost equivalent to US$216,000. <s> The copy was installed in the House of the Faun in 2005.
simple: The Alexander Mosaic is a Roman floor mosaic from the House of the Faun in Pompeii. <s> It was made in 100 BC. <s> It shows a battle between the armies of Alexander the Great and Darius III of Persia. <s> It measures 2.72 x 5.13m (8 ft 11in x 16 ft 9in). <s> The original is at the Naples National Archaeological Museum. <s> The mosaic is based on a 3rd-century BC Hellenistic painting, by Philoxenos of Eretria. <s> The mosaic shows a battle between Alexander and Darius. <s> Alexander won the Battle of Issus. <s> Alexander won again two years later at the Battle of Gaugamela. <s> The work shows the Battle of Issus. <s> The two main figures are easy to see. <s> The Persian soldiers have a stern look. <s> The mosaic was found again on October 24, 1831 in Pompeii. <s> It was moved to Naples in September 1843. <s> It is in the Museo Archeologico Nazionale. <s> In 2003 the "International Center for the Study and Teaching of Mosaic" (CISIM) in Ravenna, Italy, wanted to make a copy of the mosaic. <s> The mosaic master Severo Bignami and his eight-person team took a large photograph of the mosaic. <s> It took them 22 months to make a copy of the mosaic. <s> The copy was put in the House of the Faun in 2005.

title: Doraemon: Nobita's Dinosaur
complex: Doraemon: Nobita's Dinosaur (ドラえもん のび太の恐竜 , "Doraemon – Nobita no Kyōryū" ) is a 1980 Japanese animated film based on the manga series "Doraemon". <s> The film premiered on 15 March 1980 in Japan. <s> It's the first feature-length "Doraemon" film.
simple: Doraemon:Nobita's Dinosaur is a 1980 Japanese animated movie. <s> It is based on the popular manga and anime series Doraemon. <s> The movie was released in Japan on 15 March 1980.

title: Parasitoid wasp
complex: Parasitoid wasps are a large group of hymenopteran superfamilies, with all but the wood wasps (Orussoidea) being in the wasp-waisted Apocrita. <s> As parasitoids, they lay their eggs on or in the bodies of other arthropods, sooner or later causing the death of these hosts. <s> Different species specialise in hosts from different insect orders, most often Lepidoptera, though some select beetles, flies, or bugs; the spider wasps (Pompilidae) exclusively attack spiders. <s> Many parasitoid wasps use larval Lepidoptera as hosts, but some groups parasitize different host life stages (egg, larva or nymph, pupa, adult) of nearly all other orders of insects, especially Coleoptera, Diptera, Hemiptera and other Hymenoptera. <s> Some attack arthropods other than insects: for instance, the Pompilidae specialise in catching spiders: these are quick and dangerous prey, often as large as the wasp itself, but the spider wasp is quicker, swiftly stinging her prey to immobilise it. <s> Adult female wasps of most species oviposit into their hosts' bodies or eggs. <s> Some also inject a mix of secretory products that paralyse the host or protect the egg from the host's immune system; these include polydnaviruses, ovarian proteins, and venom. <s> If a polydnavirus is included, it infects the nuclei of host hemocytes and other cells, causing symptoms that benefit the parasite. <s> As adults, parasitoid wasps feed primarily on nectar from flowers. <s> Females of some species will also drink hemolymph from hosts to gain additional nutrients for egg production. <s> Polydnaviruses are a unique group of insect viruses that have a mutualistic relationship with some parasitic wasps. <s> The polydnavirus replicates in the oviducts of an adult female parasitoid wasp. <s> The wasp benefits from this relationship because the virus provides protection for the parasitic larvae inside the host, (i) by weakening the host's immune system and (ii) by altering the host's cells to be more beneficial to the parasite. <s> The relationship between these viruses and the wasp is obligatory in the sense that all individuals are infected with the viruses; the virus has been incorporated in the wasp's genome and is inherited. <s> The hosts of parasitoids have developed several levels of defence. <s> Many hosts try to hide from the parasitoids in inaccessible habitats. <s> They may also get rid of their frass (body wastes) and avoid plants that they have chewed on as both can signal their presence to parasitoids hunting for hosts. <s> The egg shells and cuticles of the potential hosts are thickened to prevent the parasitoid from penetrating them. <s> Hosts may use behavioral evasion when they encounter an egg laying female parasitoid, like dropping off the plant they are on, twisting and thrashing so as to dislodge or kill the female and even regurgitating onto the wasp to entangle it. <s> The wriggling can sometimes help by causing the wasp to "miss" laying the egg on the host and instead place it nearby. <s> Wriggling of pupae can cause the wasp to lose its grip on the smooth hard pupa or get trapped in the silk strands. <s> Some caterpillars even bite the female wasps that approach them. <s> Some insects secrete poisonous compounds that kill or drive away the parasitoid. <s> Ants that are in a symbiotic relationship with caterpillars, aphids or scale insects may protect them from attack by wasps. <s> Even parasitoid wasps are vulnerable to hyperparasitoid wasps. <s> Some parasitoid wasps change the behavior of the infected host, causing them to build a silk web around the pupae of the wasps after they emerge from its body to protect them from hyperparasitoids. <s> Hosts can kill endoparasitoids by adhering hemocytes to the egg or larva in a process called encapsulation. <s> In aphids, the presence of a secondary bacterium endosymbiont, "Buchnera aphidicola" that carries a particular latent phage makes the aphid relatively immune to their parasitoid wasps by killing many of the eggs. <s> As the parasitoid's survival depends on its ability to evade the host's immune response, some parasitoid wasps have developed the counterstrategy of laying more eggs in aphids that have the endosymbiont so that at least one of them may hatch and parasitize the aphid. <s> Certain caterpillars eat plants that are toxic to both themselves and the parasite to cure themselves. <s> "Drosophila melanogaster" larvae also "self-medicate" with ethanol to treat parasitism. <s> "D. melanogaster" females lay their eggs in food containing toxic amounts of alcohol if they detect parasitoid wasps nearby. <s> The alcohol protects them from the wasps, at the cost of retarding their own growth.
simple: They are parasitoids which lay their eggs in or on the caterpillars of other insect species. <s> Many lay their eggs in inert stages of their host (egg or pupa). <s> Much like bees, butterflies, and moths, those which do feed as adults usually get all of their nutrition from nectar. <s> Polydnaviruses are a unique group of insect viruses that have a mutualistic relationship with parasitic wasps. <s> The polydnavirus, like all viruses, need a host to replicate itself. <s> This it does in the oviducts of the female wasp. <s> The virus protects the parasitic larva inside the host by weakening the host’s immune system. <s> The relationship between these viruses and the wasp is obligatory: all individuals are ‘infected’ with the viruses; the virus has been added to the wasp’s genome. <s> The victims of parasitoids do have defences they can use. <s> Many try to hide from the wasps. <s> The egg shells and cuticles of the prey are thickened to prevent the wasp from penetrating them. <s> When the wasp arrives, prey may drop off the plant they are on, or twist and thrash to dislodge the female. <s> Some regurgitate onto the wasp to tangle it up. <s> The wriggling can sometimes help by causing the wasp to miss laying the egg on the host and instead place it nearby. <s> Wriggling of pupae can cause the wasp to lose its grip on the smooth hard pupa or get trapped in the silk strands. <s> Some caterpillars bite wasps that approach it. <s> Some secrete poisonous compounds that kill or drive away the parasitoid. <s> Ants that are in a symbiotic relationship with caterpillars, aphids or scale insects defend them from attack by wasps. <s> Even parasitoid wasps are vulnerable to hyperparasitoid wasps. <s> Some parasitoid wasps change the behaviour of the infected host to build a silk web around the pupa of the wasps after they emerge from its body to protect them from hyperparasitoids. <s> In endoparasitoids, host immune cells can encapsulate the eggs and larvae of parasitoid wasps. <s> In aphids, a secondary endosymbiont, "Buchnera aphidicola" carries a latent phage. <s> This phage makes the aphid relatively immune to their parasitoid wasps by killing many of the eggs. <s> However, wasps counter this by laying more eggs in aphids that have the endosymbiont so that at least one of them can hatch and parasitize the aphid. <s> Certain caterpillars eat plants that are toxic to both themselves and the parasite to cure themselves. <s> "Drosophila melanogaster" larvae also "self-medicate" with ethanol to treat parasitism. <s> "D. melanogaster" females lay their eggs in food containing toxic amounts of alcohol if they detect parasitoid wasps nearby. <s> Despite the alcohol slowing the growth of the flies, it protects them from the wasps.

title: Raymond Chow
complex: Raymond Chow Man-Wai, (; 8 October 1927 – 2 November 2018) was a Hong Kong film producer, and presenter. <s> He was responsible for successfully launching martial arts and the Hong Kong cinema onto the international stage. <s> As the founder of Golden Harvest, he produced some of the biggest stars of the martial arts film genre, including Bruce Lee, Jackie Chan, and Tsui Hark. <s> Chow died on November 2, 2018, in Hong Kong.
simple: Raymond Chow Man-Wai, OBE, GBS (; 8 October 1927 – 2 November 2018) was a Hong Kong movie producer, and presenter. <s> He was known for promoting martial arts and the Hong Kong cinema onto the international stage. <s> Chow was the founder of Golden Harvest, he produced some of the biggest stars of the martial arts movie genre, including Bruce Lee, Jackie Chan, and Tsui Hark. <s> Chow died on 2 November 2018 at the age of 91.

title: Tom and Jerry Tales
complex: Tom and Jerry Tales is a Canadian-American animated television series starring the seven-time Academy Award-winning cat-and-mouse duo Tom and Jerry. <s> Produced by Warner Bros. <s> Animation and Turner Entertainment Co., It is the seventh made-for-television incarnation of the "Tom and Jerry" franchise as well as the first "Tom and Jerry" television series to emulate the original theatrical shorts created by William Hanna and Joseph Barbera; it originally ran in the United States from September 23, 2006 to March 22, 2008 on Kids' WB.
simple: Tom and Jerry Tales is an animated television series which began production in 2005. <s> The series stars the well-known title characters from the "Tom and Jerry" shorts, and is the first made for TV cartoon to emulate the theatrical shorts.

title: Félix María de Samaniego
complex: Félix María de Samaniego (October 12, 1745 – August 11, 1801), was a Spanish neoclassical fabulist. <s> He was born and died in Laguardia, Álava, in the Basque Country, and was educated at Valladolid. <s> A government appointment was secured for him by his uncle the Count de Peñaflorida.
simple: Félix María de Samaniego (October 12, 1745— August 11, 1801; born and died in Laguardia, Álava) was a Spanish neoclassical fabulist, educated at Valladolid. <s> He was a Spanish neoclassical fabulist and was educated at Valladolid. <s> A government appointment was secured for him by his uncle the Count de Peñaflorida.

title: James S. C. Chao
complex: James Si-Cheng Chao (; born December 29, 1927) is a Chinese-American entrepreneur and philanthropist. <s> He is the founder of the Foremost Group, a New York-based shipping, trading, and finance enterprise. <s> The James S.C. Chao Scholarship is named after him. <s> Active philanthropists, Chao and his wife established the Mulan Foundation in 1984 to provide scholarships to help students in the U.S. and China access higher education and to promote U.S.-China cultural exchanges. <s> In October 2012, Harvard University announced that Chao and his family foundation would donate $40 million to the Harvard Business School for the construction of the Ruth Mulan Chu Chao Center and the establishment of the Ruth Mulan Chu and James Si-Cheng Chao Family Fellowship Fund. <s> The Center will be a new building dedicated to executive education, the first building on campus named after a woman and of an Asian surname. <s> Chao has served for more than a decade as Chairman of both the Chiao-Tung University Alumni Association in America and the Chiao-Tung University Alumni Foundation of America from 1988-1999. <s> Chao met his future wife, Ruth Mulan Chu Chao, when she and her family relocated to Shanghai from their ancestral estate in Anhui Province during World War II. <s> In 1949, each relocated separately to Taiwan at the culmination of the Chinese Civil War, and they married in 1950. <s> In 1958, Chao left behind his then 7-month pregnant wife and two young children when he moved to the United States, where they rejoined him in 1961. <s> Ruth Mulan Chu Chao died on August 2, 2007. <s> The Chaos had six daughters: Elaine, Jeanette, May, Christine, Grace, and Angela and six grandchildren. <s> Chao's oldest daughter is Elaine Chao, who is the first woman of Asian Pacific American descent appointed to a president's cabinet: she served as secretary of labor from 2001 to 2009, and has served as secretary of transportation since 2017.
simple: James Si-Cheng Chao (; born December 29, 1927) is a Chinese-American businessman and philanthropist. <s> He is the founder of the Foremost Group, a New York-based shipping, trading, and finance enterprise. <s> The James S.C. Chao Scholarship is named after him. <s> Active philanthropists, Chao and his wife, Ruth Mulan Chu, established the Mulan Foundation in 1984 to provide scholarships to help students in the U.S. and China access higher education. <s> Chao has served for more than a decade as Chairman of both the Chiao-Tung University Alumni Association in America and the Chiao-Tung University Alumni Foundation of America from 1988-1999. <s> Chu died in 2007 from lymphoma. <s> They had six children.

title: Kelly Gallagher (alpine skier)
complex: Kelly Marie Gallagher, MBE (born 18 May 1985), is a British skier and the first athlete from Northern Ireland to compete in the Winter Paralympics. <s> Gallagher won Britain's first ever Winter Paralympic gold medal during Sochi 2014.
simple: Kelly Gallagher (born 24 April 1987) is a skier from Northern Ireland.

title: Padmashali
complex: Padmashali (also spelt as Padmasali) is a Telugu-speaking Hindu caste residing in the Indian states of Telangana, Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka, Maharashtra, Gujarat and Tamil Nadu. <s> They are traditional weavers, weaving is the hereditary occupation of Padmashalis. <s> The term "Padmashali" is derived from two words "Padma" and "Shali", The Padma means lotus and Shali means weaver. <s> The word Padma referring to the myth of the thread was a lotus which sprang from the navel of Vishnu. <s> The Padmashalis support their mythological origins and "Puranas" such as "Kulapurana" and "Markandeya Purana". <s> The Padmashalis are further divided into two groups based on Sampradaya, being the Shaivas and the Vaishnavas. <s> While the Shaivas give preference to worshipping Shiva, the Vaishnavas give preference to worship of Vishnu.
simple: Padmashali is a Telugu-speaking Hindu artisan community. <s> The term "Padmashali" is derived from two words "Padma" and "Shali", The Padma means lotus and Shali means weaver. <s> They support their Sanskrit origin with various myths and "Puranas" such as "Kulapurana" and "Markandeya Purana". <s> The Padmashalis divided into two groups based on "Sampradaya", being the Shaivas and the Vaishnavas and they worship both Shiva and Vishnu.

title: Gandzasar monastery
complex: Gandzasar monastery is a 10th to 13th century Armenian monastery situated in the Mardakert district of de facto Republic of Artsakh (de jure: Kalbajar Rayon). <s> "Gandzasar" means "treasure mountain" or "hilltop treasure" in Armenian. <s> The monastery holds relics believed to belong to St. John the Baptist and his father St Zechariah.
simple: The Gandzasar monastery (Armenian: Գանձասար) is an Armenian monastery in Nagorno-Karabakh, in the Mardakert region, near the village of Vank. <s> Gandzasar means treasure mountain in Armenian.

title: Naga National Council
complex: The Naga National Council (NNC) was a political organization of Naga people, active from the late 1940s to the early 1950s. <s> Under the leadership of Angami Zapu Phizo in the 1940s, it unsuccessfully campaigned for the secession of the Naga territory from India and creation for a sovereign Naga state.
simple: The Naga National Council was a political organization of Naga people, active from the late 1940s to the early 1950s. <s> Under the leadership of Angami Zapu Phizo in the 1940s, it unsuccessfully campaigned for the secession of the Naga territory from the Republic of India and creation for a sovereign Naga state.

title: SF9 (band)
complex: SF9 ( ; shortened from Sensational Feeling 9) is a South Korean boy group formed by FNC Entertainment. <s> SF9 is the company's first dance boy group to debut. <s> SF9 debuted on October 5, 2016 with the release of their first single album, "Feeling Sensation". <s> SF9's debut single album "Feeling Sensation" with lead single "Fanfare" being released on October 5, 2016.
simple: SF9 (Hangul: 에스에프나인) is a South Korean boy band formed by FNC Entertainment. <s> SF9 debuted with "Feeling Sensation" single album, which was launched on 5 October 2016.

title: Miguel-Ángel Cárdenas
complex: Miguel-Ángel Cárdenas (October 3, 1934 – June 2, 2015), also known as Michel Cardena, was a Colombian-Dutch, New Realism and Pop Art painter and a pioneer of video art in the Netherlands. <s> His works cover a variety of artistic media, including painting, drawing, video, photography, object assemblages and digital art. <s> Miguel-Ángel Cárdenas was born in Espinal, Colombia in 1934. <s> Between 1953 and 1957 he studied architecture at the National University of Colombia in Bogota, Colombia, and visual art at the Escuela de Bellas Artes Bogota.
simple: Miguel-Ángel Cárdenas (October 3, 1934 - June 2, 2015), also known as Michel Cardena, was a Colombian-Dutch, New Realism and Pop Art painter. <s> He was known for his video art in the Netherlands. <s> His works covered many artistic media, including painting, drawing, video, photography, object assemblages and digital art. <s> He was born in Espinal, Tolima, Colombia.

title: Natural history
complex: Natural history is a domain of inquiry involving organisms including animals, fungi and plants in their environment; leaning more towards observational than experimental methods of study. <s> A person who studies natural history is called a naturalist or natural historian. <s> Definitions from biologists often focus on the scientific study of individual organisms in their environment, as seen in this definition by Marston Bates: "Natural history is the study of animals and Plants – of organisms.
simple: Natural history is the study of plants and animals in the wild, and the environments they live in. <s> People who study natural history are called naturalists. <s> "Naturalist" is short for "natural historian".

title: Phoenix (band)
complex: Phoenix is an indie pop band from Versailles, France, consisting of Thomas Mars (lead vocals), Deck d'Arcy (bass/keyboards/backing vocals), Christian Mazzalai (guitar/backing vocals) and Laurent Brancowitz (guitar/keyboards/backing vocals). <s> They are best known for their singles "If I Ever Feel Better," "Lisztomania," "Too Young" and "1901."
simple: Phoenix is a French alternative rock band that was Grammy awarded. <s> It consists of Thomas Mars (vocals), Deck D'Arcy (bass) and Laurent Brancowitz and Christian Mazzalai who play guitar.

title: Riddarholm Church
complex: Riddarholm Church is the church of a former medieval abbey in Stockholm, Sweden. <s> The church serves as the final resting place of most Swedish monarchs. <s> Riddarholm Church is located on the island of Riddarholmen, close to the Royal Palace in Stockholm, Sweden. <s> The congregation was dissolved in 1807 and today the church is used only for burial and commemorative purposes. <s> Swedish monarchs from Gustavus Adolphus (d. 1632 AD) to Gustaf V (d. 1950) are entombed here (with only one exception: Queen Christina who is buried within St. Peter's Basilica in Rome), as well as the earlier monarchs Magnus III (d. 1290) and Charles VIII (d. 1470). <s> It has been discontinued as a royal burial site in favor of the Royal Cemetery and today is run by departments of the Swedish Government and Royal Court. <s> It is one of the oldest buildings in Stockholm, parts of it dating to the late-13th century, when it was built as a greyfriars monastery. <s> After the Protestant Reformation, the monastery was closed and the building transformed into a Protestant church.
simple: The Riddarholmen Church is a church building in Stockholm, Sweden. <s> It is on the island of Riddarholmen. <s> Several Swedish monarchs are buried here. <s> It is one of the oldest building in Stockholm, and dates back to the Middle Ages.

title: Rishang Keishing
complex: Rishang Keishing (25 October 1920 – 22 August 2017) was a senior politician of the Indian National Congress party and a Member of the Parliament of India representing Manipur in the Rajya Sabha, the upper house of the Indian Parliament. <s> Keishing served as Chief Minister of Manipur from 1980 to 1988 and from 1994 to 1997. <s> He was from Bungpa village, Phungyar District, Manipur. <s> He first entered Manipur State's Vidhan Sabha in 1972, winning Phungyar seat, and represented the seat for 30 years, winning the election 7 times. <s> In 2002, he lost in the assembly polls. <s> His son, Victor Keishing, reclaimed the seat a few years later. <s> After his defeat in the state polls in 2002, Rishang Keishing moved to Delhi, representing the state in Rajya Sabha for two terms, 2002 to 2008, and 2008 and 2014. <s> In 2007 he became the country's oldest parliamentarian. <s> He retired from Rajya Sabha in 2014, at the age of 93. <s> He died on Tuesday, 22 August 2017, aged 96 at Regional Institute of Medical Sciences Hospital, Imphal, Manipur.
simple: Rishang Keishing (25 October 1920 – 22 August 2017) was an Indian politician. <s> He was a senior politician of the Indian National Congress party was a Member of the Parliament of India representing Manipur in the Rajya Sabha, the upper house of the Indian Parliament. <s> Keishing served as Chief Minister of Manipur from 1980 to 1988 and from 1994 to 1997. <s> He was from Bungpa village, Ukhrul District, Manipur. <s> He was the oldest serving parliamentarian in the world, his term at Rajya Sabha, the Upper House of Indian Parliament ends 9 April 2014. <s> Keishing died on 22 August 2017, aged 96, in Imphal, Manipur of multiple organ failure.

title: Ya'akov Nehoshtan
complex: Ya'akov Nehoshtan (Hebrew: יעקב נחושתן ‎; 22 April 1925 – 17 April 2019) was an Israeli politician and diplomat. <s> He served as a member of the Knesset for Gahal between 1969 and 1974 and as ambassador to the Netherlands between 1982 and 1985. <s> Born in Kazanlak, Bulgaria, Nehoshtan attended high school in Vratsa and was a member of the Hashomer Hatzair youth group. <s> He made aliyah to Mandatory Palestine in 1944, and studied law at the Hebrew University of Jerusalem, gaining certification as a lawyer. <s> He joined the Irgun in 1944, and was arrested by the British authorities the following year and exiled to a detention camp in Eritrea. <s> In 1947 he was moved to a camp in Kenya. <s> In 1979 he was appointed Deputy Chief of Mission at the Embassy of Israel in Washington, D.C. and in 1982 became ambassador to the Netherlands, a post he held until 1985. <s> His son, Ido, served as commander of the Israeli Air Force.
simple: Ya'akov Nehoshtan (Hebrew: יעקב נחושתן‎; 22 April 1925 – 17 April 2019) was an Israeli politician, diplomat and lawyer. <s> Nehoshtan died on 17 April 2019, at the age of 93. <s> He served as a member of the Knesset for Gahal between 1969 and 1974. <s> He also served as Israeli Ambassador to the Netherlands between 1982 and 1985. <s> Nehoshtan was born in Kazanlak, Bulgaria. <s> He fled to Mandatory Palestine in 1944. <s> His son, Ido, served as commander of the Israeli Air Force.

title: Marianne Flynner
complex: Marianne Flynner, (born 16 September 1954) is a Swedish singer. <s> During the 1980s she travelled with Rocktåget, and sung as a backup-choir girl with among others, Roxette and Eva Dahlgren. <s> For eight years, she lived in California, before studying at Adolf Fredrik's Music School. <s> in the United States, she was influenced by country music. <s> By late 1993, Country Girl came out and her first album with own songs, and it peaked at 47th position at the Swedish album chart. <s> In 1994 came her second album, Tic-Tac Time, and in 1996 came her third, Sagt och gjort. <s> The albums consisted of acoustic, country-influenced, folk rock. <s> In 1995 she scored a hit together with Susanne Alfvengren and Åsa Jinder performing the Swedish women's national team fight song "Det är nu!" <s> during the 1995 FIFA Women's World Cup, which was played in Sweden. <s> On 4 January 1997, her song "Den sista december" received a Svensktoppen test, but failed to enter chart. <s> Another famous song is "Hennes ögon" from 1996, written by Lotta Ahlin, and recorded by, among others, Jill Johnson in 1998.
simple: Marianne Flynner, born 16 September 1954 in Stockholm, Sweden, is a Swedish singer. <s> During the 1980s, she travelled with Rocktåget, and sung as a backup-choir girl with among others, Roxette and Eva Dahlgren. <s> For eight years, she lived in California, before studying at Adolf Fredrik's Music School. <s> in the USA, she was influenced by country music. <s> By late 1993, Country Girl came out and her first album with own songs, and it peaked at 47th position at the Swedish album chart. <s> In 1994 came her second album, Tic-Tac Time, and in 1996 came her third, Sagt och gjort. <s> The albums consisted of accustic, country-influenced, folk rock. <s> In 1995 she scored a hit together with Susanne Alfvengren and Åsa Jinder performing the Swedish women's national team fight song "Det är nu!" <s> during the 1995 FIFA Women's World Cup, which was played in Sweden. <s> On 4 January 1997, her song "Den sista december" received a Svensktoppen test, but failed to enter chart. <s> Another famous song is "Hennes ögon" from 1996, written by Lotta Ahlin, and recorded by, among others, Jill Johnson in 1998.

title: Michael Thalbourne
complex: Michael Anthony Thalbourne, Ph.D. (24 March 1955 – 4 May 2010, Adelaide, South Australia) was an Australian psychologist who worked in the field of parapsychology. <s> He was educated at the University of Adelaide and the University of Edinburgh. <s> His books include: "A glossary of terms used in parapsychology" (2003), "The common thread between ESP and PK" (2004), and "Parapsychology in the Twenty-First Century: Essays on the future of Psychical Research" (2005). <s> He was first cousin twice removed on his mother's side of Supreme Court of South Australia judge George Coutts Ligertwood.
simple: Michael A. Thalbourne, Ph.D., (March 24 1955 – May 4 2010) was an Australian psychologist and parapsychologist. <s> He was educated at the University of Adelaide and the University of Edinburgh. <s> His books include: "A glossary of terms used in parapsychology" (2003), "The common thread between ESP and PK" (2004), and "Parapsychology in the Twenty-First Century: Essays on the future of Psychical research" (2005).

title: The Battle for Wesnoth
complex: The Battle for Wesnoth is a turn-based strategy video game with a fantasy setting, designed by Australian developer David White and first released in June 2003. <s> In "Wesnoth", the player attempts to build a powerful army by controlling villages and defeating enemies for experience. <s> The game is loosely based on the Sega Genesis games "Master of Monsters" and "Warsong". <s> "The Battle for Wesnoth" is free software, available under the GPLv2 license in source form and for a variety of computer operating systems. <s> The game is programmed in C++. <s> It is cross-platform, and runs on AmigaOS 4, BeOS, FreeBSD, Linux (including OS flavors running on GP2X and Nokia n800, n810, and n900 handheld devices), OS X/Darwin, Windows, MorphOS, NetBSD, OpenBSD, RISC OS, iOS, Solaris/illumos, Android, Playbook and Google Native Client running under Google Chrome. <s> Even when not counting this community content, the list of contributors to the official version of the game as displayed in-game contains over 550 unique entries (May 2010). <s> Developers of the game also include well-known authors from the free software and open source scene, like the co-founder of the Open Source Initiative and core Linux kernel developer Eric S. Raymond, or Linux kernel programmer Rusty Russell. <s> As of April 2010, The Battle for Wesnoth is available in about 50 languages, 9 of which have more than 90% of messages translated. <s> The first development release of "Wesnoth" 0.1 happened on June 18, 2003. <s> In October 2005, the game reached its 1.0 milestone release. <s> On January 29, 2012, version 1.10 was released. <s> On May 2, 2018, version 1.14.0 was released.
simple: The Battle for Wesnoth (or just Wesnoth) is a strategy video game. <s> It is designed by David White and the first released was made in June 2003. <s> The game is available under the GPL license. <s> The game is programmed in C++. <s> It is cross-platform and runs on AmigaOS 4, BeOS, FreeBSD, Linux, Mac OS X, Microsoft Windows, MorphOS, NetBSD, OpenBSD, RISC OS, iOS, Solaris and Android. <s> Some developers are well-known authors of other free and open-source projects. <s> The game is translated in more than 50 languages. <s> In 10 of them, the game is very well translated (These languages have more than 95% of messages translated). <s> The 1.14.5 version is the last release and was made the 18 September 2018.

title: Rockport, Arkansas
complex: Rockport is a city on the Ouachita River in Hot Spring County, Arkansas, United States. <s> As of the 2010 census, the population of Rockport was 755, down from 792 in 2000.
simple: Rockport is a city on the Ouachita River in Hot Spring County, Arkansas, United States. <s> As of the 2010 census, the population was 755, down from 792 in 2000.

title: Angular diameter
complex: The angular diameter, angular size, apparent diameter, or apparent size is an angular measurement describing how large a sphere or circle appears from a given point of view. <s> In the vision sciences, it is called the visual angle, and in optics, it is the angular aperture (of a lens).
simple: Angular size is a measurement of how large or small something is using rotational measurement.

title: Dudley Manlove
complex: Dudley Devere Manlove (June 11, 1914 – April 17, 1996) was an American radio announcer and an actor. <s> Manlove is known for his roles in the science fiction B movies "The Creation of the Humanoids" and "Plan 9 from Outer Space". <s> He also had multiple guest-starring roles in the television series "Dragnet" and "Alfred Hitchcock Presents".
simple: Dudley Manlove (June 11, 1914 - April 17, 1996) was an American radio announcer, movie actor, and television actor. <s> He had a few parts in movies that included the space alien, Eros, in Ed Wood's 1959 science fiction classic, "Plan 9 from Outer Space". <s> On television, he appeared in many series including "Dragnet" and "Alfred Hitchcock Presents".

title: Great cormorant
complex: The great cormorant ("Phalacrocorax carbo"), known as the great black cormorant across the Northern Hemisphere, the black cormorant in Australia, the large cormorant in India and the black shag further south in New Zealand, is a widespread member of the cormorant family of seabirds. <s> The genus name is Latinised Ancient Greek, from φαλακρός ("phalakros", "bald") and κόραξ ("korax", "raven"), and "carbo" is Latin for "charcoal". <s> It breeds in much of the Old World and the Atlantic coast of North America. <s> The great cormorant is a large black bird, but there is a wide variation in size in the species' wide range. <s> Weight is reported to vary from 1.5 kg to 5.3 kg . <s> Males are typically larger and heavier than females, with the nominate race ("P. c. carbo") averaging about 10% larger in linear measurements than the smallest race in Europe ("P. c. sinensis").
simple: The great cormorant "(Phalacrocorax carbo)", is a member of the cormorant family of seabirds. <s> It is a large black bird which breeds in much of the Old World and the Atlantic coast of North America. <s> There is a lot of in its size in different parts of the world.Weight is reported to vary from 1.5 kg to 5.3 kg.

title: Stringer (slag)
complex: Stringers are filaments of slag left in wrought iron after the production process. <s> In their correct proportions their presence is beneficial, as they help to control the ductility of the finished product, but when the proportion of slag is too high, or when the filaments run at right angles to the direction of tension, they can cause weakness.
simple: Stringers are thin strands of slag in wrought iron.

title: Markus Persson
complex: Markus Alexej Persson (] ; born 1 June 1979), better known as Notch, is a Swedish video game programmer and designer. <s> He is best known for creating the sandbox video game "Minecraft" and for founding the video game company Mojang in 2010, alongside Carl Manneh and Jakob Porser. <s> Persson's principal venture for founding Mojang was "Minecraft" which gained popularity and support since its tech demo in 2009. <s> Since then, he has gained significant notability within the video game industry, winning multiple awards and establishing relations with the industry's figureheads. <s> He retained his position as the lead designer of "Minecraft" until the game's official launch in 2011, after which he transferred creative authority to Jens Bergensten. <s> In November 2014, he left Mojang after its acquisition by Microsoft for $2.5 billion. <s> Microsoft eventually dissociated from Persson following comments on his Twitter account which faced criticism for accusations of being racist, transphobic, homophobic, and sexist.
simple: Markus "Notch" Persson (born 1 June 1979) is a Swedish game designer. <s> He is famous for creating the video game Minecraft. <s> Persson started the company Mojang AB in 2009. <s> On September 15 2014 he announced that he would be leaving the company.

title: Yoshi's Story
complex: Yoshi's Story is a side-scrolling platform game published and developed by Nintendo for the Nintendo 64. <s> It was first released in Japan in December 1997, and worldwide the following year. <s> It was re-released on the Wii's Virtual Console service in 2007, and later for the Wii U's Virtual Console in 2016. <s> Serving as a follow up to the Super NES title "Yoshi's Island", the game continues within the platform genre, presenting gameplay similar to its predecessor. <s> However, "Yoshi's Story" turns in a more puzzle-oriented direction, with the aspect of challenge being foremost tied to the achievement of a high score by strategic means. <s> Taking place within a pop-up storybook, the game features vivid pre-rendered 3D graphics, illustrating worlds that are crafted from different materials, such as cardboard, fabrics, plastic, and wood. <s> On each course, the goal is to fill the Fruit Frame by eating 30 pieces of fruit. <s> These may be found in abundance throughout every course, lying around, floating in bubbles, and even carried by some enemies. <s> The player can choose to eat everything they come across on their path.
simple: Yoshi's Story is a platform video game for the Nintendo 64 game console. <s> It was developed and published by Nintendo. <s> It was released in Japan on December 21, 1997, in North America on March 10, 1998, and in Europe on May 10, 1998. <s> It was later released for the Wii's Virtual Console service in 2007. <s> The game takes place in a pop-up book. <s> Each world is made from a different material, such as cardboard, fabric, plastic, and wood. <s> The goal in each stage is to fill the Fruit Frame by collecting 30 pieces of fruit. <s> They can be found lying on the stage, floating in bubbles, or carried by enemies.

title: Los Andes Province, Chile
complex: Los Andes Province is one of eight provinces of the central Chilean region of Valparaíso (V). <s> The city of Los Andes is the capital of the province. <s> As a province, Los Andes is a second-level administrative division, governed by a provincial governor who is appointed by the president. <s> Edith Quiroz Ortiz, appointed by president Piñera on April 22, 2010, is the first woman to hold the office of Governor of Los Andes. <s> The province spans a landlocked area of 3,054.1 sqkm , the second largest in the Valparaíso Region. <s> According to the 2002 census, Los Andes is the sixth most populous province in the region with a population of 91,683. <s> At that time, there were 74,104 people living in urban areas, 17,579 people living in rural areas, 46,325 men and 45,358 women.
simple: Los Andes Province is one of eight provinces of the central Chilean region of Valparaíso (V). <s> The city of Los Andes is the capital of the province. <s> As a province, Los Andes is a second-level administrative division, consisting of four communes ("comunas"). <s> The province is administered by a governor. <s> The Los Andes province has an area of 3054.1 sqmi, the second largest province in the Valparaíso region after the Petorca province. <s> s of 2002 (last national census), there were 91,683 people living in the province, giving it a population density of 30.019645722144006 /km2 inhabitants/km2..

title: Dipstick
complex: Some dipsticks are dipped into a liquid to perform a chemical test or to provide a measure of quantity of the liquid. <s> A testing dipstick is usually made of paper or cardboard and is impregnated with reagents that indicate some feature of the liquid by changing color. <s> In medicine, dipsticks can be used to test for a variety of liquids for the presence of a given substance, known as an analyte. <s> For example, urine dipsticks are used to test urine samples for haemoglobin, nitrite (produced by bacteria in a urinary tract infection), protein, nitrocellulose, glucose and occasionally urobilinogen or ketones. <s> Dipsticks can also be used to measure the quantity of liquid in an otherwise inaccessible space, by inserting and removing the stick and then checking the extent of it covered by the liquid. <s> The most familiar example is the oil level dipstick found on most internal combustion engines. <s> Other kinds of dipsticks are used to measure everything from fuel levels to the amount of beer left in an ale cask (Firkin).
simple: A dipstick is a tool which can be dipped into liquid to measure how much of it there is, or to test it for things. <s> A testing dipstick is usually made of paper or cardboard. <s> Measuring dipsticks show the amount of liquid in a container. <s> Measuring dipsticks are used by inserting and removing the stick and then checking how much of the stick is covered by the liquid. <s> The oil level dipstick is an example of a measuring dipstick found on most internal combustion engines.

title: Tarsier
complex: Tarsiers are any haplorrhine primates of the family Tarsiidae, which is itself the lone extant family within the infraorder Tarsiiformes. <s> Although the group was once more widespread, all of its species living today are found in the islands of Southeast Asia. <s> Fossils of tarsiiform primates are found in Asia, Europe, and North America, with disputed fossils from Africa, but extant tarsiers are restricted to several Southeast Asian islands in Indonesia, Philippines, and Malaysia, The fossil record indicates that their dentition has not changed much, except in size, in the past 45 million years. <s> The genus "Tarsius" has a longer fossil record than any other primate genus, but the assignment of the Eocene and Miocene fossils to the genus is questionable. <s> Tarsiers are small animals with enormous eyes; each eyeball is approximately 16 mm in diameter and is as large as, or in some cases larger than, its entire brain. <s> The unique cranial anatomy of the tarsier results from the need to balance their large eyes and heavy head so they are able to wait silently for nutritious prey. <s> Tarsiers have a strong auditory sense, and their auditory cortex is distinct. <s> Tarsiers also have long hind limbs, owing mostly to the elongated tarsus bones of the feet, from which the animals get their name. <s> The combination of their elongated tarsi and fused tibiofibulae makes them morphologically specialized for vertical clinging and leaping. <s> The head and body range from 10 to 15 cm in length, but the hind limbs are about twice this long (including the feet), and they also have a slender tail from 20 to 25 cm long. <s> Their fingers are also elongated, with the third finger being about the same length as the upper arm. <s> Most of the digits have nails, but the second and third toes of the hind feet bear claws instead, which are used for grooming. <s> Tarsiers have soft, velvety fur, which is generally buff, beige, or ochre in color. <s> Unlike many nocturnal vertebrates, tarsiers lack a light-reflecting layer (tapetum lucidum) of the retina and have a fovea. <s> The tarsier's brain is different from that of other primates in terms of the arrangement of the connections between the two eyes and the lateral geniculate nucleus, which is the main region of the thalamus that receives visual information. <s> The sequence of cellular layers receiving information from the ipsilateral (same side of the head) and contralateral (opposite side of the head) eyes in the lateral geniculate nucleus distinguishes tarsiers from lemurs, lorises, and monkeys, which are all similar in this respect. <s> Some neuroscientists suggested that "this apparent difference distinguishes tarsiers from all other primates, reinforcing the view that they arose in an early, independent line of primate evolution." <s> Tarsiers are the only extant entirely carnivorous primates: they are primarily insectivorous, and catch insects by jumping at them. <s> They are also known to prey on birds, snakes, lizards, and bats. <s> Gestation takes about six months, and tarsiers give birth to single offspring. <s> Young tarsiers are born furred, and with open eyes, and are able to climb within a day of birth. <s> They reach sexual maturity by the end of their second year. <s> Sociality and mating system varies, with tarsiers from Sulawesi living in small family groups, while Philippine and western tarsiers are reported to sleep and forage alone. <s> Tarsiers tend to be extremely shy animals.
simple: They were once widespread, but now tarsiers live only on islands in south-east Asia. <s> Fossils are found in Asia, Europe, and North America, and some disputed fossils from Africa. <s> The fossil record shows that their teeth have not changed much, except in size, in the past 45 million years. <s> They also have the longest continuous fossil record of any primate. <s> They have large eyes. <s> Each is about 16 mm wide.They are very sensitive to touch, and weigh as much as their entire brain. <s> Unlike many nocturnal animals, tarsiers lack a light-reflecting area (tapetum lucidum) of the eye. <s> They also have a fovea, which is also not usual in nocturnal animals. <s> The tarsier's brain is different from other primates in one respect. <s> The sequence of cell layers in the lateral geniculate nucleus getting information from both eyes is different from the set-up in lemurs, lorises, and monkeys. <s> "This apparent difference distinguishes tarsiers from all other primates, and reinforces the view that they arose in an early, independent line of primate evolution". <s> Tarsiers are the only primates which are wholly carnivorous. <s> They mainly eat insects, but some are also known to eat birds and snakes. <s> Pregnancy takes about six months, which is a long time for such a small animal. <s> Tarsiers give birth to single offspring. <s> Tarsiers have incredibly good hearing.

title: Petén Department
complex: Petén is a department of the Republic of Guatemala. <s> It is geographically the northernmost department of Guatemala, as well as the largest by area — at 35,854 km2 it accounts for about one third of Guatemala's area. <s> The capital is Flores. <s> The population at the 2002 Census was 366,735; the latest official estimate as of mid-2012 was 662,779. <s> The Petén department is bordered on the east by Belize and by Mexico on the north and west, with the Mexican state of Chiapas to the west, Tabasco to the northwest and Campeche to the north. <s> To the south it borders the Guatemalan departments of Alta Verapaz and Izabal. <s> Much of the western border with Mexico is formed by the Usumacinta River and its tributary the Salinas River. <s> Portions of the southern border of the department are formed by the rivers Gracias a Dios and Santa Isabel. <s> The main bodies of standing water in the department are the lakes Petén Itzá, Peténchel, Quexil, Salpetén and Macanche in the centre of the department; Yaxhá and Sacnab in the east, Petexbatún in the southwest, and Perdida, Larga, La Gloria, San Diego, Mendoza, El Repasto and Lacandón in the west. <s> The Petén department was created by decree of the Guatemalan government on 8 May 1866.
simple: Petén is a department of the nation of Guatemala. <s> It is geographically the most northern department of Guatemala. <s> It is about one third of Guatemala's area. <s> The capital is Flores. <s> The Petén department is bordered on the east by Belize and by Mexico on the north and west. <s> To the south it borders the Guatemalan departments of Alta Verapaz and Izabal. <s> Much of the western border with Mexico is formed by the Usumacinta River and its tributary the Salinas River. <s> Parts of the southern border of the department are formed by the rivers Gracias a Dios and Santa Isabel. <s> The main bodies of water in the department are the lakes Petén Itzá, Peténchel, Quexil, Salpetén and Macanche in the centre of the department; Yaxhá and Sacnab in the east, Petexbatún in the southwest, and Perdida, Larga, La Gloria, San Diego, Mendoza, El Repasto and Lacandón in the west. <s> The Petén department was formed by the Guatemalan government on 8 May 1866.

title: Ages of Man
complex: The Ages of Man are the stages of human existence on the Earth according to Greek mythology and its subsequent Roman interpretation.
simple: Ages of Man is an Ancient Greek myth that divides the history of the world into five eras.

title: Motorvision
complex: Motorvision is a home video by the American grunge band Soundgarden. <s> It was released on November 17, 1992. <s> It features eight songs performed live at the Paramount Theatre in Seattle, Washington on March 5 and 6, 1992, during the "Badmotorfinger" tour. <s> AllMusic gave it three out of a possible five stars. <s> AllMusic staff writer Greg Prato said, ""Motorvision" is an excellent sample of Soundgarden in concert." <s> "Motorvision" was originally released on VHS only. <s> The video features candid footage of the band and people associated with it, including Sub Pop co-founders Bruce Pavitt and Jonathan Poneman. <s> Before the first song begins, the band is introduced on stage by a clown, J. P. Patches. <s> The performance of "Slaves & Bulldozers" includes lyrics from Pearl Jam's "Alive" and The Doobie Brothers' "Jesus Is Just Alright".
simple: Motorvision is a home video released by the Seattle grunge band Soundgarden. <s> It was released on November 17, 1992. <s> It features eight songs performed live at the Paramount Theatre in Seattle, Washington on March 5, 1992 and March 6, 1992 during the "Badmotorfinger" tour. <s> "Motorvision" was released on VHS only, with no official DVD version available. <s> The video features candid footage of the band and people associated with it, including Sub Pop co-founders Bruce Pavitt and Jonathan Poneman. <s> Before the first song begins, the band is introduced on stage by a clown, J. P. Patches.

title: Serenade
complex: In music, a serenade ( ; also sometimes called serenata, from the ) is a musical composition and/or performance delivered in honor of someone or something. <s> Serenades are typically calm, light pieces of music. <s> The term comes from the Italian word , which itself derives from the Latin . <s> In the Baroque era, a serenata—which the form was called since it occurred most frequently in Italy and Vienna—was a typically celebratory or eulogistic dramatic cantata for two or more singers and orchestra, performed outdoors in the evening by artificial light. <s> Some composers of this type of serenade include Alessandro Stradella, Alessandro Scarlatti, Johann Joseph Fux, Johann Mattheson, and Antonio Caldara. <s> Often these were large-scale works performed with minimal staging, intermediate between a "cantata" and an opera. <s> The main difference between a "cantata" and a serenata, around 1700, was that the "serenata" was performed outdoors and therefore could use instruments which would be too loud in a small room (for example, trumpets, horns, and drums). <s> The most important and prevalent type of serenade in music history is a work for large instrumental ensemble in multiple movements, related to the divertimento, and mainly being composed in the Classical and Romantic periods, though a few examples exist from the 20th century. <s> Usually the
