simple: Flávio Costa (born 14 September, 1906) is a former Brazilian football player.

title: Frogs in captivity
complex: Frogs have recently become very popular exotic pets as they are generally undemanding, often visually appealing, and can be kept under fairly basic conditions. <s> Many frogs, especially common ones, can be inexpensive, but some specimens can cost several hundreds of Dollars/Pounds. <s> Their food is in most cases easily purchased. <s> Commonly kept pet frogs include ranids, hylids, bufonids, leptodactylids, and dendrobatids. <s> Pet frogs can be fed a wide variety of live foods, from pinhead crickets to mice and rats, depending on the size of the frog. <s> Particularly small pet frogs, like those of "Dendrobates" and "Phyllobates" species, will generally feed on small crickets, fruit flies, springtails, and other small arthropods. <s> Medium-sized pet frogs can be fed larger crickets, mealworms, butterworms, silkworms, grasshoppers, and even small fish. <s> Large pet frogs, like those in the genus "Ceratophrys" can be fed small fish, other frogs, reptiles, and small mammals such as mice or rats.
simple: Frogs have become a popular exotic pet. <s> They can be kept in basic conditions, compared to reptiles. <s> They are not expensive and their food is easily purchased. <s> Common pet frogs includes ranids, hylids, bufonids, leptodactylids, and dendrobatids. <s> Pet frogs can be fed a lot of different live foods. <s> Small pet frogs will only eat crickets, fruit flies, springtails and other small arthropods. <s> Medium-sized pet frogs can be fed larger crickets, mealworms, butterworms, silkworms, grasshoppers and small fish. <s> Large pet frogs like Ceratophrys frogs, can be fed small fish, other frogs, reptiles, and small mammals such as mice or rats.

title: Kiffis
complex: Kiffis is a commune in the Haut-Rhin department in Alsace in north-eastern France.
simple: Kiffis is a commune. <s> It is found in the Haut-Rhin department of eastern France.

title: Yurik Vardanyan
complex: Yuri Norayrovich Vardanyan ( ; , also transliterated Yurik Vardanian, 13 June 1956 – 1 November 2018) was a Soviet weightlifter. <s> Vardanyan won a gold medal at the 1980 Summer Olympics, becoming the world's first weightlifter to achieve a 400 kilogram total in the 82.5 kg weight category. <s> During his career he set several world records. <s> He trained at Lokomotiv in Leninakan, Armenia. <s> He earned the title Honoured Master of Sports of the USSR in 1977 and was awarded the Order of Lenin in 1985. <s> In 1994 he was elected a member of the International Weightlifting Federation Hall of Fame. <s> Vardanyan was born on 13 June 1956 in Leninakan, Armenian SSR (now Gyumri, Armenia), a city well known for its weightlifters. <s> He began weight training in 1970 under the guidance of his uncle Sergey Vardanyan. <s> Yuri Vardanyan died on 1 November 2018 at the age of 62. <s> On 2 April 2009 Vardayan was appointed as an advisor to President Serzh Sargsyan.
simple: Yuri Norayrovich Vardanyan (; , also transliterated Yurik Vardanian, 13 June 1956 – 1 November 2018) was a Soviet-Armenian weightlifter. <s> Vardanyan won a gold medal at the 1980 Summer Olympics, becoming the world's first weightlifter to win a 400 kilogram total in the 82.5 kg weight category. <s> During his career he set several world records. <s> In 1994 he was elected member of the International Weightlifting Federation Hall of Fame. <s> He was born in Leninakan, Soviet Union (now Gyumri, Armenia). <s> Vardanyan in Yerevan, Armenia on 1 November 2018 from a pulmonary embolism at the age of 89. <s> On 2 April 2009 he was appointed as President Serzh Sargsyan's adviser.

title: Ghotki District
complex: Ghotki District is a district in Pakistan, located in the Sindh province. <s> Its capital city is Ghotki City.
simple: Ghotki District is a district of Sindh Province, Pakistan.

title: Northrop Grumman B-2 Spirit
complex: The Northrop (later Northrop Grumman) B-2 Spirit, also known as the Stealth Bomber, is an American heavy strategic bomber, featuring low observable stealth technology designed for penetrating dense anti-aircraft defenses; it is a flying wing design with a crew of two. <s> The bomber can deploy both conventional and thermonuclear weapons, such as up to eighty 500 lb Mk 82 JDAM Global Positioning System-guided bombs, or sixteen 2400 lb B83 nuclear bombs. <s> The B-2 is the only acknowledged aircraft that can carry large air-to-surface standoff weapons in a stealth configuration. <s> Development started under the "Advanced Technology Bomber" (ATB) project during the Carter administration; its expected performance was one of the President's reasons for the cancellation of the Mach 2 capable B-1A bomber. <s> The ATB project continued during the Reagan administration, but worries about delays in its introduction led to the reinstatement of the B-1 program. <s> Program costs rose throughout development. <s> Designed and manufactured by Northrop, later Northrop Grumman, the cost of each aircraft averaged US$737 million (in 1997 dollars). <s> Total procurement costs averaged $929 million per aircraft, which includes spare parts, equipment, retrofitting, and software support. <s> The total program cost, which included development, engineering and testing, averaged $2.1 billion per aircraft in 1997. <s> Because of its considerable capital and operating costs, the project was controversial in the U.S. Congress. <s> The winding-down of the Cold War in the latter portion of the 1980s dramatically reduced the need for the aircraft, which was designed with the intention of penetrating Soviet airspace and attacking high-value targets. <s> During the late 1980s and 1990s, Congress slashed plans to purchase 132 bombers to 21. <s> In 2008, a B-2 was destroyed in a crash shortly after takeoff, though the crew ejected safely. <s> Twenty B-2s are in service with the United States Air Force, which plans to operate them until 2032. <s> The B-2 is capable of all-altitude attack missions up to 50000 ft , with a range of more than 6000 nmi on internal fuel and over 10000 nmi with one midair refueling. <s> It entered service in 1997 as the second aircraft designed to have advanced stealth technology after the Lockheed F-117 Nighthawk attack aircraft. <s> Though designed originally as primarily a nuclear bomber, the B-2 was first used in combat dropping conventional, non-nuclear ordnance in the Kosovo War in 1999. <s> It later served in Iraq, Afghanistan, and Libya.
simple: The Northrop Grumman B-2 Spirit, also called the Stealth Bomber, is an American strategic bomber. <s> It has a lot of stealth technology, and it is designed to get through many anti-aircraft defenses. <s> It can drop both conventional and nuclear weapons. <s> Two people fly the bomber, and it can drop up to 80 500 lb-class JDAM GPS-guided bombs, or sixteen 2400 lb B83 nuclear bombs. <s> The bomber began being designed as the "Advanced Technology Bomber" (ATB) during the Carter administration. <s> The designing of the ATB continued during the Reagan administration. <s> The bomber was designed and is made by Northrop Grumman, with help from Boeing. <s> Each aircraft cost US$737 million (in 1997 dollars). <s> Because the bomber is very expensive, the project was controversial in the U.S. Congress. <s> Congress wanted to buy 132 bombers, but during the late 1980s and 1990s, Congress reduced this to 21. <s> In 2008, a B-2 was destroyed in a crash shortly after takeoff. <s> 20 B-2s are being used by the United States Air Force. <s> Although the B-2 was supposed to be a mainly nuclear bomber, it was first used in combat to drop normal bombs on Serbia during the Kosovo War in 1999.

title: Avaí FC
complex: Avaí Futebol Clube (] ) is a Brazilian football team from Florianópolis in Santa Catarina, founded on September 1, 1923. <s> Their home stadium is Estádio Aderbal Ramos da Silva, also known as Ressacada, with a capacity of 17,800. <s> They play in blue and white shirts, shorts and socks. <s> Their best known supporter is tennis player Gustavo Kuerten. <s> The club was founded after a businessman called Amadeu Horn gave football kits to a group of boys. <s> The boys played a match against a team called Humaitá, and won. <s> On September 1, 1923, at Amadeu Horn's house, the club was founded, known as Avahy Football Club at the time. <s> The team was named Avahy after the Battle of Avay, in the Paraguayan War. <s> In the following year, it became the first Santa Catarina State Championship champion. <s> Avaí has played in the Brazilian First Division ("Série A") eight times: 1974, 1976, 1977, 1979, 2009, 2010, 2011 and 2015. <s> In 1998, they won their only national title, the Brazilian Third Division ("Série C"). <s> From 1999 to 2008 and from 2012 to 2014, they played in the Série B with their best campaigns being the third place attained in 2004 (when Avaí reached the Final Four, but could not be promoted to the First Division because only the two best placed teams were promoted) and 2008. <s> In 2008 they finished 3rd in the championship and were promoted to the First Division for the first time in 30 years. <s> In its first year playing in Série A, Avaí finished in 6th place, thus qualifying for the Copa Sudamericana. <s> The team eventually was relegated in 2011, and returned to the Série A in 2014, when the team won the promotion in the last round. <s> Avaí won the most Santa Catarina State Championship titles in the 20th Century (13), and is currently the all-time record state champions (16), just ahead of cross-bridge rivals Figueirense (15). <s> Avaí's greatest rival is Figueirense. <s> Avaí's stadium is Estádio Aderbal Ramos da Silva (though it's mostly referred to as Ressacada), and it was opened in 1983. <s> It has a maximum capacity of 17,800 people, but its record crowd was 33,000 at the Catarinense Championship final.
simple: Avaí Futebol Clube, or Avaí as they are usually called, is a Brazilian football team from Florianópolis in Santa Catarina, founded on September 1, 1923. <s> Home stadium is the Ressacada stadium, capacity 19,000. <s> They play in blue shirts, shorts and socks. <s> The club was founded after a businessman called Amadeu Horn gave football kits to a group of boys. <s> These boys played a match against a team called Humaitá, and won. <s> On September 1, 1923, at Amadeu Horn's house, the club was founded, being called at that time Avahy Football Club. <s> The team was named Avahy after the Battle of Avahy, in the Paraguayan War In the following year, it became the first Santa Catarina State Championship champion. <s> Avaí played the Brazilian First Division ("Série A") four times: in 1974, 1976, 1977 and 1979. <s> In 1998, it won its only national title, the Brazilian Third Division ("Série C"). <s> Since 1999, it plays the Série B and the best campaigns happened in 2001 and 2004, when Avaí reached the Final Four, but could not be promoted to the First Division (only the two best placed teams were promoted). <s> Avaí is the club with more titles won in the Santa Catarina State Championship in the 20th century (13). <s> Avaí's greatest rival is Figueirense F.C.. <s> Avaí's stadium is Estádio da Ressacada, inaugurated in 1983, with a maximum capacity of 19,000 people.

title: 2028 Summer Olympics
complex: The 2028 Summer Olympics, officially known as the Games of the XXXIV Olympiad, and commonly known as Los Angeles 2028/LA 2028, is a forthcoming international multi-sport event that is scheduled to take place from July 21 to August 6, 2028, in Los Angeles, California, United States. <s> The process of bidding for the host city was originally scheduled to begin in 2019, with the winning bid due to be announced in 2021. <s> However, following the withdrawal of a number of cities from the bidding process for both the 2022 Winter Olympics and the 2024 Summer Olympics, the International Olympic Committee (IOC) resolved in July 2017 to jointly award both the 2024 and 2028 Games. <s> Thus on July 31, 2017, an agreement was reached wherein Los Angeles would bid for the 2028 Games with $1.8 billion of additional funding from the IOC, which then cleared the way for Paris to be confirmed as host of the 2024 Games. <s> Both cities were formally announced as winners of their respective Games at the 131st IOC Session in Lima, Peru, on September 13, 2017. <s> The bid was praised by the IOC for using a record-breaking number of existing and temporary facilities and relying on corporate money.
simple: The 2028 Summer Olympics, which will be officially known as the Games of the XXXIV Olympiad, is a sporting event that will happen from July 21 to August 6 in Los Angeles, California, United States. <s> Applying to host the games was supposed to begin in 2019. <s> The host city was supposed to be announced in 2021. <s> In July 2017, The International Olympic Committee decided to award 2024 and 2028 Games at the same time. <s> On July 31, 2017, an agreement was announced that Los Angeles would apply to host the 2028 Summer Olympics. <s> On September 13, 2017, the hosts for both Olympic games was announced at the 131st IOC Session in Lima, Peru.

title: 2015 Washington, D.C., quadruple murder incident
complex: On May 14, 2015, three members of the Savopoulos family—Savvas, Amy, and their son Philip—as well as their housekeeper, Veralicia Figueroa, were killed at the Savopoulos home in Washington, D.C. <s> The victims were held hostage for 19 hours, starting on May 13. <s> Ten-year-old Philip was tortured in order to coerce $40,000 in cash from the family. <s> The perpetrator(s) restrained them with duct tape before killing them, then set the house on fire. <s> They all sustained blunt force trauma, and Philip was also stabbed. <s> The Savopouloses were a prominent, upper-class family in the Woodley Park neighborhood of Northwest Washington. <s> Savvas Savopoulos was the CEO and president of American Iron Works, a construction company that played a role in building the Verizon Center. <s> Two teenage daughters, Abigail and Katerina Savopoulos, were not present at the scene when the four were killed.
simple: The 2015 Washington, D.C., mass murder occurred on May 14, 2015. <s> Three members of the Savopoulos family (Savvas, Amy, and their son, Philip) were murdered at their home in Washington, D.C.. <s> Their housekeeper, Veralicia Figueroa, was also murdered. <s> The victims were held hostage for nineteen hours, from May 13. <s> Ten-year-old Philip was tortured in order to coerce $40,000 in cash from the family. <s> The killers restrained the victims with duct tape before killing them. <s> They then set the house on fire. <s> All the victims had been hit with something, and Philip was also stabbed. <s> The Savopouloses were an upper-class family. <s> They lived in the Woodley Park neighborhood of Northwest Washington. <s> Savvas Savopoulos was the CEO and President of American Iron Works. <s> This is a construction company that helped build the Verizon Center. <s> The family left behind two teenage daughters, Abigail and Katerina Savopoulos.

title: The Stinky Cheese Man and Other Fairly Stupid Tales
complex: The Stinky Cheese Man and Other Fairly Stupid Tales is a postmodern children's book written by Jon Scieszka and illustrated by Lane Smith. <s> Published in 1992 by Viking, it is a collection of twisted, humorous parodies of famous children's stories and fairy tales, such as "Little Red Riding Hood", "The Ugly Duckling" and "The Gingerbread Man". <s> Illustrated in a unique style by Lane Smith, the book won "The New York Times" Best Illustrated Book award, was a Caldecott Honor book, and has won numerous other awards in various countries. <s> The book was re-released in a 10th anniversary edition in 2002 and included a new story, a parody of "The Boy Who Cried Wolf" on the dust jacket. <s> The foreword includes a parody of "Goldilocks and the Three Bears" as an example of a "Fairly Stupid Tale". <s> Also, the table of contents includes the title, "The Boy Who Cried Cow Patty", a story found nowhere in the book. <s> The latter story was printed on the back of the dust jacket for the book's 10th anniversary edition (whereas the original edition had the Little Red Hen complaining about buying this book, while asking who "this ISBN guy" is and complaining that she is only in three of the pages as a book gag).
simple: The Stinky Cheese Man and Other Fairly Stupid Tales is a children's book by Jon Scieszka. <s> It was published in 1992 by Viking. <s> It is a collection of stories which make fun of famous children's stories and fairy tales, such as "Chicken Licken", "The Gingerbread Man" (changed to The Stinky Cheese Man of the title), "The Ugly Duckling", and others. <s> It was illustrated by Lane Smith, who won the Caldecott Honor for his illustrations. <s> This book also won the New York Times Best Illustrated Book award, among numerous awards in many countries. <s> The book was also re-released in a new edition in 2002 to celebrate its tenth anniversary. <s> This story was printed on the back of the dust jacket.

title: Battenheim
complex: Battenheim is a commune in the Haut-Rhin department in Alsace in north-eastern France. <s> It forms part of the Mulhouse Alsace Agglomération, the inter-communal local government body for the Mulhouse conurbation.
simple: Battenheim is a French commune. <s> It is in the Haut-Rhin department of eastern France.

title: Tour guide
complex: A tour guide (U.S.) or a tourist guide (European) is a person who provides assistance, information on cultural, historical and contemporary heritage to people on organized tours and individual clients at educational establishments, religious and historical sites, museums, and at venues of other significant interest, attractions sites.
simple: A tour guide (also known as tourist guide in Europe) is a person who gives information about a place or a place's history to "tourists" (people who are traveling for fun).

title: Puneri Pagadi
complex: The Puneri Pagadi is a distinctive style of turban, which is considered as a symbol of pride and honor in the city of Pune. <s> It was introduced two centuries ago. <s> Though it is a symbol of honour, the use of the "pagadi" has changed over the years and now it is also used on traditional days in colleges. <s> To preserve the identity of the "pagadi", there were demands from the locals to grant it a Geographical Indication (GI) status. <s> Their demand was fulfilled and the "pagadi" became an intellectual property on 4 September 2009. <s> The "pagadi" was introduced in the 19th century by Mahadev Govind Ranade, a social reformer. <s> Later, it was worn by many leaders like Lokmanya Tilak, J.S. Karandikar, D.D. Sathye, Dr. Vitthalrao Gade, Tatyasaheb Kelkar and Datto Vaman Potdar. <s> The "pagadi" became more popular in 1973 after the Marathi play, "Ghashiram Kotwal". <s> The "pagadi" is used mostly on special occasions like wedding ceremonies and traditional days in schools and colleges. <s> Youngsters wear it while performing the "gondhal" art form. <s> The "pagadi", being a symbol of honour, is also used as a souvenir. <s> It also finds usage in period films and theatres. <s> The 10-membered "Shree Puneri Pagadi Sangh" had applied before the Geographical Indication Registry to get a Geographical Indication (GI) tag for the "pagadi". <s> Great Mission Group Consultancy, which promotes intellectual property rights filed the application on behalf of them. <s> The aim was to make the "pagadi" recognizable, preserve its identity and also that of the "Puneri" culture. <s> Consequently, on 4 September 2009, the Geographical Indication status was given to the headgear and the "pagadi" became the official cultural identity of Pune. <s> Thus, the "pagadi" got the Intellectual Property Right (IPR) and selling of any turban made outside Pune, under the name of "Puneri pagadi" became illegal. <s> Along with the "Puneri pagadi", IPR has been previously issued to Indian products like Darjeeling tea, Banarasi saris, Tirupati ladoos, among others.
simple: Puneri Pagadi is a turban, a cloth worn on the head. <s> "Puneri" means "belonging to Pune" and "pagadi" means turban. <s> The "pagadi" was introduced 200 years ago by Mahadev Govind Ranade, who was a social reformer. <s> It was also later worn by leaders like Lokmanya Tilak, J.S. Karandikar, D.D. Sathye, Tatyasaheb Kelkar and Datto Vaman Potdar. <s> The "pagadi" became more famous in 1973 after a Marathi play. <s> The "pagadi" used to be worn by people to show pride but now it is also worn on special occasions. <s> The "pagadi" is used in marriages. <s> It is also used on special events in schools and colleges (commonly on traditional days). <s> It is used by actors while performing "gondhal" art form. <s> They are the ones who applied for getting a GI tag for the "pagadi". <s> Actually, Great Mission Group Consultancy submitted the application for them. <s> The aim of this was to protect the identity of the "pagadi". <s> They also wanted to protect the "Puneri" culture. <s> In 2009, it was given the status of Geographic Indication (GI) which means that the "pagadi" will be a property of only Pune. <s> The application was accepted and on 4 September 2009, the "pagadi" became an intellectual property. <s> No one else can sell any such turban under the name of "Puneri Pagadi" outside Pune.Only Brahmins used to use this pagadi in that era. <s> Before this, the GI tag was also given to Indian products like Tirupati "ladoos", Darjeeling tea, Banarasi "saris".

title: Mab (moon)
complex: Mab , or Uranus XXVI (26), is an inner satellite of Uranus. <s> It was discovered by Mark R. Showalter and Jack J. Lissauer in 2003 using the Hubble Space Telescope. <s> It was named after Queen Mab, a fairy queen from English folklore who is mentioned in William Shakespeare's play "Romeo and Juliet". <s> Because the moon is small and dark, it was not seen in the heavily scrutinized images taken by "Voyager 2" during its Uranus flyby in 1986. <s> However, it is brighter than another moon, Perdita, which was discovered from Voyager's photos in 1997. <s> This led scientists to re-examine the old photos again, and the satellite was finally found in the images. <s> The size of Mab is not known exactly. <s> If it is as dark as Puck, it is about 24 km in diameter. <s> On the other hand, if it is brightly coloured like the neighbouring moon Miranda, it would be even smaller than Cupid and comparable to the smallest outer satellites. <s> Mab is heavily perturbed. <s> The actual source for perturbation is still unclear, but is presumed to be one or more of the nearby orbiting moons. <s> Following its discovery, Mab was given the temporary designation S/2003 U 1. <s> The moon is also designated Uranus XXVI.
simple: It was found by Mark R. Showalter and Jack J. Lissauer in 2003 using the Hubble Space Telescope. <s> It was named after Queen Mab, a fairy queen from English folklore who is noted in William Shakespeare's play "Romeo and Juliet". <s> Because the moon is small and dark, it was not seen in the images taken by "Voyager 2" during its Uranus flyby in 1986. <s> However, it is brighter than another moon, Perdita, which was discovered from "Voyager's" photos in 1997. <s> This led scientists to look at the old photos again, and the moon was finally found in the images. <s> If it is as dark as Puck, then it is about 24 km in diameter. <s> On the other hand, if it is brightly coloured like the neighbouring moon Miranda, then it would be even smaller than Cupid and comparable to the smallest farther moons. <s> Mab is heavily perturbed, meaning its movement is not only caused by the gravity of another large thing. <s> The actual source for perturbation is still unclear, but is probably one or more of the nearby orbiting moons. <s> Following its discovery, Mab was given the code name S/2003 U 1. <s> The moon is also known as Uranus XXVI.

title: Bactria–Margiana Archaeological Complex
complex: The Bactria–Margiana Archaeological Complex (short BMAC), also known as the Oxus civilization, is the modern archaeological designation for a Bronze Age civilization of Central Asia, dated to c. 2400–1600 BC, located in present-day northern Afghanistan, eastern Turkmenistan, southern Uzbekistan and western Tajikistan, centred on the upper Amu Darya (Oxus River). <s> Its sites were discovered and named by the Soviet archaeologist Viktor Sarianidi (1976). <s> "Bactria" was the Greek name for the area of Bactra (modern Balkh), in what is now northern Afghanistan, and "Margiana" was the Greek name for the Persian satrapy of Marguš, the capital of which was Merv, in modern-day southeastern Turkmenistan. <s> Sarianidi's excavations from the late 1970s onward revealed numerous monumental structures in many sites, fortified by impressive walls and gates. <s> Reports on the BMAC were mostly confined to Soviet journals until the last years of the Soviet Union, so the findings were largely unknown to the West until Sarianidi's work began to be translated in the 1990s.
simple: The Bactria–Margiana Archaeological Complex (or BMAC, also known as the Oxus civilization) is the modern archaeological name for a Bronze Age culture of Central Asia, dated to ca. 2300–1700 BCE. <s> It was in present-day Turkmenistan, northern Afghanistan and northeastern Iran, southern Uzbekistan and western Tajikistan. <s> Its sites were discovered and named by the Soviet archaeologist Viktor Sarianidi (1976). <s> "Bactria" was the Greek name for the area of "Bactra" (modern Balkh), in what is now northern Afghanistan. <s> "Margiana" was the Greek name for the Persian satrapy of Margu, in today's Turkmenistan. <s> Sarianidi's excavations from the late 1970s onward many buildings in many sites. <s> Reports on the BMAC were mostly in Soviet journals, until the last years of the Soviet Union. <s> The findings were unknown to the West until Sarianidi's work was translated in the 1990s.

title: Palm Springs, Florida
complex: Palm Springs is a village in Palm Beach County, Florida, United States, situated between Greenacres, Lake Clarke Shores, Lake Worth, and West Palm Beach. <s> As of the 2010 United States Census, had a population of 18,928.
simple: Palm Springs is a city of Florida in the United States.

title: Fatima Bhutto
complex: Fatima Bhutto ( ; born 29 May 1982) is a Pakistani writer. <s> Born in Kabul, she is daughter of Murtaza Bhutto, niece of former Pakistani Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto and granddaughter of former Pakistani Prime Minister Zulfiqar Ali Bhutto. <s> She is a critic of her aunt Benazir Bhutto and her husband Asif Ali Zardari, whom she accused of being involved in her father's murder.
simple: Fatima Bhutto (born 1982) is a young Pakistani poet and writer. <s> She is the niece of former Pakistani Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto and grand-daughter of former Prime Minister Zulfiqar Ali Bhutto.

title: Data storage
complex: Data storage is the recording (storing) of information (data) in a storage medium. <s> DNA and RNA, handwriting, phonographic recording, magnetic tape, and optical discs are all examples of storage media. <s> Recording is accomplished by virtually any form of energy. <s> Electronic data storage requires electrical power to store and retrieve data. <s> A recording medium is a physical material that holds information. <s> Newly created information is distributed and can be stored in four storage media–print, film, magnetic, and optical–and seen or heard in four information flows–telephone, radio and TV, and the Internet as well as being observed directly. <s> Digital information is stored on electronic media in many different recording formats. <s> With electronic media, the data and the recording media are sometimes referred to as "software" despite the more common use of the word to describe computer software. <s> With (traditional art) static media, art materials such as crayons may be considered both equipment and medium as the wax, charcoal or chalk material from the equipment becomes part of the surface of the medium.
simple: A data storage device is a device for recording (storing) information (data). <s> Recording can be done using virtually any form of energy. <s> "Electronic data storage" is storage which requires electricity to store and get back that data. <s> A recording medium is a physical material that holds data expressed in any of the existing recording formats. <s> Most often the term is used with computers. <s> With electronic media, the data and the recording medium is sometimes referred to as "software" despite the more common use of the word to describe computer software.

title: Howard County, Missouri
complex: Howard County is a county in the U.S. state of Missouri, with its southern border formed by the Missouri River. <s> As of the 2010 census, the population was 10,144. <s> Its county seat is Fayette. <s> The county was organized January 23, 1816, and named for Benjamin Howard, the first Governor of the Missouri Territory. <s> Settled originally by migrants from the Upper South, it is part of the region historically known as Little Dixie. <s> It is part of the Columbia, Missouri, metropolitan area. <s> Located on the north bank of the Missouri River, Howard County was settled primarily from the Upper Southern states of Kentucky, Tennessee and Virginia. <s> The migrants brought slaves and slaveholding traditions with them, and cultivated hemp and tobacco, crops of Middle Tennessee. <s> Howard was one of several counties settled mainly by Southerners along the Missouri River in the center of the state. <s> Because of this, this area became known as Little Dixie, and Howard County was at its heart. <s> Following the 1848 revolutions in the German nations, many German immigrants also came to this region, developing farms. <s> Due to the reliance on slave labor, by 1860 African-American slaves composed at least 25 percent of the county's population. <s> Given their backgrounds and cultural affiliations, many Howard County residents supported the Confederacy during the Civil War. <s> Ethnic German immigrants and descendants tended to support the Union. <s> After the end of Reconstruction, whites enforced Jim Crow laws and racial segregation in the county to maintain white supremacy. <s> In the most violent period, at the turn of the 20th century, five African Americans were lynched in Howard County from 1891 to 1914: Olli Truxton, Frank Embree, Thomas Hayden, Arthur McNeal, and Dallas Shields. <s> Howard County tied with Pike County for the highest rate of lynchings in the state. <s> The county continued to be developed for agriculture and is still largely rural. <s> However, Howard County has lost population since its peak in 1880. <s> The mechanization of farming reduced the demand for labor, and many workers left for jobs in the cities and less oppressive societies. <s> By 2000 African Americans in the county had declined to less than seven percent of the total. <s> In the early 21st century, nearly one-third of the residents identify as being of German ancestry, reflecting the wave of mid-19th century immigration. <s> According to the U.S. Census Bureau, the county has a total area of 472 sqmi , of which 464 sqmi is land and 7.7 sqmi (1.6%) is water. <s> As of the census of 2000, there were 10,212 people, 3,836 households, and 2,631 families residing in the county. <s> The population density was 22 people per square mile (8/km2). <s> There were 4,346 housing units at an average density of 9 per square mile (4/km2). <s> The racial makeup of the county was 91.13% White, 6.84% Black or African American, 0.33% Native American, 0.12% Asian, 0.08% Pacific Islander, 0.40% from other races, and 1.10% from two or more races. <s> Approximately 0.86% of the population were Hispanic or Latino of any race. <s> 32.4% were of German, 16.1% American, 8.9% English and 8.3% Irish ancestry. <s> There were 3,836 households out of which 31.50% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 55.30% were married couples living together, 9.50% had a female householder with no husband present, and 31.40% were non-families. <s> 27.30% of all households were made up of individuals and 13.30% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. <s> The average household size was 2.46 and the average family size was 2.98. <s> In the county, the population was spread out with 24.00% under the age of 18, 13.30% from 18 to 24, 25.20% from 25 to 44, 21.30% from 45 to 64, and 16.10% who were 65 years of age or older. <s> The median age was 37 years. <s> For every 100 females, there were 94.00 males. <s> For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 94.40 males. <s> The median income for a household in the county was $31,614, and the median income for a family was $40,167. <s> Males had a median income of $26,369 versus $19,950 for females. <s> The per capita income for the county was $15,198. <s> About 7.50% of families and 11.60% of the population were below the poverty line, including 14.70% of those under age 18 and 14.40% of those age 65 or over.

title: Dungeon
complex: A dungeon is a room or cell in which prisoners are held, especially underground. <s> Dungeons are generally associated with medieval castles, though their association with torture probably belongs more to the Renaissance period. <s> An oubliette or bottle dungeon is a form of dungeon which is accessible only from a hatch or hole (an "angstloch") in a high ceiling.
simple: A dungeon is a room or cell in a castle to keep prisoners. <s> An oubliette is a type of dungeon that can be entered by using a trapdoor in the ceiling.

title: Photocatalysis
complex: In chemistry, photocatalysis is the acceleration of a photoreaction in the presence of a catalyst. <s> In catalysed photolysis, light is absorbed by an adsorbed substrate.
simple: Photocatalysis is using light as a catalyst to increase the rate of a photoreaction. <s> Catalysis is using a catalyst to change the rate of a chemical reaction.

title: Malacology
complex: Malacology is the branch of invertebrate zoology that deals with the study of the Mollusca (mollusks or molluscs), the second-largest phylum of animals in terms of described species after the arthropods. <s> Mollusks include snails and slugs, clams, octopus and squid, and numerous other kinds, many of which have shells. <s> One division of malacology, conchology, is devoted to the study of mollusk shells. <s> Malacology derives from Greek , "malakos", "soft"; and , "-logia". <s> Those who study malacology are known as malacologists. <s> Those who study primarily or exclusively the shells of mollusks are known as conchologists.
simple: Malacology is the study of molluscs. <s> These animals include snails, slugs, octopus, squid, and bivalves generally, such as clams and mussels. <s> Most of them have shells. <s> Those scientists who study molluscs are called "malacologists".

title: Dīs Pater
complex: Dīs Pater (pronounced ] ) was a Roman god of the underworld. <s> Dis was originally associated with fertile agricultural land and mineral wealth, and since those minerals came from underground, he was later equated with the chthonic deities Pluto (Hades) and Orcus. <s> "Dīs Pater" was commonly shortened to simply Dīs and this name has since become an alternative name for the underworld or a part of the underworld, such as the City of Dis of Dante's "The Divine Comedy", which comprises Lower Hell.
simple: Dīs Pater (Latin: “Father of riches”) was a god of the underworld in Roman mythology. <s> Originally a chthonic deity associated with riches and fertility, he became commonly equated with the Greek god Hades alongside the Roman deity Orcus, and so came to be associated with the dark and dismal realm of the dead. <s> The god's name, "Dīs Pater", was often shortened to simply Dīs, which came to be used as an alternative name for the underworld, as is the case in Dante's "The Divine Comedy", in which the City of Dis comprises Lower Hell.

title: Rolf Rüssmann
complex: Rolf Rüssmann (13 October 1950 – 2 October 2009) was a German international footballer who played as a defender for FC Schalke 04, Club Brugge and Borussia Dortmund.
simple: Rolf Rüssmann (13 October, 1950 – 2 October, 2009) was a German football player.

title: Robert Woodrow Wilson
complex: Robert Woodrow Wilson (born January 10, 1936) is an American astronomer who, along with Arno Allan Penzias, discovered cosmic microwave background radiation (CMB) in 1964. <s> The pair won the 1978 Nobel prize in physics for their discovery. <s> While working on a new type of antenna at Bell Labs in Holmdel Township, New Jersey, they found a source of noise in the atmosphere that they could not explain. <s> After removing all potential sources of noise, including pigeon droppings on the antenna, the noise was finally identified as CMB, which served as important corroboration of the Big Bang theory.
simple: Robert Woodrow Wilson (born 10 January 1936) is an American Nobel Prize-winning astronomer. <s> He found part of the cosmic microwave background radiation in 1964. <s> Fourteen years later, they won the 1978 Nobel Prize in Physics for the discovery. <s> He was working at the Bell Telephone Laboratories in New Jersey on an antenna with Arno Penzias.

title: Paulo Henrique (footballer, born 1943)
complex: Paulo Henrique Souza de Oliveira (born 5 January 1943), usually called Paulo Henrique, is a Brazilian former professional football player, who played as defender and currently a manager.
simple: Paulo Henrique Souza de Oliveira (born 5 January, 1943) is a former Brazilian football player.

title: Vrbanjci
complex: Vrbànjci is a village in the Bosnia and Herzegovina, Republika Srpska, in the Municipality of Kotor Varoš, as well as former Municipality in Kotor Varoš former County. <s> Vrbanjci lies along the Vrbanja river (for which it is named), between its tributaries Jezerka, Bosanka, and Cvrcka. <s> Vrbanjci was formerly known as Plitska. <s> This name was given to the village when the largest part of the settlement was situated near Bosanka (Plitka Rika, Shallow River). <s> On this toponym there is a neighboring village named Plitska, almost forgotten since its destruction in 1992. <s> The history of this area commemorates the battle on The Field of Večići, approximately Mlâvâ locality, on the Vrbanja river, where was the clash between the Ottomans army and repressed pro Bosnian forces, from almost the entire State of Bosnia. <s> Legend of there slayed brothers (shahids), who while dead carried their own heads is reconted until today. <s> There is a turbeh, in the village of Večići in the memory. <s> According to the historical context, it probably occurred around 1463, when Bosnia fell under Ottoman Administration. <s> During the last War in Bosnia (1992–1995), Serb paramilitary and police forces have committed crimes against the civilian population in Vrbanjci and surrounding villages. <s> Most of the Bosniak population are back in their native lands and have restored their estates, with the assistance of the international community, but above all thanks to their own resources.
simple: Vrbànjci is a village in the Bosnia and Herzegovina, in the Municipality of Kotor Varoš <s> Vrbanjci spread along the Vrbanja river (for which it is named), between its tributaries Jezerka, Bosanka, and Cvrcka. <s> The history of this area commemorates the battle on The Field of Večići, on the Vrbanja river, where was the clash between the Ottomans army and repressed pro Bosnian forces, from almost the entire State of Bosnia. <s> According to the historical context, it probably happened around 1463, when Bosnia fell under Ottoman Administration. <s> During the last War in Bosnia (1992–1995), Serb paramilitary and police forces have committed severe crimes against the civilian Bosnisk's and Croats populations in Vrbanjaca and surrounding villages, including Večići <s> Most of the refugies Bosniak population are back in their native lands and have restored their houses, with the assistance of the international community, but above all thanks to their own resources.

title: Lorne Chabot
complex: Lorne "Chabotsky" Chabot (October 5, 1900 – October 10, 1946) was a Canadian professional ice hockey player. <s> Chabot played in the National Hockey League from 1926 to 1937. <s> He was a member of two Stanley Cup championship teams, the New York Rangers in 1928, and the Toronto Maple Leafs in 1932. <s> Chabot played for the New York Rangers, Toronto Maple Leafs, Montreal Canadiens, Chicago Black Hawks, Montreal Maroons, and New York Americans. <s> Chabot won the Vezina Trophy in 1934-35 for being the league's best goaltender. <s> Chabot played in the two longest games in NHL history, losing the longest in 1935-36 as a member of the Montreal Maroons and winning the second longest in 1932-33 as a member of the Toronto Maple Leafs. <s> Both games went into the sixth overtime; both final scores were 1-0. <s> He was the first hockey player to appear on the cover of "Time Magazine".
simple: Lorne "Chabotsky" Chabot (October 5, 1900 in Montreal, Quebec - October 10 1946) was a Canadian ice hockey goaltender. <s> Lorne played in the National Hockey League from 1926 to 1937. <s> During this time, he played for the New York Rangers, Toronto Maple Leafs, Montreal Canadiens, Chicago Black Hawks, Montreal Maroons, and New York Americans. <s> Lorne won the 1935 Vezina Trophy for the being the league's best goaltender. <s> He was the first hockey player to appear on the cover of Time Magazine.

title: East Berlin
complex: East Berlin was the capital city of the German Democratic Republic from 1949 to 1990. <s> Formally, it was the Soviet sector of Berlin, established in 1945. <s> The American, British, and French sectors were known as West Berlin. <s> From 13 August 1961 until 9 November 1989, East Berlin was separated from West Berlin by the Berlin Wall. <s> The Western Allied powers did not recognise East Berlin as the GDR's capital, nor the GDR's authority to govern East Berlin. <s> On 3 October 1990, the day Germany was officially reunified, East and West Berlin formally reunited as the city of Berlin. <s> The Western Allies (the US, UK, and France) never formally acknowledged the authority of the East German government to govern East Berlin; the official Allied protocol recognised only the authority of the Soviet Union in East Berlin in accordance with the occupation status of Berlin as a whole. <s> The United States Command Berlin, for example, published detailed instructions for U.S. military and civilian personnel wishing to visit East Berlin. <s> In fact, the three Western commandants regularly protested against the presence of the East German National People's Army (NVA) in East Berlin, particularly on the occasion of military parades. <s> Nevertheless, the three Western Allies eventually established embassies in East Berlin in the 1970s, although they never recognised it as the capital of East Germany. <s> Treaties instead used terms such as "seat of government." <s> On 3 October 1990, East and West Germany and East and West Berlin were reunited, thus formally ending the existence of East Berlin. <s> City-wide elections in December 1990 resulted in the first “all Berlin” mayor being elected to take office in January 1991, with the separate offices of mayors in East and West Berlin expiring at the time, and Eberhard Diepgen (a former mayor of West Berlin) became the first elected mayor of a reunited Berlin. <s> Since reunification, the German government has spent vast amounts of money on reintegrating the two halves of the city and bringing services and infrastructure in the former East Berlin up to the standard established in West Berlin. <s> Despite the large sums of economic aid poured into East Berlin, there still remain obvious differences between the former East and West Berlins. <s> East Berlin has a distinct visual style; this is partly due to the greater survival of prewar façades and streetscapes, with some even still showing signs of wartime damage. <s> The unique look of Stalinist architecture that was used in East Berlin (along with the rest of the former GDR) also contrasts markedly with the urban development styles employed in the former West Berlin. <s> Additionally, the former East Berlin (along with the rest of the former GDR) retains a small number of its GDR-era street and place names commemorating German socialist heroes, such as Karl-Marx-Allee, Rosa-Luxemburg-Platz, and Karl-Liebknecht-Straße. <s> Many such names, however, were deemed inappropriate (for various reasons) and changed after a long process of review. <s> At the time of German reunification, East Berlin comprised the boroughs of
simple: East Berlin was the name of the eastern part of Berlin between 1949 and 1990. <s> It was the Soviet sector of Berlin that was established in 1945. <s> The American, British and French sectors became West Berlin, a " de facto" part of West Germany . <s> From 13 August 1961 until 9 November 1989 it was separated from West Berlin by the Berlin Wall. <s> The Western Allies (the USA, Great Britain and France) only recognized the power of the Soviet Union in East Berlin in accordance with the occupation status of Berlin as a whole. <s> The three Western commandants regularly protested about the presence of the East German National People's Army (NPA) in East Berlin. <s> Nevertheless, the three Western Allies eventually established embassies in East Berlin in the 1970s, although they never recognized it as East Germany's capital. <s> Treaties instead used terms such as "seat of government." <s> On 3 October 1990, West Germany and East Germany were united, and East Berlin ceased to exist. <s> Since reunification, the German government has spent lots of money on rejoining the two halves of the city and bringing services and buildings in the former East Berlin up to the standard in West Berlin. <s> There are still differences between eastern and western Berlin. <s> There are a lot more pre-war buildings in Eastern Berlin, some still show signs of wartime damage. <s> At the time of German reunification, East Berlin comprised the boroughs of

title: Shuri, Okinawa
complex: Gibo and Shuri Stations on the Okinawa Urban Monorail lay within the boundaries of Shuri. <s> Shuri Castle Park, Tamaudun, and other major sites are within easy walking distance of Shuri Station, which is currently the terminus of the monorail line, though there are plans to extend it in the future.
simple: Today, Shuri Station it is the last stop on the Okinawa Urban Monorail.

title: Dave Legeno
complex: David Legeno (12 October 1963 – July 2014) was an English actor and mixed martial artist. <s> Legeno was born David Ronald Murray in Marylebone, London, England. <s> He tried to change his last name to Legend; however, because of unclear handwriting it was read as "Legeno". <s> Legeno's first major film role was in Guy Ritchie's "Snatch". <s> He had roles in "Batman Begins", "", "Centurion", and "Last Knights". <s> Most notably, Legeno played the werewolf, Fenrir Greyback, in "Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince", "Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows – Part 1", and "Part 2". <s> Legeno's body was found by a pair of hikers on July 6, 2014 in Death Valley, California, United States. <s> Due to the remote area, a helicopter was called in to retrieve his remains. <s> Legeno died of heat-related issues and may have been dead for three to four days before his body was discovered. <s> No foul play is suspected.
simple: David "Dave" Legeno (12 October 1963 – 6 July 2014) was an English actor, boxer, and mixed martial artist. <s> Legeno was born in Marylebone, London. <s> He also had roles in "Batman Begins" (2005), "Stormbreaker" (2006) and "Snow White and the Huntsman" (2012). <s> He was best known for his role as the werewolf Fenrir Greyback in three "Harry Potter" movies; "Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince" (2009), "Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows – Part 1" (2010) and "Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows – Part 2" (2011). <s> Legeno was found dead by hikers on 6 July 2014. <s> His cause of death was heat stroke.

title: Lake Mweru
complex: Lake Mweru (also spelled "Mwelu", "Mwero") is a freshwater lake on the longest arm of Africa's second-longest river, the Congo. <s> Located on the border between Zambia and Democratic Republic of the Congo, it makes up 110 km of the total length of the Congo, lying between its Luapula River (upstream) and Luvua River (downstream) segments. <s> Mweru means 'lake' in a number of Bantu languages, so it is often referred to as just 'Mweru'. <s> The move of the boma from Chiengi to Kalungwishi had the effect of leaving the Belgian boma at Pweto a free rein at the northern end of the lake, leading a hundred years later to about 33 km2 of Zambian territory next to Pweto being ceded to the DR Congo (then Zaire). <s> See the Luapula Province border dispute for further details and references.
simple: Lake Mweru is a freshwater lake on the Congo River. <s> It is on the border between the Democratic Republic of the Congo and Zambia. <s> The lake makes up 110 km of the border. <s> 'Mweru' means 'lake' in many Bantu languages, so the lake is often just called Mweru. <s> This border dispute is known as Luapula Province border dispute.

title: Markaryd Municipality
complex: Markaryd Municipality ("Markaryds kommun") is a municipality in south-west Kronoberg County in southern Sweden, where the town Markaryd is seat.
simple: Markaryd Municipality is a municipality in Kronoberg County in southern Sweden. <s> The seat is in Markaryd.

title: 20 BC
complex: Year 20 BC was either a common year starting on Wednesday or Thursday or a leap year starting on Tuesday, Wednesday or Thursday (link will display the full calendar) of the Julian calendar (the sources differ, see leap year error for further information) and a common year starting on Tuesday of the Proleptic Julian calendar. <s> At the time, it was also known as the Year of the Consulship of Appuleius and Nerva (or, less frequently, year 734 "Ab urbe condita"). <s> The denomination 20 BC for this year has been used since the early medieval period, when the Anno Domini calendar era became the prevalent method in Europe for naming years.
simple: Year 20 BC was either a common year starting on Wednesday or Thursday or a leap year starting on Tuesday, Wednesday or Thursday of the Julian calendar. <s> At the time, it was known as the Year of the Consulship of Appuleius and Nerva.

title: Line of succession to the Bahraini throne
complex: Succession to the Bahraini throne is determined by primogeniture amongst the male descendants of Sheikh Isa bin Ali Al Khalifa (1848 – 1932). <s> However, the ruling King of Bahrain has the right to appoint any of his other sons as his successor if he wishes to. <s> The current ruler of Bahrain is King Hamad bin Isa Al Khalifah. <s> After Isa bin Muhammad Al Khalifa come firstly the descendants of Hakim Hamad bin Isa Al Khalifa, and then last in line the descendants of Hakim Isa bin Ali Al Khalifa.
simple: Succession to the Bahraini throne is done by primogeniture from the male descendants of Sheikh Isa bin Ali Al Khalifa (1848 – 1932). <s> However, the ruling King of Bahrain can select any of his other sons as his successor if he wishes to. <s> The current ruler of Bahrain is King Hamad bin Isa Al Khalifah. <s> After Sheikh Isa bin Muhammad Al Khalifa come firstly the descendants of Hakim Hamad bin Isa Al Khalifa, and then last in line the descendants of Hakim Isa bin Ali Al Khalifa.

title: Remy
complex: Remy or Rémy (] English: , or ) is a name of French origin, and is associated with the Latin name Remigius.
simple: Remy or Rémy is a French name.

title: Wolong National Nature Reserve
complex: Wolong National Nature Reserve , also known as Wolong Special Administrative Region , is a protected area located in Wenchuan County, Sichuan Province, People's Republic of China. <s> Established in 1963 with an initial size of about 20,000 hectares, the reserve was further expanded in 1975, covering an area of about 200,000 hectares in the Qionglai Mountains region. <s> There are over 4,000 different species recorded in the reserve. <s> According to China's Third National Giant Panda Survey, Wolong National Nature Reserve houses about 150 wild individuals of highly endangered giant pandas. <s> The reserve is also a home to many other endangered species including: snow leopards, red pandas, golden monkeys, white-lipped deer and many precious plants. <s> Before the devastating 2008 Wenchuan earthquake Wolong got up to 200,000 visitors every year. <s> Its area is superseded by the Wolong Special Administrative Region. <s> In June 1980, the China Conservation and Research Center for the Giant Panda was established at Wolong with the efforts of both World Wildlife Fund (WWF) and the Chinese government. <s> To this date, researchers have conducted many breeding research projects on giant pandas and have successfully bred 66 panda cubs. <s> A mountain stream runs through the Wolong Valley (where the reserve is); the stream is heavily armoured with boulders and smaller rounded stones. <s> Stream waters are rather alkaline with pH levels in the range of 8.91. <s> (Hogan, 2007) Water quality turbidity is quite high due to extensive sand and gravel mining in stream. <s> According to a 2001 research by Dr. Jianguo Liu of Michigan State University, the rate of destruction is higher after the reserve's creation than before its creation. <s> Using NASA's satellite images and records of population, Liu's research team concluded that due to tourism and the increase in local population, the reserve is facing an unprecedented threat. <s> "Tourists don't think they have an impact on panda habitat, but indirectly each visitor has some impact," Liu said. <s> "We don't see ourselves as a destructive force, but we are."
simple: Wolong National Nature Reserve is a national park in Sichuan Province, People's Republic of China. <s> It was established in 1963. <s> The reserve has an area of about 200,000 hectares. <s> There are over 4,000 different species recorded in the reserve. <s> Wolong National Nature Reserve houses more than 150 highly endangered giant pandas. <s> In June 1980, the China Research and Conservation Center for the Giant Panda was established. <s> The World Wildlife Fund (WWF) and the Chinese government cooperated to establish the center. <s> Researchers have made trials on how to breed the giant pandas. <s> They have successfully bred 66 panda cubs. <s> A mountain stream runs through the Wolong Valley (where the Reserve is); the stream is heavily armoured with boulders and smaller rounded stones. <s> Stream waters are rather alkaline with pH levels in the range of 8.91. <s> (Hogan, 2007) Water quality turbidity is quite high due to extensive sand and gravel mining in stream. <s> According to a 2001 research by Dr. Jianguo Liu of Michigan State University, the rate of destruction is higher after the reserve's creation than before its creation. <s> Using NASA's satellite images and records of the number of people there, Liu's research team concluded that due to tourism and the increase in the number of people, the reserve is facing an unprecedented threat. <s> "Tourists do not think they have an impact on panda habitat, but indirectly each visitor has some impact," Liu said. <s> "We do not see ourselves as a destructive force, but we are."

title: Otto Arosemena
complex: Otto Arosemena Gómez (19 July 1925 – 20 April 1984) was President of Ecuador from 16 November 1966 to 1 September 1968. <s> Arosemena was born in Guayaquil to Luis Alberto Arosemena Tola and Mercedes Gómez Santistevan. <s> He came from a well-known Guayaquil family; his cousin and his cousin's father had both previously served as president. <s> He went to elementary school at San José de los Hermanos Cristianos School and to high school at Salesiano Cristóbal Colón High School and Vicente Rocafuerte High School in Guayaquil. <s> He graduated from the University of Guayaquil in 1955 with a degree in law. <s> He was already involved in public life during his education: in 1951, he was named a member of the Electoral Tribunal of Guayas. <s> Later, he became president of the tribunal. <s> Beginning in 1954, his political ascendancy was vertiginous. <s> In 1954, he was elected Deputy for Guayas Province in the National Congress; he was reelected in 1956. <s> In 1957 he was elected president of the Chamber of Deputies, in 1960 he was elected Senator and member of the Monetary Board on behalf of Congress, and in 1961 he was named President of the Monetary Board and Vice President of the Senate. <s> He fought against the military junta that in July 1963 had overthrown his cousin, President Carlos Julio Arosemena Monroy. <s> In 1965, when the country was facing one of its worst political, social, and economic crises—a result of dictatorial misrule—he founded a new political party in Quito called the Democratic Institutionalist Coalition ("Coalición Institucionalista Demócrata", CID). <s> One year later, he was elected Deputy of the Constituent Assembly held by "President" Yerovi Indaburu. <s> The Constituent Assembly elected Arosemena President of Ecuador on 16 November 1966. <s> His government, though short, greatly increased Ecuador's development and ensured the consolidation of democracy. <s> In accordance with the law, he called presidential elections, and Velasco Ibarra won for his fifth and final time. <s> Arosemena finished his term on 31 August 1968. <s> Arosemena's political adversaries later attacked his policies, particularly with respect to oil policy. <s> He responded by writing the book "Infamy and Truth" ("Infamia y verdad"), in which he addresses his administration's oil policy.
simple: Otto Arosemena Gómez (19 July 1925 – 20 April 1984) was President of Ecuador, November 16, 1966 to September 1, 1968. <s> Arosemena was born on 19 July 1925 in Guayaquil, Ecuador. <s> He studied at University of Guayaquil. <s> In 1965, when the country was facing one of its worst political, social, and economic crises—a result of dictatorial misrule—he founded a new political party in Quito called the Democratic Institutionalist Coalition (Coalición Institucionalista Demócrata, CID). <s> One year later, he was elected Deputy of the Constituent Assembly held by "President" Yerovi Indaburu. <s> The Constituent Assembly elected Arosemena President of Ecuador on November 16, 1966. <s> His government, though short, greatly increased Ecuador's development and ensured the consolidation of democracy. <s> In accordance with the law, he called presidential elections, and Velasco Ibarra won for his fifth and final time. <s> Arosemena finished his term on August 31, 1968. <s> Arosemena's political adversaries later attacked his policies, particularly with respect to oil policy. <s> He responded by writing the book Infamy and Truth (Infamia y verdad), in which he addresses his administration's oil policy.

title: Posadas, Misiones
complex: Posadas (] ) is the capital city of the Argentine province of Misiones, in its south, at the far north-east of the country on the left bank of the Paraná River, opposite Encarnación, Paraguay. <s> The city has an area of 965 km2 and a population of 324,756, and the Greater Posadas area has a population of over 351,000 ( 2010 census ).
simple: Posadas is the capital city of the Misiones Province in Argentina.

title: Koji Miyata
complex: Koji Miyata (宮田 孝治 , Miyata Koji , born January 15, 1923) is a former Japanese football player. <s> He played for Japan national team.
simple: Koji Miyata (宮田 孝治, Miyata Koji, born January 15, 1923) is a former Japanese football player. <s> He has played for the Japanese national team.

title: Abu Nuwas
complex: Abū Nuwās al-Ḥasan ibn Hānī al-Ḥakamī (756–814), known as Abū Nuwās ( ; , "Abū Novās"), was a classical Arabic poet. <s> Born in the city of Ahvaz in modern-day Iran, to an Arab father and a Persian mother, he became a master of all the contemporary genres of Arabic poetry. <s> He also entered the folkloric tradition, appearing several times in "The Book of One Thousand and One Nights".
simple: Abu-Nuwas al-Hasan ben Hani al-Hakami (750–810), or Abū-Nuwās, was a classical Arabic poet. <s> He is in "The Book of One Thousand and One Nights".

title: Dino Risi
complex: Dino Risi (23 December 1916 – 7 June 2008) was an Italian film director. <s> With Mario Monicelli, Luigi Comencini, Nanni Loy and Ettore Scola, he was one of the masters of "Commedia all'italiana". <s> He was born in Milan. <s> His biggest hits were "Poor, But Handsome (Poveri ma belli)", followed by two sequels, which he also directed; "A Difficult Life (Una vita difficile"); "The Easy Life (Il sorpasso)"; "Opiate '67" or, in a cut version, "15 From Rome (I Mostri)"; and "Scent Of A Woman (Profumo di Donna)", which was remade by Martin Brest starring Al Pacino in 1992.
simple: Dino Risi (23 December 1917 – 7 June 2008) was an Italian movie director. <s> His best known works were "Poor, But Handsome (Poveri ma belli)", followed by two sequels, which he also directed; "A Difficult Life (Una vita difficile"); "The Easy Life (Il sorpasso)"; "Opiate '67" or, in a cut version, "15 From Rome (I Mostri)"; and "Scent Of A Woman (Profumo di Donna)".

title: Kaufman, Texas
complex: Kaufman is a city in Kaufman County, Texas, United States. <s> The population was 6,703 at the 2010 census. <s> It is the county seat of Kaufman County. <s> Kaufman was founded as "Kings Fort", named after Dr. William P. King who established the fort in 1840 after purchasing 2.5 sqmi of land where the city is now located.
simple: Kaufman is a city in the U.S. state of Texas. <s> It is the county seat of Kaufman County.

title: Ryan Jimmo
complex: Ryan Jimmo (November 27, 1981 – June 26, 2016) was a Canadian mixed martial artist who competed in the light heavyweight division of the Ultimate Fighting Championship. <s> He mostly fought in Canada and competed on the of "The Ultimate Fighter". <s> Jimmo was the former MFC Light Heavyweight Champion. <s> Jimmo was involved in a parking lot altercation early in the morning of June 26, 2016, in Edmonton, Alberta, Canada. <s> He spoke to the occupant of a truck, and, as he was walking away, that truck ran him over and drove away.
simple: Ryan Jimmo (November 27, 1981 – June 26, 2016) was a Canadian mixed martial artist. <s> He competed in the light heavyweight division of the Ultimate Fighting Championship. <s> He mostly fought in Canada. <s> He competed on the of "The Ultimate Fighter". <s> He was the former MFC Light Heavyweight Champion. <s> Jimmo died, aged 34, at a hospital in Edmonton, Alberta on June 26, 2016 after being run-over by a truck because he was involved in a fight with the truck driver.

title: Jason Bonham
complex: Jason John Bonham (born 15 July 1966) is an English drummer. <s> He is the son of the late Led Zeppelin drummer John Bonham and Patricia "Pat" Bonham (née Phillips).
simple: Jason John Bonham (born 15 July 1966) is an English rock drummer who is noted for being the son of Led Zeppelin drummer John Bonham, as well for his own music.

title: Lichtenberg
complex: Lichtenberg is the eleventh borough of Berlin, Germany. <s> In Berlin's 2001 administrative reform it absorbed the former borough of Hohenschönhausen. <s> The district contains the Tierpark Berlin in Friedrichsfelde, the larger of Berlin's two zoological gardens. <s> Lichtenberg was also the site of the extensive headquarters complex of the Stasi, the East German intelligence service. <s> Prior to the establishment of the GDR it housed the main office of the Soviet Military Administration in Berlin, and before that it was an officers' mess of the Wehrmacht. <s> The complex is now the location of the Stasi Museum. <s> The Berlin-Hohenschönhausen Memorial is on the site of the main remand prison of the Stasi. <s> Lichtenberg is also the location of the German-Russian Museum, the historical venue of the unconditional surrender of the German armed forces (Wehrmacht) on 8 May 1945.
simple: Lichtenberg is a borough of Berlin, Germany. <s> In 2001 it took over the old borough of Hohenschönhausen. <s> Lichtenberg contains the Tierpark Berlin, the larger of Berlin's two zoological parks. <s> Lichtenberg was also the site of the headquarters of the Stasi, the East German intelligence service. <s> The complex is now a museum. <s> The Berlin-Hohenschönhausen Memorial is on the site of the main prison of the Stasi.

title: Johnson County, Texas
complex: Johnson County is a county located in the U.S. state of Texas. <s> As of the 2010 census, its population was 150,934. <s> Its county seat is Cleburne. <s> Johnson County is named for Middleton Johnson, a Texas Ranger, soldier, and politician.
simple: Johnson County is a county in the U.S. state of Texas. <s> In 2010, 150,934 people lived there. <s> The county seat is Cleburne.

title: BandNews FM
complex: BandNews FM is a Brazilian all-news radio network owned by Grupo Bandeirantes de Comunicação. <s> First broadcast in May 20, 2005, it is the first Brazilian radio network that provides non-stop news programming 24 hours a day, considering that CBN does intersperse news with talk shows.
simple: Rádio BandNews FM is a Brazilian "all news" radio network. <s> It is owned by Grupo Bandeirantes de Comunicação. <s> It first started in 20 March 2005.

title: Douchy-lès-Ayette
complex: Douchy-lès-Ayette is a commune in the Pas-de-Calais department in the Hauts-de-France region of France.
simple: Douchy-lès-Ayette is a commune. <s> It is found in the region Nord-Pas-de-Calais in the Pas-de-Calais department in the north of France.

title: Jovita Carranza
complex: Jovita Carranza is the 44th Treasurer of the United States after being appointed by President Donald Trump. <s> She previously served as the Deputy Administrator for the United States Small Business Administration from December 2006 to January 2009. <s> Appointed by President George W. Bush, Carranza was unanimously confirmed by the U.S. Senate. <s> Prior to the SBA appointment, Carranza served as Vice President of Air Operations for United Parcel Service (UPS) at its facility in Louisville, Kentucky. <s> Previously, Carranza was the President and CEO of the JCR Group, a consulting firm with a focus on business development, profit and loss management, operations, logistics and systems optimization. <s> On April 4, 2019, President Trump proposed Carranza to be Administrator of the Small Business Administration, replacing Linda McMahon. <s> Her nomination was submitted to the Senate on August 1, 2019.
simple: She is the 44th Treasurer of the United States after being appointed by President Donald Trump. <s> She was the Deputy Administrator for the United States Small Business Administration from December 2006 to January 2009 during George W. Bush's presidency. <s> Carranza was Vice President of Air Operations for United Parcel Service (UPS) the world's largest package delivery company at its facility in Louisville, Kentucky. <s> Carranza was the President & CEO of the JCR Group, a consulting firm with a focus on business development, profit and loss management, operations, logistics and systems optimization. <s> On April 4, 2019, President Trump nominated Carranza to be Administrator of the Small Business Administration, replacing Linda McMahon.

title: Ancient Egyptian royal titulary
complex: The royal titulary or royal protocol is the standard naming convention taken by the pharaohs of ancient Egypt. <s> It symbolises worldly power and holy might and also acts as a sort of mission statement for the reign of a monarch (sometimes it even changed during the reign). <s> The full titulary, consisting of five names, did not come into standard usage until the Middle Kingdom but remained in use as late as the Roman Empire. <s> G5-O33 The Horus name is the oldest form of the pharaoh's name, originating in prehistoric Egypt. <s> Many of the oldest-known Egyptian pharaohs were known only by this title. <s> The Horus name was usually written in a serekh, a representation of a palace façade. <s> The name of the pharaoh was written in hieroglyphs inside this representation of a palace. <s> Typically an image of the falcon god Horus was perched on top of or beside it. <s> At least one Egyptian ruler, the Second Dynasty pharoah Seth-Peribsen, used an image of the god Set instead of Horus, perhaps signifying an internal religious division within the country. <s> He was succeeded by Khasekhemwy, who placed the symbols of both Set and Horus above his name. <s> Thereafter, the image of Horus always appeared alongside the name of the pharaoh. <s> By the time of the New Kingdom, the Horus name was often written without the enclosing serekh. <s> The name is first definitively used by the First Dynasty pharaoh Semerkhet, though it only became a fully independent title by the Twelfth Dynasty. <s> This particular name was not typically framed by a cartouche or serekh, but always begins with the hieroglyphs of a vulture and cobra resting upon two baskets, the dual noun "nebty". <s> G8 Also known as the "Golden Horus Name", this form of the pharaoh's name typically featured the image of a Horus falcon perched above or beside the hieroglyph for gold. <s> The meaning of this particular title has been disputed. <s> One belief is that it represents the triumph of Horus over his uncle Seth, as the symbol for gold can be taken to mean that Horus was "superior to his foes". <s> Gold also was strongly associated in the ancient Egyptian mind with eternity, so this may have been intended to convey the pharaoh's eternal Horus name. <s> Similar to the Nebty name, this particular name typically was not framed by a cartouche or serekh. <s> title: Juan José Lara Ortiz
complex: Juan Jose Lara Ortiz (born November 30, 1965 in Sevilla) is a wheelchair basketball athlete from Spain. <s> He has a physical disability: he is 1 point wheelchair basketball player. <s> He played wheelchair basketball at the 1996 Summer Paralympics. <s> His team was third. <s> They beat the United States 66-60 to finish third.
