title: Pontoon Dock DLR station
complex: Pontoon Dock is a station on the Docklands Light Railway (DLR) in Silvertown in east London, which is on the Woolwich Arsenal branch, opened on 2 December 2005. <s> It is located in the east of Silvertown in the London Borough of Newham, in the redevelopment zone known as Silvertown Quays, and is in Travelcard Zone 3.
simple: Pontoon Dock DLR station, on the Woolwich Arsenal branch of the DLR, opened on 2 December 2005. <s> It is in the east of Silvertown in the London Borough of Newham, and is in Travelcard Zone 3.

title: Hot n Cold
complex: "Hot n Cold" is a song by American singer Katy Perry. <s> The song was written by Perry, Dr. Luke, and Max Martin and produced by Dr. Luke and Benny Blanco for her second studio album, "One of the Boys" (2008). <s> The track was released as the album's second single on September 9, 2008. <s> The lyrics address an unstable romantic relationship caused by a partner's mood swings. <s> The song reached number three on the "Billboard" Hot 100, becoming Perry's second consecutive top three single, following "I Kissed a Girl". <s> It also became Perry's second top five single in the United Kingdom, Australia, Ireland and New Zealand, and topped the charts in Finland, Germany, Canada, Norway, Spain, and Denmark, among others. <s> To date, "Hot n Cold" has sold over 5.7 million copies in the US, making it one of Perry's highest-selling singles in the nation.
simple: "Hot N Cold" is a single by pop singer Katy Perry. <s> The song came from the album "One of the Boys". <s> The single was released on September 30, 2008. <s> The song reached number one in Canada, Denmark, Norway, Finland, Switzerland, Germany, Austria, and Belgium (Wallonia). <s> It climbed to the top three in the US and the top five in the UK, Australia, and New Zealand.

title: Mošovce
complex: Mošovce is one of the largest villages in the historical region of Turiec, currently in the Turčianske Teplice District in the Žilina Region of northern Slovakia. <s> Many preserved historical buildings are the evidence of the 770 years of its existence. <s> It was mentioned for the first time in 1233 in the deed of donation by King Andrew II. <s> Originally, Mošovce was made up of two settlements: The first one, "Machyuch", was located in the area of today’s "Starý Rad", and the second one, "Terra Moys", which gave the village its current name, occupied the place of the present day "Vidrmoch". <s> And it is the name of the second settlement meaning The Land of Mojš, which makes us believe that the whole village once belonged to certain Mr. "Mojš", whose name might have been an abbreviation of a compound Slavic name "Mojtech", similar to the names "Vojtech" or "Mojmír". <s> Throughout history the name of the village has undergone many variations ranging from "Mossovych", "Mosocz", "Mossowecz", "villa regia Mayos alio nomine Mossovych", "oppidioum Mayus sue Mosocz", "Mosocz olim Mayus" to the present-day Mošovce. <s> The name of a separate ancient part of Mošovce, a former settlement "Chornukov", has been preserved in the modern form of "Čerňakov". <s> Yet another part of the village bears the name of "Mazan". <s> Mošovce first developed as a royal settlement with a free advocacy, and from the middle the 14th century as a privileged town subjected to the royal castle of Blatnica. <s> In 1527 it fell into the hands of the Révay family, who suppressed the town privileges of Mošovce for almost 400 years. <s> In the past, Mošovce was an important craft center of the Turiec region. <s> Crafts experienced a surprising expansion, and there were around 15 guilds active in the town; the bootmaker and the most famous furrier guild were the ones to survive for the longest time. <s> The present-day Mošovce can be characterized as an important tourist area with many sights. <s> The surroundings of Mošovce are truly unique. <s> A complex of historic tree avenues and groves creates an aesthetic and impressive landscape, which works as an extension to the woodland scenery of the Veľká Fatra Mountains with its peaks of "Tlstá", "Ostrá" and "Drienok". <s> This mountain range belongs to the most attractive ones in Slovakia. <s> Limestone and dolomite rock formations of fantastic shapes, as well as the beautiful nature in the nearby Blatnická and Gaderská Valleys attract people from all parts of the world. <s> One of the most remarkable monuments is a Rococo-Classical Manor House from the 2nd half of the 18th century with an extensive English park. <s> Other sites in the town include: The birthplace of Ján Kollár, a Neo-Gothic Catholic church with a valuable altar built on the spot of its ancient predecessor, a Lutheran church built in 1784, a Mausoleum now hosting the Museum of Crafts, an Art-Nouveau greenhouse, and a garden pavilion from 1800. <s> Mošovce has produced several notable personalities, including Frico Kafenda (1883–1963), composer and pedagogue; Anna Lacková-Zora (1899–1988), writer; Štefan Krčméry (1892–1955), literary critic, historian, and poet; Jur Tesák Mošovský, Baroque playwright, church dignitary, and a religious writer, whose works belong to the period of Humanism; and Miloslav Schmidt, the founder of the amateur fire brigades in Slovakia. <s> However, the most well known person born in Mošovce is likely the Slavic poet, philosopher, and Lutheran preacher, Ján Kollár (1793–1852), who greatly influenced the literature of at least two nations with his poetic composition Slávy Dcera. <s> His work is often cited as the basis and motive for contemporary patriots and national activists. <s> It has been translated into various Slavic, as well as non-Slavic languages.
simple: Mošovce is one of the biggest villages in the Turiec Region of Slovakia. <s> Mošovce has existed for 770 years. <s> King Andrew II wrote about the village for the first time in 1233. <s> At first, "Mošovce" had two parts: The first one, "Machyuch", was in the area of today’s "Starý Rad" Street. <s> The village took its today's name from the second part, "Terra Moys", which was in the place of the present day "Vidrmoch" Street. <s> Because of the name of the second part, which means "The Land of Mojš", we believe that all the village was the property of a certain Mr. "Mojš". <s> In the history the name of the village changed from "Mossovych", "Mosocz", "Mossowecz", "villa regia Mayos alio nomine Mossovych", "oppidioum Mayus sue Mosocz", "Mosocz olim Mayus" to the present-day "Mošovce". <s> The name of a separate very old part of "Mošovce", "Chornukov", chaged to the modern form of "Čerňakov". <s> Mošovce was at first a royal village, and in about 1350 changed into a privileged town, which belonged to the royal castle of Blatnica. <s> In 1527 the Révay family became its owners, and they took away the town privileges of "Mošovce" for almost 400 years. <s> In the past, Mošovce was an important craft center of the Turiec region. <s> Crafts were very successful, and there were around 15 guilds in the town; the bootmaker and the most famous furrier guild existed for the longest time. <s> The present-day Mošovce is an important tourist area with many interesting places. <s> The nature around Mošovce is really beautiful. <s> This landscape looks nice with the forests of the Veľká Fatra Mountains. <s> This mountain range is one of the nicest ones in Slovakia. <s> People from all parts of the world come visit the beautiful Limestone and dolomite rocks, and the beautiful nature in the Blatnická and Gaderská Valleys, which are not far away. <s> One of the most interesting buildings is a small Rococo-Classical Palace with a big English park. <s> Other places in the town are: The birthplace of Ján Kollár, a Neo-gothic Catholic church with a valuable altar built on the place of an older church, a Lutheran church built in 1784, a Mausoleum, an Art-Nouveau greenhouse and a pavilion from 1800. <s> In the Mausoleum there is now a Museum of Crafts. <s> The greatest ones are Frico Kafenda (1883-1963), composer; Anna Lacková-Zora (1899-1988), writer; Štefan Krčméry (1892-1955), literary critic, historian, and poet; Júr Tesák Mošovský, Baroque playwright; and Miloslav Schmidt, the founder of the amateur fire brigades in Slovakia. <s> Probably the most important person born in Mošovce is the great Slavic poet, philosopher, and Lutheran priest, Ján Kollár (1793-1852), who was very active in the literature of at least two nations. <s> His work was very important for the patriots and national activists, who lived at the same time as Kollár. <s> People translated the book into many Slavic and non-Slavic languages.

title: Sumiteru Taniguchi
complex: Sumiteru Taniguchi (谷口 稜曄 , Taniguchi Sumiteru , 26 January 1929 – 30 August 2017) was a survivor of the 1945 atomic bombing of Nagasaki, a prominent activist for a treaty prohibiting nuclear weapons, and chairman of the Nagasaki Council of A-Bomb Sufferers. <s> Taniguchi died of duodenal papilla cancer in Nagasaki on 30 August 2017 at the age of 88.
simple: Sumiteru Taniguchi (谷口 稜曄, Taniguchi Sumiteru, January 26, 1929 – August 30, 2017) was a Japanese postman and anti-nuclear activist. <s> He was known for being a survivor of the 1945 atomic bombing of Nagasaki, Japan. <s> He was chairman of the Nagasaki Council of A-Bomb Sufferers. <s> Taniguchi died of lung and skin cancer on August 30, 2017 in Nagasaki at the age of 88.

title: Richea
complex: Richea is a genus of 11 species of flowering plants in the family Ericaceae. <s> Nine of the species are endemic to Tasmania and the other two are endemic to the south-east of the Australian mainland.
simple: Richea is a genus of shrubs or trees in the family Ericaceae.

title: Natalia Oreiro
complex: Natalia Marisa Oreiro Iglesias (] ; born 19 May 1977) is a Uruguayan singer, actress, and fashion designer. <s> Oreiro began her career in telenovelas. <s> Since 2008 she has switched to work primarily in films. <s> Oreiro has worked on social awareness shows and events for organizations like Greenpeace and UNICEF, the latter of which designated her as ambassador for Argentina and Uruguay in September 2011. <s> She has been included in "Esquire" magazine's "The Sexiest Woman Alive Atlas" list. <s> Natalia Oreiro, daughter of Carlos Florencio Oreiro Poggio and Mabel Cristina Iglesias Bourié, was born on 19 May 1977. <s> Natalia studied drama at the age of eight and at twelve started auditioning for advertisements. <s> During her teens she appeared in more than 30 television commercials for such trade marks as Coca-Cola, Pepsi and Johnson & Johnson. <s> At the age of 16 she moved to Argentina to work there and unleash her ambition to be a star. <s> She worked as an MTV VJ and in 1995, she landed a role in the soap opera "Dulce Ana". <s> She was then cast in the TV series "90-60-90 modelos" (1996) and next in "Ricos y famosos" (1997, playing Valeria). <s> Next, she starred in the Argentinian film "Un Argentino en New York" (1998). <s> After the movie, Natalia launched her first album, "Natalia Oreiro" and the single "Cambio Dolor" became the opening theme for her next acting project, the prime time show "Muñeca Brava" (1998–1999). <s> For her performance in "Muñeca Brava", Natalia was nominated twice (1998 and 1999) for a Martín Fierro Award as best actress in a leading role. <s> In 1998, Natalia Oreiro recorded the theme "Paths of the Soul" next to Kennedy Choir2 and with more than 120 Argentine artists under the direction of Instrumental pianist and conductor Nazareno Andorno. <s> She pursued her musical career with the next album "Tu Veneno" and presentations in Gala de la Hispanidad, Gala de Murcia (both in Spain) and Festival de la Calle 8 in Miami. <s> Her most important appearance was in the prestigious Latin television show "Sábado Gigante Internacional", hosted by Don Francisco. <s> Natalia's major achievement at this time was her music performance in Chile at Viña del Mar Festival 2000 for which she was crowned Queen of that event. <s> The album scored a Latin Grammy nomination for Best Pop Female Vocal Album, but lost to Christina Aguilera's "Mi Reflejo". <s> On 1 June 2002, her third studio album "Turmalina" was released by BMG Ariola Argentina. <s> "Turmalina" was produced by Latin record producer Kike Santander and is a combination of rhythms such as rock, pop and some sort of reminiscent of the 60's and 50's sounds. <s> On this album, Oreiro write and composed the songs: "Alas De Libertad" which is inspired by kids she met some time ago in the city of Jujuy, Argentina; "Mar" tells the love story between a sailor and his girlfriend. <s> Natalia also contributed to the lyrics of "Cayendo". <s> "Que Digan Lo Que Quieran" is "Turmalina" ' s first single. <s> Official Uruguayan 2002 World Cup song "Pasión Celeste" is recorded with Fredy Bessio. <s> "Cuesta arriba, cuesta abajo" was opening song of soap opera "Kachorra" ("Runaway Lady"). <s> "Kachorra" ended with a rating lower than 20 points in Argentina.
simple: Natalia Oreiro (born May 18, 1977 in Montevideo,Uruguay) is a Latin Grammy-nominated Uruguayan singer and actress. <s> Natalia Oreiro was born in Montevideo, Uruguay on May 19, 1977. <s> She is daughter of Carlos Oreiro Poggio and the painter Mabel Iglesias Bourié. <s> She studied drama when she was eight years old than she appeared in advertisements at twelve years old such as Coca-Cola, Pepsi and Johnson & Johnson. <s> At the age of 16 she moved to Argentina to work there. <s> She worked as an MTV VJ and in 1995, she landed a role in the soap opera "Dulce Ana". <s> After that she st in the TV series "90-60-90 modelos" (1996) and "Ricos y famosos" (1997). <s> In 1998, Natalia Oreiro starred in her first movie "Un Argentino en New York" with Guillermo Francella. <s> After the movie, she released three studio albums ("Natalia Oreiro, Tu Veneno, Turmalina") and she starred many TV series and movies. <s> Than she launched her first studio album "Natalia Oreiro" (1998). <s> "Cambio Dolor" was first single from her debut album and became the opening theme for the prime time show "Muñeca Brava" (1998-1999). <s> In 2000, her second studio album, "Tu Veneno" (Your Poison) was released and was presentation in "Gala de la Hispanidad", "Gala de Murcia" (both in Spain) and "Festival de la Calle 8" in Miami. <s> She was crowned Queen of that event at Viña del Mar Festival 2000 in Chile. <s> She was nominated for Latin Grammy Awards, but lost to Christina Aguilera's "Mi Reflejo". <s> "Turmalina" was produced by Latin maker Kike Santander. <s> "Que Digan Lo Que Quieran" (Should they say whatever they want) was first single from "Turmalina". <s> Natalia made contributions with singer/songwriter Jaime Roos and Falta y Resto for the official Uruguayan 2002 FIFA World Cup song "Pasión Celeste". <s> "Cuesta Arriba, Cuesta Abajo" became the opening theme for soap opera "Kahorra".

title: Michael Polakovs
complex: Michael Polakovs (23 February 1923 – 6 December 2009), born in Riga, Latvia, was a circus clown who performed in the US under the name of Coco the Clown, a moniker that his father, Nicolai Poliakoff, had made famous in Europe. <s> Michael was the eldest of Nicolai and his wife Valentina's two sons; they also had four daughters. <s> Nicolai was offered a contract to tour the UK with the Bertram Mills Circus in 1930, which allowed him to bring his wife and their two elder children, Michael and his sister Helen, to England. <s> The rest of the family joined them in 1934. <s> Michael joined his father in the circus ring, clowning and stiltwalking. <s> Many circuses were closed following the outbreak of the Second World War in 1939, and during the early part of the war Michael was employed by the Ascot Gas Board to dig holes in roads, for £2 16s 6d a week. <s> Nicolai and his family succeeded in finding employment with the Blackpool Tower Circus after it was decided that it would remain open during the war. <s> Michael and his sister Tamara appeared in each summer season until 1946, and toured during the winter months with stage circuses organised by impresario Tom Arnold. <s> Michael joined Billy Smart's Circus in 1951, and toured the US with the Mills Brothers Circus in 1953. <s> He returned to the US in the late 1950s, performing under his father's name of Coco the Clown with the Ringling Bros. and Barnum & Bailey Circus. <s> He was hired by the McDonald's fast-food chain in 1966 to revamp the character of Ronald McDonald, for whom he designed the outfit and make-up still in use today. <s> Michael also appeared in the first eight television commercials featuring the new character. <s> Michael retired to Catlettsburg, Kentucky with his second wife, Hazel, with whom he had one son and one daughter. <s> He also had four children from his first marriage, one of whom, Graham, also became a clown. <s> Died in 6 December 2009
simple: Michael Polakovs, known in America as Coco the Clown, (born Riga, Latvia 23 February 1923; died USA, 6 December 2009) was a famous clown. <s> His father was known as Coco the Clown in Britain. <s> Michael played the part of Coco the Clown in America. <s> Michael Polakovs was born in Riga. <s> Nikolai was known as Coco the Clown. <s> Michael was the eldest of six children. <s> In 1951 he went with a brother and a sister to work for Billy Smart’s circus. <s> There he became known as Coco the Clown. <s> He started the popularity of the character Ronald McDonald, advertising for the fast food chain. <s> He designed Ronald’s clothes and make-up and appeared in the first eight of his television commercials. <s> Later he settled with his second wife in Kentucky. <s> He had four children by his first wife and two children by his second wife. <s> He died aged 86 in 2009.

title: Neanderthal genome project
complex: The Neanderthal genome project is an effort of a group of scientists to sequence the Neanderthal genome, founded in July 2006. <s> It was initiated by 454 Life Sciences, a biotechnology company based in Branford, Connecticut in the United States and is coordinated by the Max Planck Institute for Evolutionary Anthropology in Germany. <s> In May 2010 the project published their initial draft of the Neanderthal genome based on the analysis of four billion base remain in modern humans outside Africa.
simple: The Neanderthal genome project is a project for the sequencing of the Neanderthal genome. <s> The project was announced by the Max Planck Institute for Evolutionary Anthropology in Germany and 454 Life Sciences in the United States in July 2006.

title: Japanese serow
complex: The Japanese serow (, lit. <s> "coarse pelt deer" ) : ("Capricornis crispus") is a Japanese goat-antelope, an even-toed ungulate mammal. <s> It is found in dense woodland in Japan, primarily in northern and central Honshu. <s> The animal is seen as a national symbol of Japan and is subject to protection in conservation areas. <s> Adult Japanese serow stand about 32 in tall and weigh 30 – . <s> They are black to whitish, and colouring lightens in summer. <s> The fur is very bushy, especially the tail. <s> Both sexes have short, backwards-curving horns and are difficult to distinguish by sight. <s> Japanese serow are found in dense mountain forests where they eat leaves, shoots, and acorns. <s> They are diurnal and feed in early mornings and late afternoons. <s> Serows are solitary, or gather in couples or small family groups. <s> The animal marks its territory with sweet-and-sour-smelling preorbital gland secretions, and males and females have separate territories that may overlap. <s> "Capricornis crispus" is socially monogamous. <s> Females reach sexual maturity at 30 months.
simple: The Japanese serow is a mammal that lives in Japan. <s> They live in dense woodland in Japan, primarily in northern and central Honshu and are found in dense mountain forests.They live in open grassland and forests at an elevation of about 1,000 metres (3,300 ft), and uses caves to rest in. <s> The animal is seen as a national symbol of Japan and protected in conservation areas. <s> Adult Japanese serow stand about 81 centimetres (32 in) tall and weigh 30–45 kilograms (66–99 lb). <s> They are black to whitish, and colouring lightens in summer. <s> They eat leaves, shoots, and acorns. <s> Capricornis crispus is socially monogamous.

title: Boysenberry
complex: The boysenberry is a cross among the European raspberry ("Rubus idaeus"), European blackberry ("Rubus fruticosus"), American dewberry ("Rubus aboriginum"), and loganberry ("Rubus" × "loganobaccus"). <s> It is a large 8.0 g aggregate fruit, with large seeds and a deep maroon color.
simple: A boysenberry is a cross between a European raspberry ("Rubus idaeus"), a common blackberry ("Rubus fruticosus"), an American dewberry ("Rubus aboriginum") and a loganberry ("Rubus" × "loganobaccus"). <s> It has large seeds and a maroon color.

title: Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.
complex: Wolverhampton Wanderers Football Club , commonly known as Wolves, is an English professional football club in Wolverhampton, West Midlands. <s> Formed as St Luke's F.C. in 1877, they have played at Molineux Stadium since 1889 and compete in the Premier League, the top division of English football, after winning the 2017–18 EFL Championship. <s> Wolves competes in the 2019–20 UEFA Europa League, the first time the club has qualified for a European tournament for thirty-nine years, by virtue of finishing in seventh-place in the 2018–19 Premier League in their first season back in the top tier. <s> Wolves have won the FA Cup four times, most recently in 1960, and finished runners-up on a further four occasions. <s> The club has also won the Football League Cup twice, in 1974 and 1980.
simple: Wolverhampton Wanderers are an English association football club. <s> They are based in Wolverhampton, West Midlands. <s> The club started in 1877 and play their home games at a stadium called Molineux Stadium. <s> They have won the FA Cup four times.

title: Tuvan People's Republic
complex: The Tuvan People's Republic (TPR); ; Uniform Turkic Alphabet: "Tьʙа Arat Respuʙlik" , ] , known as the Tannu Tuva People's Republic until 1926, was a partially recognized socialist republic that existed between 1921 and 1944. <s> The country was located in the same territory as the former Tuvan protectorate of Imperial Russia known as Uryankhay Krai.
simple: Tuvan People's Republic was a partially recognized state that existed from 1921 to 1944. <s> Until 1926, it was also known as People's Republic Tannu-Tuva.

title: Mario vs. Donkey Kong (video game)
complex: Mario vs. Donkey Kong is a 2004 puzzle-platform game developed by Nintendo Software Technology and released for the Game Boy Advance. <s> The game is the spiritual successor to "Donkey Kong", which was released in 1994 for the Game Boy. <s> The game's first sequel, "", was released on the Nintendo DS in 2006. <s> It was later released on the 3DS Virtual Console on December 16, 2011 and for the Wii U on February 9, 2017. <s> In "Mario vs. Donkey Kong", the player assumes the role of Mario, who is pursuing Donkey Kong through a toy factory in order to retrieve several stolen Mini-Mario toys. <s> The game, a puzzle platform game, plays similarly to the Game Boy "Donkey Kong" game, giving Mario a vast set of different athletic moves, including a handstand, a sideways somersault, and a triple jump, all of which can be used to maneuver platforming stages in various different ways. <s> There are several different environments, ranging from a lava environment to the classic construction site, and there are four different types; in the first, and most common, Mario has to pick up a key and take it to the locked door, and then find and pick up the Mini-Mario toy at the end of the level. <s> The second type is where Mario must guide six Mini-Mario toys to the Toy Box, while protecting them from dangerous environments. <s> The third type is the boss level, where Mario must fight Donkey Kong in order to proceed to the next world. <s> The fourth type is the Plus Level, where Mario must activate one Mini-Mario in the level, which is holding a key, and take it to the door. <s> The fifth type of level is the Expert levels. <s> The expert levels can be accessed after beating the main worlds.
simple: Mario vs. Donkey Kong is a 2004 puzzle-platform video game for the Game Boy Advance. <s> It was developed by Nintendo Software Technology and published by Nintendo. <s> It is a spiritual successor to "Donkey Kong", which was released for the Game Boy in 1994. <s> In the game, the player plays as Mario, who is chasing Donkey Kong through a toy factory after Donkey Kong stole many Mini-Mario toys. <s> It plays similarly to the Game Boy "Donkey Kong" game. <s> There are five types of levels. <s> In the first type, Mario has to pick up a key and take it to a locked door, then find and pick up the Mini-Mario toy at the end of the level. <s> In the second type, Mario has to guide six Mini-Mario toys to the Toy Box. <s> In the third type, Mario has to fight Donkey Kong in order to go to the next world. <s> In the fourth type, the Plus level, Mario has to turn on one Mini-Mario with a key and take it to the door. <s> The fifth type of level, the Expert level, plays like the first type of level, but is harder.

title: Delaware Route 52
complex: Delaware Route 52 (DE 52) is a state highway in New Castle County, Delaware. <s> The route runs from U.S. Route 13 Business (US 13 Bus.) <s> in downtown Wilmington north to Pennsylvania Route 52 (PA 52) at the Pennsylvania border near Centerville. <s> DE 52 runs through the city of Wilmington and passes through areas of the Brandywine Valley north of Wilmington.
simple: Delaware Route 52 is a state highway in Delaware. <s> It goes from Wilmington north to the Pennsylvania border.

title: Kedarnath Singh
complex: Kedarnath Singh (7 July 1934 – 19 March 2018) was an Indian poet who wrote in Hindi. <s> He was also an eminent critic and essayist. <s> He was awarded the Jnanpith Award (2013), Sahitya Akademi Award (1989) in Hindi for his poetry collection, "Akaal Mein Saras" ("Cranes in Drought").
simple: Kedarnath Singh (7 July 1934 – 19 March 2018) was an Indian poet. <s> He was one of the most known modern poets writing in Hindi. <s> He was also a critic and essayist. <s> He was awarded the Jnanpith Award (2013), Sahitya Akademi Award (1989) in Hindi for his poetry collection, "Akaal Mein Saras" ("Cranes in Drought").

title: The Statesman (India)
complex: The Statesman is an Indian English-language broadsheet daily newspaper founded in 1875 and published simultaneously in Kolkata, New Delhi, Siliguri and Bhubaneswar. <s> It incorporates and is directly descended from The Friend of India, founded in 1818.
simple: The Statesman is a English language newspaper published in India. <s> It is published simultaneously from Kolkata, New Delhi, Siliguri and Bhubaneshwar.

title: Lee Meriwether
complex: Lee Ann Meriwether (born May 27, 1935) is an American actress, former model, and the winner of the 1955 Miss America pageant. <s> She is known for her role as Betty Jones, Buddy Ebsen's secretary and daughter-in-law in the 1970s crime drama "Barnaby Jones". <s> The role earned her two Golden Globe Award nominations in 1975 and 1976, and an Emmy Award nomination in 1977.
simple: Lee Ann Meriwether (born May 27, 1935, Los Angeles) is an actress and former Miss America and has acted in many television series. <s> Before acting, she was crowned Miss America 1955. <s> She is best known for playing Catwoman in the 1966 movie version of "Batman", Betty Jones in the 1970s crime drama "Barnaby Jones" and Ruth Martin on the ABC soap opera "All My Children".

title: 70 Virginis b
complex: 70 Virginis b (abbreviated 70 Vir b) is an extrasolar planet approximately 60 light-years away in the constellation of Virgo. <s> Announced in 1996 by Geoffrey Marcy and R. Paul Butler, 70 Virginis was one of the first stars confirmed to have planets orbiting it. <s> When first announced, 70 Virginis b was considered to be within its star's habitable zone (preferably in the "Goldilocks zone"), but it was later confirmed that the planet has an eccentric orbit, closer to its parent. <s> 70 Virginis b is a gas giant extrasolar planet that is 7.5 times the mass of Jupiter and is in an eccentric 116-day orbit about its host. <s> Its surface gravity is expected to be about six to eight times that of Jupiter's. <s> At the time of discovery in January 1996, it was believed that the star was only 29 ly away resulting in the star being less luminous based on its apparent magnitude. <s> As a result, the planet's orbit was thought to be in the habitable zone and the planet was nicknamed Goldilocks (not too cold or too hot). <s> The Hipparcos satellite later showed that the star was more distant from Earth and therefore brighter resulting in the planet being too hot to be in the habitable zone.
simple: 70 Virginis b is an extrasolar planet that is around 60 light-years away from the Earth in the constellation of Virgo. <s> The finding of this planet was announced in 1996 by astronomers Geoffrey Marcy and R. Paul Butler. <s> 70 Virginis was one of the first stars that was known to have planets orbiting it. <s> When first announced, 70 Virginis b was thought to be inside its star's habitable zone, but proof was later found that the planet has an eccentric orbit, closer to its parent. <s> 70 Virginis b is a Jupiter-type extrasolar planet that orbits around 70 Virginis every 116 days. <s> It has 7.5 times the mass of Jupiter. <s> Its surface gravity is thought to be about two to three times that of Jupiter's. <s> At the time that it was found in January 1996, it was thought that the star was only 29 light years away from the Earth. <s> As a result, the planet's orbit was thought to be in the habitable zone and the planet was given the nickname "Goldilocks" (not too cold or too hot). <s> The Hipparcos satellite later showed that the star was farther away from 70 Virginis and therefore its brightness was a result of the planet being too hot to be in the habitable zone.

title: The Maccabees (band)
complex: The Maccabees were an English indie rock band, formed in 2004 in London. <s> They released four albums: "Colour It In" in 2007, followed by "Wall of Arms" in 2009, "Given to the Wild" which was released on 9 January 2012 and their last album "Marks to Prove It" released on 31 July 2015. <s> The band announced that they decided to disband in August 2016, with farewell gigs in 2017. <s> The band came up with the name by flicking through the Bible and picking out a random word. <s> Despite adopting a name with perceived religious connotations, lead singer Orlando Weeks has more recently affirmed, in an interview on Steve Lamacq's BBC 6 Music show, that none of the band is religious. <s> Notwithstanding, Maccabees are referred to in the Bible. <s> Their debut single, "X-Ray", was released on Promise records on 28 November 2005, and received some evening play on London radio station Xfm London. <s> They received little significant exposure, however, until six months later, when they released their second single, "Latchmere", the subject of which is the wave machine at the Latchmere Leisure Centre in Battersea, South London, on Fierce Panda Records in April 2006. <s> This was championed by Radio 1 DJ Steve Lamacq and received airtime on MTV2. <s> The video, directed by Hugh Frost and Samuel Bebbington, also proved an internet hit after it was posted on YouTube. <s> They had their first taste of festivals by playing on the Carling stage of the Leeds/Reading festival in 2006. <s> The band were signed to major label Fiction Records, and released their debut album "Colour It In" in May 2007. <s> Because an early copy of the album appeared on the "New York Times" website, "Colour It In" became available to download exclusively from iTunes on 16 December, before its physical release on 14 May, in an effort to combat the leak. <s> The single "First Love" was their first to chart in the UK top 40, and was followed by "About Your Dress", which peaked at No. 33. <s> Their album received positive reviews, and charted at No. 24. <s> They then toured the United States with fellow indie group Bloc Party. <s> A full UK tour followed from October 2007, culminating in a sell-out show at the Roundhouse venue in London.
simple: The Maccabees are a English indie band based in Brighton. <s> The band thought of the name 'The Maccabees' by opening the Bible to a random page. <s> Even though the name has religious meaning, lead singer Orlando Weeks said that none of the band are religious in an interview on Steve Lamacq's BBC Radio 1 show. <s> The Maccabees' debut single, 'X-Ray', was released on the Promise record label on 28 November 2005. <s> It was played a little in the evenings on London radio station Xfm London. <s> The band got very attentiong until six months later, when they released their second single, 'Latchmere'. <s> It was released on Fierce Panda Records in April 2006. <s> This song was talked about by Radio 1 DJ Steve Lamacqu and was played on MTV2. <s> The video, directed by Hugh Frost and Samuel Bebbington, also became a hit after it was put on YouTube. <s> The band are currently signed to Fiction Records, and released their debut album 'Colour It In' in May 2007. <s> Because the album had been leaked, or accidentally put, on the internet, 'Colour It In' became available to download exclusively from iTunes on 17 April before its release on 14 May. <s> The song First Love was the Maccabees' first to chart in the UK top 40. <s> It was followed by 'About Your Dress', which charted at #33. <s> Their next album was released to positive reviews, and charted at #24. <s> They toured the USA with fellow Indie group Bloc Party. <s> A UK tour happened in October 2007, ending in a show at the Roundhouse venue in London, where all the tickets were sold.

title: Changfeng County
complex: Changfeng County is a county of Anhui Province, East China, it is under the administration of the prefecture-level city of Hefei, the capital of Anhui. <s> It is the northernmost county-level division of Hefei, the provincial capital. <s> The county has a surface of 1922.24 km2 and a population of 629,535 inhabitants. <s> It contains 9 towns, 6 townships, and a development zone.
simple: Changfeng is a county in the province of Anhui in China. <s> The county has a surface of 1,922.24km2 and a population of 629,535 people. <s> It contains 9 towns, 6 townships, and a development zone.

title: Hocquinghen
complex: Hocquinghen is a commune in the Pas-de-Calais department in the Hauts-de-France region of France.
simple: Hocquinghen is a commune. <s> It is found in the region Nord-Pas-de-Calais in the Pas-de-Calais department in the north of France.

title: 2 Chainz
complex: Tauheed Epps (born September 12, 1977), known professionally as 2 Chainz (formerly Tity Boi), is an American rapper, songwriter and media personality. <s> Born and raised in College Park, Georgia, he initially gained recognition for being one-half of the Southern hip hop duo Playaz Circle, alongside his longtime friend and fellow rapper Earl "Dolla Boy" Conyers. <s> The duo was signed to fellow Georgia-based rapper Ludacris' Disturbing tha Peace label, and are best known for their debut single "Duffle Bag Boy". <s> In February 2012, Epps signed a solo record deal with Def Jam Recordings, an imprint of Universal Music Group.
simple: Tauheed Epps (born September 12, 1977), known professionally as 2 Chainz (formerly Tity Boi), is an American rapper. <s> He was born in College Park, Georgia. <s> He is also known for being half the duo of the rap group Playaz Circle along with rapper and long time friend Dolla Boy. <s> The group was discovered by fellow rapper Ludacris and signed them to his Record Label DTP.

title: David Gallagher
complex: David Lee Gallagher (born February 9, 1985) is an American actor. <s> Beginning a prolific career as a child actor and model at the age of two, Gallagher is a five-time Young Artist Award nominee and Teen Choice Award winner, best known for his role as Simon Camden on the long-running television series "7th Heaven", as well as for his feature film roles; as Mikey Ubriacco in "Look Who's Talking Now", as Kevin Harper in "Angels in the Endzone" and as Richie Rich in "Richie Rich's Christmas Wish". <s> Gallagher is also well known for the voice of Riku in the "Kingdom Hearts" video game series. <s> His first role after leaving "7th Heaven" was a guest stint on "Numb3rs", playing serial killer Buck Winters in September 2006, a role which he reprised in January 2009.
simple: David Lee Gallagher (born February 9, 1985) is an American actor. <s> He began his career as a and when he was two years old and is best known for his role as Simon Camden on the television series "7th Heaven". <s> He is also known for his feature film roles; as Mikey Ubriacco in "", as Kevin Harper in "" and as in "". <s> During his career as a child and teen star, he was nominated for five Young Artist Awards and won a Teen Choice Award. <s> He is also known for voicing the character Riku in the "Kingdom Hearts" video game series.

title: Koichi Hashiratani
complex: Koichi Hashiratani (柱谷 幸一 , Hashiratani Koichi , born March 1, 1961) is a former Japanese football player and manager. <s> He played for Japan national team. <s> His younger brother Tetsuji Hashiratani is also a former footballer.
simple: Koichi Hashiratani (柱谷 幸一, Hashiratani Koichi, born March 1, 1961) is a former Japanese football player. <s> He has played for the Japanese national team.

title: Kamran Mirza
complex: Kamran Mirza (1509 – 5 (or 6) October 1557) was the second son of Babur, the founder of the Mughal Empire and the first Mughal Emperor. <s> Kamran Mirza was born in Kabul to Babur's wife Gulrukh Begum. <s> He was half-brother to Babur's eldest son Humayun, who would go on and inherit the Mughal throne, but he was full-brother to Babur's third son, Askari.
simple: Kamran Mirza, sometimes known simply as Kamran, (1509 – 5 (or 6) October 1557) was the second son of Babur, the founder of the Mughal Empire and the first Mughal Emperor. <s> Kamran Mirza was born in Kabul to Babur's wife Gulrukh Begum.

title: Yoshinori Shigematsu
complex: Yoshinori Shigematsu (重松 良典 , Shigematsu Yoshinori , born April 2, 1930) is a former Japanese football player. <s> He played for Japan national team.
simple: Yoshinori Shigematsu (重松 良典, Shigematsu Yoshinori, born April 2, 1930) is a former Japanese football player. <s> He has played for the Japanese national team.

title: S/2004 S 6
complex: S/2004 S 6 is the provisional designation of a dusty object seen orbiting Saturn very close to the F ring. <s> It is not clear whether it is only a transient clump of dust, or if there is a solid moonlet at its core. <s> It was first seen by scientists in images taken by the Cassini-Huygens probe on October 28, 2004 and announced on November 8 that year. <s> It appears to be the best tracked object in this region with at least five probable sightings in the period to late 2005. <s> In comparison, two objects in the F ring's vicinity (S/2004 S 3 and S/2004 S 4 ) that were first seen several months earlier have not been recovered with any confidence. <s> Nevertheless, it continues to be unclear whether there is a solid core to S/2004 S 6 or whether it is just a transient dust clump that will dissipate on a timescale of years or months. <s> Notably, an imaging sequence covering an entire orbital period at 4 km resolution taken on November 15, 2004 (soon after S/2004 S 6 's discovery) failed to recover the object, while it has been seen again later. <s> The lighting conditions in S/2004 S 6 's part of the orbit were different during these two observations, however, with the discovery being made when the region was strongly backlit by the sun. <s> A suggested resolution of the absence in November is that S/2004 S 6 's visibility is primarily due to a diffuse cloud of fine dust that is much brighter in forward scattered light (the conditions of the discovery image), and that the solid core (if any) is small. <s> S/2004 S 6 has been seen both inside and outside the main F ring, and its orbit must cross the ring. <s> Careful calculations show that the object periodically plows through the ring material, coming within 1.5 km of the densest core e.g. on 9 April 2005. <s> It has been suggested that a spiral structure in the tenuous material surrounding the F ring may have been a consequence of this. <s> The dusty halo seen in images is sizeable, being around 2000 km in lengthwise extent. <s> The solid object, if any, would be no greater than 3–5 km in diameter based on brightness.
