title: Banner County, Nebraska
complex: Banner County is a county in the western part of the state of Nebraska in the Great Plains region of the United States. <s> As of the 2010 United States Census, its population was 690. <s> Its county seat is the unincorporated community of Harrisburg; there are no incorporated municipalities within the county. <s> When Nebraska became a state in 1867, a single county encompassed the entire Panhandle. <s> In 1870, the Panhandle's southern half was organized as Cheyenne County. <s> The arrival of increasing numbers of settlers led to the partitioning of the county in 1888: the eastern third became Deuel County; the middle third became present-day Cheyenne County; and the western third became Kimball, Scotts Bluff, and Banner Counties. <s> The last of these was named by citizens who declared it would become the state's "banner county", and "the brightest star in the constellation of Nebraska counties".

title: Ring galaxy
complex: A ring galaxy is a galaxy with a circle-like appearance. <s> Hoag's Object, discovered by Art Hoag in 1950, is an example of a ring galaxy. <s> The ring contains many massive, relatively young blue stars, which are extremely bright. <s> The central region contains relatively little luminous matter. <s> Some astronomers believe that ring galaxies are formed when a smaller galaxy passes through the center of a larger galaxy. <s> Because most of a galaxy consists of empty space, this "collision" rarely results in any actual collisions between stars. <s> However, the gravitational disruptions caused by such an event could cause a wave of star formation to move through the larger galaxy. <s> Other astronomers think that rings are formed around some galaxies when external accretion takes place. <s> Star formation would then take place in the accreted material because of the shocks and compressions of the accreted material.
simple: A ring galaxy is a kind of galaxy that has a ring shape. <s> The ring is made up of many massive, young blue stars, which are extremely bright. <s> The middle of the galaxy contains far less luminous matter. <s> Some astronomers believe that ring galaxies are formed when a smaller galaxy passes through the center of a larger galaxy. <s> Because galaxies are mostly made up of empty space, a collision rarely happens between stars. <s> However, the gravitational disruptions could cause a wave of star formation to move through the larger galaxy. <s> Other astronomers think that rings are formed around some galaxies when an accretion disc is formed. <s> Star formation would then result from the shocks and compressions in the newly formed disc.

title: French Stewart
complex: Milton French-Stewart (born February 20, 1964), known professionally as French Stewart, is an American actor and dancer, known for his role as Harry Solomon on the 1990s sitcom "3rd Rock from the Sun" and for his role as Chef Rudy on the sitcom "Mom".
simple: Milton French-Stewart (born February 20, 1964), known professionally as French Stewart, is an American actor and comedian. <s> He is best known for his role as Harry Solomon on the 1990s sitcom "3rd Rock from the Sun" and for his role as Chef Rudy on the sitcom "Mom".

title: Floydada, Texas
complex: Floydada is a city in and the county seat of Floyd County, Texas, United States. <s> This rural community lies on the high plains of the Llano Estacado in West Texas and is sometimes referred to as the Pumpkin Capital of Texas.
simple: Floydada is a city in the U.S. state of Texas. <s> It is the county seat of Floyd County.

title: Lixy
complex: Lixy is a commune in the Yonne department in Bourgogne-Franche-Comté in north-central France.
simple: Lixy is a commune. <s> It is found in the Yonne department in the center of France.

title: Trochophore
complex: A trochophore ( ; also spelled trocophore) is a type of free-swimming planktonic marine larva with several bands of cilia. <s> By moving their cilia rapidly, a water eddy is created. <s> In this way they control the direction of their movement. <s> Additionally, in this way they bring their food closer, in order to capture it more easily.
simple: A trochophore is a type of larva found in marine plankton. <s> By moving their cilia rapidly, a water eddy is created. <s> In this way they control the direction of their movement. <s> Also, in this way they bring their food closer, to capture it more easily.

title: Phil LaMarr
complex: Phillip "Phil" LaMarr (born January 24, 1967) is an American actor, voice actor, comedian and impressionist. <s> He was a featured cast member on the sketch comedy series "Mad TV" and has had an extensive voice acting career, with roles in animated series including "Justice League", "Justice League Unlimited", "Futurama", "Samurai Jack", "Static Shock" and "Foster's Home for Imaginary Friends". <s> He has also provided voice-work for video games, such as "Metal Gear", "Jak and Daxter", "Darksiders", "Final Fantasy", "Infamous", "Dead Island", "Kingdom Hearts" and "Mortal Kombat".
simple: Phillip "Phil" LaMarr (born January 24, 1967) is an American actor, voice actor, comedian and impressionist. <s> He was best known as one of the original cast members on the sketch comedy series "MADtv", and is known for his voice roles in various animated series such as "Justice League", "Justice League Unlimited", "Futurama", "Samurai Jack", "Static Shock", and "Foster's Home for Imaginary Friends".

title: Koror City
complex: Koror City is the largest city in Palau, home to about half of the country's population. <s> It was formerly the capital until it was replaced by Ngerulmud in 2006.
simple: Koror is the capital city of Palau.

title: Vishal Bhardwaj
complex: Vishal Bhardwaj (born 4 August 1965) is an Indian film director, screenwriter, producer, music composer and playback singer. <s> He is known for his work in Hindi cinema, and is the recipient of seven National Film Awards in four categories.
simple: Vishal Bhardwaj (born 4 August 1965) is an n Hindi movie director.

title: Charles Arthur Bowsher
complex: Charles Arthur Bowsher (born May 31, 1931) is an American businessman and politician. <s> He served as the 6th Comptroller General of the United States from 1981 to 1996. <s> During that period, he led the Government Accountability Office in addressing the savings and loan crisis and other major issues. <s> He also served as the 5th Assistant Secretary of the Navy (Financial Management and Comptroller) during the Lyndon B. Johnson administration from 1967 to 1971. <s> Bowsher was born in Elkhart, Indiana. <s> He was raised in Chicago where he would study at the University of Illinois at Urbana–Champaign. <s> He would enroll in the United States Army and serve for two years and would earn his M.B.A. degree at the University of Chicago. <s> After graduating from the University of Chicago, he joined the firm Arthur Andersen & Co. in 1956. <s> In the firm, he played a crucial role in the firm's efforts to encourage public discussion on the need for sound financial reporting within the public sector. <s> From 1967 to 1971, he was Assistant Secretary of the Navy (Financial Management and Comptroller). <s> Bowsher was nominated to serve as United States Comptroller General by President Ronald Reagan in 1981. <s> During his tenure, he was subject of the lawsuit "Bowsher v. Synar," which led to the U.S. Supreme Court striking down the Gramm-Rudman-Hollings Act of 1986. <s> He was known for his visible role during the savings and loan crisis when he addressed the Government Accountability Office. <s> In 1996, along with William Henry Beaver, (56th), and Donald James Kirk, (58th), Bowsher was inducted into the prestigious Accounting Hall of Fame, becoming the 57th inductee. <s> He currently serves as the Secretary-Treasurer/Budget Chairman for the Board of Directors of the Concord Coalition. <s> He also serves on the Board of Directors of the Committee for a Responsible Federal Budget.
simple: Charles Arthur Bowsher (born May 31, 1931) is an American politician and businessman. <s> He was the 6th Comptroller General of the United States from 1981 to 1996. <s> He was born in Elkhart, Indiana. <s> Raised in Chicago, Bowsher studied at the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign and at the University of Chicago. <s> In 1956, he worked as an accountant and as a key business figure for Arthur Andersen & Co.. <s> From 1967 to 1971, he was Assistant Secretary of the Navy (Financial Management and Comptroller) during the Lyndon B. Johnson presidency. <s> Bowsher was nominated by President Ronald Reagan in 1981 and was Comptroller General for 15 years from 1981 to 1996. <s> During that period, he led the Government Accountability Office during the savings and loan crisis and other major issues. <s> In 1996, Bowsher was added to the Accounting Hall of Fame. <s> After civil service, he is the Chairman for the Board of Directors of the Concord Coalition.

title: Hermival-les-Vaux
complex: Hermival-les-Vaux is a commune in the Calvados department in the Normandy region in northwestern France.
simple: Hermival-les-Vaux is a commune.

title: Guy Carleton, 1st Baron Dorchester
complex: Guy Carleton, 1st Baron Dorchester, KB (3 September 1724 – 10 November 1808), known between 1776 and 1786 as Sir Guy Carleton, was an Anglo-Irish soldier and administrator. <s> He twice served as Governor of the Province of Quebec, from 1768 to 1778, concurrently serving as Governor General of British North America in that time, and again from 1785 to 1795. <s> The title Baron Dorchester was created on 21 August 1786.
simple: Sir Guy Carleton, 1st Baron Dorchester (1724-1808) was a British soldier and Governor of Canada. <s> He was governor of Canada twice, 1768-1778 and 1785-1795.

title: Chakwal
complex: Chakwal (Punjabi and ) is the capital and main city of Chakwal District, Punjab, Pakistan. <s> It is located 90 kilometres south-east of the federal capital, Islamabad and 270 kilometres from the provincial capital, Lahore.
simple: Chakwal is a city in Pakistan. <s> It is in the Punjab province and is the capital of Chakwal District.

title: IRCd
complex: An IRCd, short for Internet Relay Chat daemon, is server software that implements the IRC protocol, enabling people to talk to each other via the Internet (exchanging textual messages in real time). <s> It is distinct from an IRC bot that connects outbound to an IRC channel. <s> The server listens to connections from IRC clients on a set of TCP ports. <s> When the server is part of an IRC network, it also keeps one or more established connections to other servers/daemons. <s> The term "ircd" originally referred to only one single piece of software, but it eventually became a generic reference to any implementation of an IRC daemon. <s> However, the original version is still distributed under the same name, and this article discusses both uses.
simple: An IRCd, meaning Internet Relay Chat server program, is a program, server software that uses the IRC protocol. <s> They exchange textual messages in real time. <s> The server accepts connections from IRC clients on a group of TCP ports. <s> When the server is part of an IRC network, it also keeps one or more connections with other servers/daemons. <s> The word "ircd" once referred to only one piece of software.

title: San Antonio Province
complex: San Antonio Province is one of eight provinces of the central Chilean region of Valparaíso (V). <s> Its capital is the port city of San Antonio (pop. <s> As a province, San Antonio is a second-level administrative division, governed by a provincial governor who is appointed by the president. <s> The province spans a coastal area of 1511.6 sqkm , . <s> According to the 2002 census, San Antonio Province had a population of 136,594, making it the fourth most populous province in the region. <s> At that time, the population was 267,022 inhabitant with 125,637 people living in urban areas, 10,957 people living in rural areas, 67,771 men and 68,823 women. <s> San Antonio Valley is a small wine region known for producing Pinot Noir, Sauvignon Blanc and Chardonnay. <s> It is located very close to the sea around the city of San Antonio, Chile, south of the Casablanca Valley and only 55 miles (90 km) west of Santiago. <s> As in other Chilean wine regions, like the Casablanca Valley, San Antonio is highly influenced by the cooling effect of the Pacific Ocean which makes wine production possible in this area.
simple: San Antonio Province is one of eight provinces of the central Chilean region of Valparaíso (V). <s> The port city of San Antonio is the capital of the province. <s> As a province, San Antonio is a second-level administrative division, consisting of six communes ("comunas"). <s> The province is administered by a governor. <s> The San Antonio province has an area of 1511.6 km2, the third smallest province in the Valparaíso region; only the Quillota and Marga Marga provinces are smaller. <s> s of 2002 (last national census), there were 136,594 people living in the province, giving it a population density of 90.36385287112994 /km2 inhabitants/km2. <s> The San Antonio valley is a small region where wine is produced. <s> It is very close to the sea around the city of San Antonio, at only 90 km west of Santiago.

title: Sandra Izbașa
complex: Sandra Raluca Izbașa (] ; born 18 June 1990) is a retired artistic gymnast from Romania. <s> She is a double Olympic champion, having won the floor event at the 2008 Olympics and vault at the 2012 Olympics. <s> She is also a winner of two Olympic bronze medals (as part of the Romanian team in 2008 and 2012) and multiple World Championship and European Championship medals.
simple: Sandra Raluca Izbaşa (]) (born June 18, 1990) is a Romanian gymnast. <s> She has won two Olympic gold medals, at the floor event at the 2008 Olympics and at the vault event at the 2012 Olympics.

title: South African Defence Force
complex: The South African Defence Force (SADF) comprised the South African armed forces from 1957 until 1994. <s> Shortly before the state reconstituted itself as a republic in 1961, the former Union Defence Force was officially succeeded by the SADF, which was established by the Defence Act (No. 44) of 1957. <s> The SADF, in turn, was superseded by the South African National Defence Force in 1994. <s> The military was mostly composed of white South Africans, who alone were subject to conscription. <s> However, Asians and Coloured citizens with mixed ancestry were eligible to serve as volunteers, several even attaining commissioned rank. <s> From 1971 onwards several Black battalions were raised in the Infantry and Service Corps on a tribal basis, and most Black soldiers served in these exclusive tribal Battalions, which had Black NCOs but White commissioned officers. <s> The first Black personnel were accepted into commissioned ranks only from 1986, and then only for serving Black soldiers and NCOs. <s> The regular Commission would not be open for Bantus until 1991, and then again they would serve only in Black units or Support/Service Support units, to avoid having position of authority over White combat arms personnel. <s> The first Black officer to be promoted to Lieutenant Colonel rank and have command over a Battalion sized unit was only appointed in February 1994, by which time the old SADF was already on its deathbed. <s> However, Black officer candidates from the various Homeland Forces and from South West Africa/SWATF had been accepted since 1981 Units such as the 32 Battalion incorporated many black volunteers, as did the 101 Battalion. <s> Conscription was opposed by organisations such as the End Conscription Campaign, but overall, white morale remained high—as indicated by the few recruits tried for serious disciplinary offences. <s> During apartheid, armed SADF troops were used in quelling opposition to minority rule, often directly supporting the South African Police. <s> South African military units were involved in the long-running Mozambican and Angolan civil wars, frequently supporting Pretoria's allies, the Mozambican National Resistance (RENAMO) and the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA). <s> SADF personnel were also deployed during the related South African Border War. <s> As non-racial democracy was introduced to the republic in 1994, the SADF was amalgamated with the formerly independent Bantustan security forces, the ANC's Umkhonto we Sizwe, PAC's Azanian People's Liberation Army and the 'self-protection units' of the Inkatha Freedom Party (IFP) to form the South African National Defence Force. <s> South Africa at one time possessed nuclear weapons, but its stockpile was dismantled during the political transition of the early 1990s.
simple: The South African Defence Force (SADF) was the name of the South African military from 1957 to 1994. <s> It replaced the Union Defence Force (UDF) in 1957. <s> The SADF, in turn, was replaced by the South African National Defence Force (SANDF) in 1994. <s> The SADF implemented conscription of white South Africans. <s> Within South Africa, the SADF was used to suppress opposition to apartheid, often directly supporting the South African Police. <s> South African military units were also involved in the Angolan Civil War an the side of the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) and Angolan rebel leader Jonas Savimbi. <s> The SADF was also deployed during the related South African border and Namibian independence wars. <s> With the a multiracial democracy introduced to South Africa in 1994, the SADF was merged with the defence forces of several formerly "independent" homelands, as well as the ANC's Umkhonto we Sizwe (Spear of the Nation), the PAC's Azanian People's Liberation Army (APLA), and the self-protection units of the Inkatha Freedom Party (IPA). <s> South Africa was the only country in Africa to have nuclear weapons, but these weapons were destroyed by the South African government during the transition to democracy. <s> South Africa has not built nuclear weapons since.

title: Jan Matsys
complex: Jan Massijs or Jan Matsys (c.1510 – 8 October 1575) was a Flemish Renaissance painter known for his history paintings, genre scenes and landscapes. <s> He also gained a reputation as a painter of the female nude, which he painted with a sensuality reminiscent of the school of Fontainebleau.
simple: Jan Massys (born around 1510 in Antwerp, died 8 October 1575, also in Antwerp) was a Flemish painter.

title: Hispanic
complex: The term Hispanic ( or ) refers to the people that originate from, or reside in, a former Spanish Empire viceroyalty. <s> "Hispanus" was the Latin name given to a person from Hispania during Roman rule. <s> The ancient Roman Hispania, which roughly comprised what is currently called the Iberian Peninsula, included the contemporary states of Spain, Portugal, and Andorra, and the British Overseas Territory of Gibraltar. <s> In English, the term "Hispano-Roman" is sometimes used.
simple: Hispanic has also been used to mean the culture and people of the former Spanish and Portuguese Empires in America. <s> This is the Iberian Peninsula and includes Portugal, Andorra, Gibraltar and Spain.

title: Sigfrid Mattsson
complex: Sigfrid Mattsson, born 19 September 1917, dead 27 August 2009, was a Swedish cross-country skier. <s> Representing Skarpnäcks IF in club competitions, he won Vasaloppet in 1952.
simple: Sigfrid Mattsson, born 19 September 1917, dead 27 August 2009, was a Swedish cross-country skier. <s> He competed for Skarpnäcks IF in club competitions. <s> In 1952, he won the Vasaloppet event.

title: Chapter V: Unbent, Unbowed, Unbroken
complex: Chapter V: Unbent, Unbowed, Unbroken is the fifth studio album by the Swedish metal band HammerFall and was released in 2005 through Nuclear Blast. <s> It features the track "Knights of the 21st Century"; the band's longest studio recording to date at 12 minutes and 20 seconds.
simple: Chapter V: Unbent, Unbowed, Unbroken is an album by Swedish power metal band HammerFall.

title: Peter Cartwright (lawyer)
complex: Peter John Cartwright (3 May 1940 – 17 April 2019) was a New Zealand lawyer and, as the husband of Dame Silvia Cartwright, viceregal consort of New Zealand between 2001 and 2006. <s> Born in Dunedin on 3 May 1940, Cartwright was the son of James Patrick Cartwright and Gladys Josephine Cartwright (née Laffey). <s> He was educated as a boarder at St Bede's College in Christchurch, and then studied law at the University of Otago from 1960 to 1965, graduating LLB. <s> He went on to become a partner in a law firm in Hamilton as a commercial lawyer. <s> He served on the boards of IHC New Zealand and the Donald Beasley Institute, and was chair of the latter for several years. <s> He also chaired the Medical Practitioners Disciplinary Tribunal, the Indecent Publications Tribunal and the Broadcasting Standards Authority, was a member of the Accident Compensation Appeal Authority, and patron of Citizen Advocacy Auckland. <s> In 1969, Cartwright married Silvia Rose Poulter who, as Silvia Cartwright, became the first female High Court judge in New Zealand, and who was appointed as the 18th Governor-General of New Zealand in 2001, serving until 2006. <s> Peter Cartwright died in Auckland on 17 April 2019.
simple: Peter John Cartwright CNZM QSO CStJ (3 May 1940 – 17 April 2019) was a New Zealand lawyer. <s> He was the husband of Dame Silvia Cartwright ("née" Poulter). <s> He was the viceregal consort of New Zealand between 2001 and 2006, when his wife was serving as the 18th Governor-General of New Zealand. <s> He was born in Dunedin. <s> He was the chairman of the Medical Practitioners Disciplinary Tribunal, the Indecent Publications Tribunal and the Broadcasting Standards Authority. <s> Cartwright died in Auckland on 17 April 2019.

title: Charles Wesley Turnbull
complex: Charles Wesley Turnbull (born February 5, 1935), was the sixth elected Governor of the U.S. Virgin Islands. <s> During his tenure as governor, Turnbull served as a member of the National Governors Association, the Southern Governors' Association, and the Democratic Governors Association.
simple: Charles Wesley Turnbull (born February 5, 1935), was the 27th Governor of the U.S. Virgin Islands serving from 1999 through 2007. <s> During his tenure as governor, Turnbull served as a member of the National Governors Association, the Southern Governors' Association, and the Democratic Governors Association.

title: List of counties in South Dakota
complex: There are 66 counties in the U.S. state of South Dakota with FIPS codes. <s> Todd County and Oglala Lakota County are the only counties in South Dakota which do not have their own county seats. <s> Hot Springs in Fall River County serves as the administrative center for Oglala Lakota County. <s> Winner in Tripp County serves as the administrative center for Todd County. <s> These are two of five counties in South Dakota which are entirely within an Indian reservation. <s> (The other three counties are Corson, Dewey, and Ziebach.) <s> South Dakota's postal abbreviation is SD and its FIPS state code is 46.
simple: There are 66 counties in the U.S. state of South Dakota. <s> Todd County and Oglala Lakota County are two counties in South Dakota that do not have their own county seat. <s> Hot Springs in Fall River County is the administrative center of Oglala Lakota County. <s> Winner in Tripp County is the administrative center of Todd County. <s> South Dakota's postal abbreviation is SD and its FIPS state code is 46.

title: Star Trek: Enterprise
complex: Star Trek: Enterprise, titled simply Enterprise for its first two seasons, is an American science fiction television series created by Rick Berman and Brannon Braga. <s> It originally aired from September 26, 2001, to May 13, 2005, on UPN, spanning . <s> The sixth series in the "Star Trek" franchise, it served as a prequel to "". <s> The show is set in the 22nd century, a hundred years before the events of "The Original Series" and just prior to the formation of the United Federation of Planets. <s> The series follows the adventures of the "Enterprise", Earth's first starship capable of traveling at warp five, as it explores the galaxy and encounters various alien species. <s> "Star Trek: Enterprise" follows the adventures of the crew of the starship "Enterprise", designation NX-01.
simple: Enterprise (retitled Star Trek: Enterprise at the start of its third season) is a science fiction television program created by Brannon Braga and Rick Berman. <s> It aired from 2001 to 2005. <s> The series follows the adventures of humanity's first "Warp" 5 starship, the "Enterprise", ten years before the United Federation of Planets shown in previous "Star Trek" series.

title: Prince Regent DLR station
complex: Prince Regent DLR station is a station on the Docklands Light Railway (DLR) in Canning Town in east London. <s> The station was opened on 28 March 1994 and provides access to the eastern end of the ExCeL Exhibition Centre and ICC London. <s> The station signage is subtitled 'for ExCeL East'. <s> There is a small bus station adjoining the station with buses to Plaistow and London City Airport. <s> The station is located on the DLR's Beckton branch, between Custom House and Royal Albert stations. <s> It is in Travelcard Zone 3. <s> During major exhibitions at the adjacent Excel Centre an additional DLR shuttle service operates between Canning Town and Prince Regent stations, to supplement the normal Tower Gateway to Beckton service.
simple: Prince Regent DLR station is a station on the Docklands Light Railway (DLR) in the Docklands area of East London. <s> The station was opened on 28 March 1994. <s> It provides access to the eastern end of the ExCeL Exhibition Centre. <s> The station signage is subtitled 'for ExCeL East'. <s> There is a small bus station adjoining the station. <s> Buses from here go to Plaistow and London City Airport. <s> The station is on the DLR's Beckton branch, between Custom House and Royal Albert stations. <s> It is in Travelcard Zone 3.

title: Man and the Biosphere Programme
complex: Man and the Biosphere Programme (MAB) is an intergovernmental scientific programme, launched in 1971 by UNESCO, that aims to establish a scientific basis for the improvement of relationships between people and their environments. <s> Biosphere reserves are areas comprising terrestrial, marine and coastal ecosystems. <s> Each reserve promotes solutions reconciling the conservation of biodiversity with its sustainable use.
simple: The Man and the Biosphere Programme (MAB) is a division of UNESCO that tries to improve and encourage conservation and sustainability around the world. <s> It was created in 1971. <s> Biosphere reserves are areas that are supposed to develop creative ideas, test them and share the results.

title: Mahmud Shah Durrani
complex: Mahmud Shah Durrani (1769 – April 18, 1829; Pashto, Persian, Urdu, Arabic: ) was born Prince and the ruler of the Durrani Empire (Afghanistan) between 1801 and 1803, and again between 1809 and 1818. <s> An ethnic Sadduzai tribe section of the Popalzai sub clan of Durrani Abdali Pashtun, he was the son of Timur Shah Durrani and grandson of Ahmad Shah Durrani. <s> Mahmud Shah Durrani was the half-brother of his predecessor, Zaman Shah. <s> On July 25, 1801, Zaman Shah was deposed, and Mahmud Shah ascended to ruler-ship. <s> He then had a chequered career; he was deposed in 1803, restored in 1809, and finally deposed again in 1818. <s> The elder brother of Dost Mohammad Khan, the chief of the Barakzai, Fateh Khan, took an important part in raising Mahmud Shah Durrani to the sovereignty of Afghanistan in 1800 and in restoring him to the throne in 1809. <s> The son of Mahmud Shah Durrani Shahzada Kamran Durrani was always in trouble with Amir Fateh Khan Barakzai, the brother of Dost Muhammad Khan. <s> Mahmud Shah repaid Fateh Khan's services by having him assassinated in 1818. <s> After the assassination of Fateh Khan Barakzai the fall of the Durrani Empires begun, thus incurring the enmity of his tribe. <s> After a bloody conflict, Mahmud Shah was deprived of all his possessions but Herat, the rest of his dominions being divided among Fatteh Khan's brothers. <s> King Mahmud Shah Durrani died in 1829. <s> The country was then ruled by Shuja Shah Durrani; another of his half-brothers.
simple: Mahmud Shah Durrani (1769 - 1829) was the ruler of the Durrani Empire between 1801 and 1803, again between 1809 and 1818. <s> He was the son of Timur Shah Durrani and half-brother of his predecessor, Zaman Shah. <s> On July 25, 1801, Zaman Shah was deposed, and Mahmud Shah ascended to rulership. <s> He then had a chequered career; he was deposed in 1803, restored in 1809, and finally deposed again in 1818. <s> He died in 1829. <s> Between his two stints, the country was ruled by Shoja Shah, another of his half-brothers.

title: Robert Jordan
complex: James Oliver Rigney Jr. (October 17, 1948 – September 16, 2007), better known by his pen name Robert Jordan, was an American author of epic fantasy. <s> He is best known for the "Wheel of Time" series, which comprises 14 books and a prequel novel.
simple: Robert Jordan (October 17, 1948 – September 16, 2007) was the pen or writing name of the American fantasy author James Oliver Rigney Jr.

title: R Apodis
complex: R Apodis (R Aps) is a star in the constellation Apus.
simple: R Apodis is a red giant star located in the constellation Apus.

title: Larry Craig
complex: Larry Edwin Craig (born July 20, 1945) is a retired American politician from the state of Idaho. <s> He served 18 years as a Republican in the United States Senate (1991–2009), preceded by 10 years in the U.S. House of Representatives, representing Idaho's 1st District (1981–91). <s> His 28 years in Congress rank as the second-longest in Idaho history, trailing only William Borah, who served over 32 years in the Senate.
simple: Larry Edwin Craig (born July 20, 1945) is an American politician. <s> He is a former Republican politician from the U.S. state of Idaho. <s> He served 18 years in the U.S. Senate (1991–2009), preceded by 10 years in the U.S. House, representing Idaho's first district (1981–91).

title: Närpes
complex: Närpes is a town and municipality of Finland.
simple: Närpes is a town in western Finland.

title: Mandeville-en-Bessin
complex: Mandeville-en-Bessin is a commune in the Calvados department in the Normandy region in northwestern France.
simple: Mandeville-en-Bessin is a commune. <s> It is found in the region Basse-Normandie in the Calvados department in the northwest of France.

title: John McLaughlin (host)
complex: John Joseph McLaughlin ( ; March 29, 1927 – August 16, 2016) was an American television personality and political commentator. <s> He created, produced, and hosted the political commentary series "The McLaughlin Group." <s> He also hosted and produced "John McLaughlin's One on One" which ran from 1984 to 2013. <s> McLaughlin was originally a supporter of the Democratic Party and opposed the Vietnam War, but then became a war supporter and changed his party affiliation to Republican. <s> In 1970 he sought permission from the Jesuit order to run for a seat in the United States Senate, representing Rhode Island. <s> They had given permission to fellow Jesuit Father Robert Drinan who ran successfully for the United States House of Representatives in Massachusetts.
simple: John McLaughlin (March 29, 1927 – August 16, 2016) was an American television personality and producer, politician, writer, and political commentator. <s> He created and hosts the long-running political commentary series "The McLaughlin Group" as well as "John McLaughlin's One On One". <s> He also ran for senator of Rhode Island in 1970, but lost the election to incumbent John O. Pastore.

title: Hélio Bicudo
complex: Hélio Pereira Bicudo (5 July 1922 – 31 July 2018) was a Brazilian jurist and politician. <s> In 1986, Bicudo was candidate to the Senate by the PT, placing 3rd, after the elected Mário Covas and Fernando Henrique Cardoso, both from the PMDB. <s> Hélio was Vice Mayor of São Paulo from 2001 to 2004, during the administration of Marta Suplicy. <s> In 2015, he filed in the Chamber of Deputies an impeachment request against president Dilma Rousseff. <s> Jurist Miguel Reale Júnior and pro-impeachment social movements decided to support Bicudo's request, which got the support of parliamentaries in the Congress and the majority of the civil society, whom organized a petition requesting the impeachment of the President of the Republic, while other parliamentaries and member of the Workers' Party positioned themselves in the defence of the defendant President. <s> Bicudo's request was, in the same year, accepted by the then President of the Chamber of Deputies Eduardo Cunha, after many meetings to instruct the claimants. <s> In 31 August 2016, the impeachment request was approved by the Federal Senate in a voting 61-20, removing Rousseff from the Presidency and officializing Michel Temer as President of Brazil. <s> Bicudo died on 31 July 2018.
simple: Hélio Pereira Bicudo (5 July 1922 – 31 July 2018) was a Brazilian jurist and politician. <s> In 1986, Bicudo was candidate to the Senate by the PT, placing 3rd, after the elected Mário Covas and Fernando Henrique Cardoso, both from the PMDB. <s> Hélio was Vice Mayor of São Paulo from 2001 to 2004, during the administration of Marta Suplicy. <s> In 2015, he filed in the Chamber of Deputies an impeachment request against president Dilma Rousseff. <s> Bicudo died on 31 July 2018 in São Paulo from a stroke, aged 96.

title: Safe from Harm (song)
complex: "Safe from Harm" is the third single and opening track from "Blue Lines", the 1991 debut from Massive Attack, with vocals by Shara Nelson and Robert Del Naja. <s> The bass, guitar, and drums are sampled from the song "Stratus" by Billy Cobham, from his album "Spectrum" (with guitar by Tommy Bolin).
simple: "Safe from Harm" is a song by trip-hop band Massive Attack.

title: Takeoff
complex: Takeoff is the phase of flight in which an aerospace vehicle goes from the ground to flying in the air. <s> For aircraft that take off horizontally, this usually involves starting with a transition from moving along the ground on a runway. <s> For balloons, helicopters and some specialized fixed-wing aircraft (VTOL aircraft such as the Harrier), no runway is needed. <s> Takeoff is the opposite of landing.
simple: Takeoff is the part of flight in which an aircraft goes from moving along the ground (taxiing) to flying in the air, usually on a runway. <s> For balloons, helicopters and some special aircraft (such as the Harrier), no runway is needed. <s> Takeoff is the opposite of landing.

title: Pictorella mannikin
complex: The pictorella mannikin or pictorella munia ("Heteromunia pectoralis") is a species of bird in the family Estrildidae. <s> It belongs to the monotypic genus Heteromunia.
simple: The Pictorella Munia (Heteromunia pectoralis) is a species of bird in the family Estrildidae.

title: Ben Grubbs
complex: Benjamin Richard Grubbs (born March 10, 1984) is a former American football guard . <s> He played college football at Auburn University, and was drafted by the Baltimore Ravens in the first round of the 2007 NFL Draft. <s> He has also played for the New Orleans Saints and Kansas City Chiefs.
simple: Benjamin Richard Grubbs (born March 10, 1984 in Eclectic, Alabama) is an American football offensive guard who currently plays for the Baltimore Ravens of the National Football League (NFL). <s> Grubbs was drafted out of Auburn University by the Baltimore Ravens with the 29th pick in the first round of the 2007 NFL Draft.

title: Pelecanimimus
complex: Pelecanimimus (meaning "pelican mimic") is a genus of basal ("primitive") ornithomimosaurian theropod dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous of Spain. <s> It is notable for possessing more teeth than any other member of the Ornithomimosauria (or any other theropod), most of which were toothless.
simple: Pelecanimimus (meaning "pelican mimic") is a primitive theropod dinosaur from Spain. <s> It is notable for possessing more teeth than any other member of the Ornithomimosauria (or any other theropod), most of which were toothless.

title: Hjalmar Schacht
complex: Hjalmar Horace Greeley Schacht (22 January 1877 – 3 June 1970) was a German economist, banker, centre-right politician, and co-founder in 1918 of the German Democratic Party. <s> He served as the Currency Commissioner and President of the Reichsbank under the Weimar Republic. <s> He was a fierce critic of his country's post-World War I reparation obligations.
simple: Hjalmar Horace Greeley Schacht (22 January 1877 in Tingleff – 3 June 1970 in München) was a German politician and minister for economics during the time of the Third Reich. <s> In the Weimar Republic he was the president of the Reichsbank.

title: Gnat
complex: A gnat is any of many species of tiny flying insects in the dipterid suborder Nematocera, especially those in the families Mycetophilidae, Anisopodidae and Sciaridae. <s> They can be both biting and non-biting. <s> Most often they fly in large numbers, called clouds. <s> "Gnat" is a loose descriptive category rather than a phylogenetic or other technical term, so there is no scientific consensus on what constitutes a gnat. <s> Some entomologists consider only non-biting flies to be gnats. <s> Certain universities also distinguish eye gnats: the Smithsonian Institution describes them as "non-biting flies, no bigger than a few grains of salt, ... attracted to fluids secreted by your eyes".
simple: A gnat is any tiny fly in the suborder Nematocera. <s> They can be both biting and non-biting. <s> Often they fly in large numbers, called clouds, in damp places like the Scottish Highlands. <s> "Gnat" is a loose descriptive category rather than a technical term. <s> the Smithsonian Institution describes them as “non-biting flies, no bigger than a few grains of salt, ... attracted to fluids secreted by your eyes”.

title: Walgreens
complex: Walgreen Company or simply Walgreens is an American company that operates as the second-largest pharmacy store chain in the United States behind CVS Health. <s> It specializes in filling prescriptions, health and wellness products, health information, and photo services. <s> As of August 31, 2018, the company operated 9,560 stores in all 50 states, the District of Columbia, Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands. <s> It was founded in Chicago, Illinois, in 1901. <s> The Walgreens headquarters office is in the Chicago suburb of Deerfield, Illinois. <s> Walgreens has its corporate headquarters in Deerfield, Illinois. <s> As of 2009, Walgreens employed 5,200 people at its headquarters. <s> In the 1980s Walgreens owned and operated a chain of casual family restaurants/pancake houses called Wag's, an attempt to compete with Woolworth's lunch counters. <s> The Wag's restaurants were very similar in concept to Denny's, IHOP, and Golden Bear. <s> At the highpoint, it had over 100 locations. <s> Walgreens sold most of these to Marriott Corp. in 1988 and by 1991, the chain was out of business.
simple: Walgreens is a pharmacy chain in the United States. <s> It was founded in 1901 in Chicago. <s> Its headquarters are in Deerfield, Illinois. <s> In the 1980s, Walgreens owned and operated a chain of casual family restaurants/pancake houses called Wag's. <s> It was very similar to Denny's, IHOP and Golden Bear. <s> In 1988, Walgreens sold most of Wag's to Marriott Corporation and by 1991 the chain was out of business.

title: Park Ji-yeon
complex: Park Ji-yeon (born June 7, 1993), referred to as Jiyeon, is a South Korean singer and actress. <s> She debuted as a member of girl group T-ara in July 2009. <s> The group went on to become one of the best-selling girl groups of all time. <s> Apart from her group's activities, she has also starred in various television dramas such as "Soul" (2009), "Master of Study" (2010), "Dream High 2" (2012), "Triangle" (2014), also starred in various films such as "" (2012), "Encounter" (2015). <s> She debuted as a solo artist with her first EP, "Never Ever", on May 20, 2014, making her the first T-ara member to debut as a solo artist. <s> Park was born in Seoul, South Korea, on June 7, 1993, from a Korean family. <s> She briefly attended Hyehwa Girls' High School and graduated from Lila Art High School in 2012. <s> She didn't attend university to focus on her career. <s> She and Hahm Eun-jung are the only two members of T-ara to be trained in acting. <s> Instead, the two switched over to singing despite their original intentions. <s> Park has expressed an interest in modeling. <s> In 2008, when she was 15 years old, she was featured in several pictorials and advertisements for clothing company Smart with Korean boy band SHINee. <s> She collaborated with Davichi and SeeYa on the digital single "Women's Generation", which was released in May 2009, making her the first member of T-ara to appear in public. <s> She appeared in SG Wannabe's music videos "I Love You" and "Crybaby" from their 2009 album, "Gift from SG Wannabe". <s> Early on, the Korean media dubbed her as "Little Kim Tae-hee" due to her close resemblance to Kim. <s> Park auditioned at the Mnet Casting System and joined the company in 2008. <s> She subsequently debuted with T-ara on July 29, 2009 as the youngest member (maknae). <s> In 2010, Park starred in "Master of Study", a Korean screen adaptation of Japanese manga "Dragon Zakura". <s> That same year, she played the leading role in horror film "" and starred in the youth drama "Jungle Fish 2". <s> In October 2010, Park became the host for MBC's "Show! <s> Music Core", alongside Bae Suzy, Choi Min-ho and Onew. <s> She also became a cast member of SBS's variety show "Heroes". <s> In 2011, Park was cast in the Korean dub of the animated film, "Gnomeo and Juliet". <s> In 2012, she was cast in the teen drama "Dream High 2", starring Kang So-ra, GOT7's JB and Jin-young, 2AM's Jinwoon, SISTAR's Hyolyn, and Park Seo-joon. <s> Park made her solo debut in May 2014, releasing the title track "Never Ever" (also known as "1 Minute 1 Second"). <s> The music video ranked number one on China's biggest music video site YinYueTai for two weeks straight. <s> In June, Park was cast in MBC's television series "Triangle", starring as the potential wife for Yim Si-wan's character. <s> The same month, she began hosting SBS MTV's "" alongside Lee Hye-ri. <s> In May 2015, Park was cast in the Korean-Chinese film "Encounter" alongside actor Lee Dong-gun. <s> In July 2015, she collaborated with 2BiC's Jun-hyung on the song "Summer Love". <s> In 2016, Park was cast in the web drama "My Runway" alongside Kang Dong-ho. <s> The drama was released on Netflix in December 2016. <s> In February 2017, it was announced that Park would be making her solo comeback after three years with a new album. <s> However, album preparations were later cancelled. <s> In early 2018, Park and her fellow T-ara members departed from MBK Entertainment following the expiration of their contracts. <s> She later signed with Chinese agency Longzhen Culture Development in May 2018. <s> Park and Vietnamese singer Soobin Hoàng Sơn have released music videos for the Korean version and Vietnamese version of their collaboration track, "Between Us". <s> Jiyeon signed with Partners Park in November 2018 for her domestic activities. <s> On November 26, it was revealed that Park would release a digital single in mid December, as a thank you gift for fans. <s> On December 22, 2018, Park released music videos for the Korean and Chinese version of her winter ballad track "One Day". <s> On April 2, 2019, Park was cast in the KBS2's mystery, romantic comedy drama "I Wanna Hear Your Song" alongside Yeon Woo-jin, Kim Se-jeong and Song Jae-rim.
simple: Park Ji-yeon is a South Korean singer and actress. <s> She is known by the stage name Jiyeon. <s> She has been a member of girl group T-ara since 2009. <s> Park was born in Seoul, South Korea, on June 7, 1993. <s> She went to Hyehwa Girls' High School and Lila Art High School. <s> She and Hahm Eun-jung are the only two members of T-ara to be trained in acting. <s> Park had a desire to be a model. <s> In 2008, she was in several advertisements for clothing. <s> In early 2009 she sang with Davichi and SeeYa in the song "Women's Generation". <s> This made her the first member of T-ara to appear in public. <s> She also was in SG Wannabe's music videos "I Love You" and "Crybaby" in 2009. <s> He first appearance with T-ara was on July 29, 2009. <s> In 2010, Park was in the movie "Master of Study". <s> That same year, she had a lead role in horror film "Death Bell 2: Bloody Camp". <s> She was also in the movie "Jungle Fish 2". <s> In 2010, Park became the host for MBC's "Show! <s> Music Core", alongside Bae Suzy, Choi Min-ho and Onew. <s> She also was in SBS's television show "Heroes". <s> In 2011, Park was a voice actor in the Korean translation of "Gnomeo and Juliet". <s> In 2012, she was in the drama "Dream High 2". <s> Park made her solo debut in May 2014. <s> It was with her song "Never Ever". <s> The music video ranked number one on China's YinYueTai for two weeks. <s> In June 2014, Park was in MBC's television series "Triangle". <s> The same month, she began hosting SBS MTV's "The Show: All About K-pop". <s> In May 2015, Park was in the Korean-Chinese movie "Encounter". <s> In July 2015, she sang the song "Summer Love" with 2BiC's Jun-hyung. <s> In 2016, Park was in the drama "My Runway". <s> The drama was released on Netflix in December 2016. <s> In February 2017, Park said she would make a new solo album. <s> It was later cancelled. <s> In early 2018, Park and her fellow T-ara members left MBK Entertainment when their contracts finished. <s> In May 2018, Park joined Chinese agency Longzhen Culture Development. <s> She then made a song with Vietnamese singer Soobin Hoàng Sơn. <s> In November 2018, she signed with Partners Park for her work in Korea. <s> In December 2018, Park made music videos for her song "One Day" <s> In 2019, she was cast in the drama "Let Me Hear Your Song".

title: Yoichiro Kakitani
complex: Yoichiro Kakitani (柿谷 曜一朗 , Kakitani Yōichirō ) (born 3 January 1990 in Osaka) is a Japanese footballer who plays as an attacking midfielder for Cerezo Osaka.
simple: Yoichiro Kakitani (born 3 January 1990) is a Japanese football player.

title: Petrykivka painting
complex: Petrykivka painting (or simply "Petrykivka") is a traditional Ukrainian decorative painting style, originating from the village of Petrykivka in Dnipropetrovsk oblast of Ukraine, where it was traditionally used to decorate house walls and everyday household items. <s> The earliest known examples of this style date from the 17th century, but it continues to thrive and develop as a modern art form. <s> In 2012, the Ministry of Culture of Ukraine recognized Petrykivka painting as a part of intangible cultural heritage of Ukraine, and it was included in the UNESCO Representative List of the Intangible Cultural Heritage of Humanity in 2013. <s> Petrykivka painting has become a "brand" in Ukrainian popular culture, and a "Petrykivka" trademark belonging to the artisans of Petrykivka village has been created.
simple: Petrykivka painting is a traditional Ukrainian decorative painting. <s> It originates from the Petrykivka village in Dnipropetrovsk oblast of Ukraine. <s> In 2013 it was included to the UNESCO Representative List of the Intangible Cultural Heritage of Humanity.

title: Albert (given name)
complex: Albert is a masculine given name. <s> It is derived from the Germanic "Adalbert", containing the words "adal" ("noble") and "beraht" ("bright"). <s> It is also less commonly in use as a surname.
simple: The name Albert is a masculine given name. <s> It comes from the Germanic words "adal" and "beraht", meaning "bright" and "noble".

title: Iran–Iraq War
complex: The Iran–Iraq War began on 22 September 1980, when Iraq invaded Iran, and it ended on 20 August 1988, when Iran accepted the UN-brokered ceasefire. <s> Iraq wanted to replace Iran as the dominant Persian Gulf state, and was worried that the 1979 Iranian Revolution would lead Iraq's Shi'ite majority to rebel against the Ba'athist government. <s> The war also followed a long history of border disputes, and Iraq planned to annex the oil-rich Khuzestan Province and the east bank of the Arvand Rud (Shatt al-Arab). <s> An estimated 500,000 Iraqi and Iranian soldiers died, in addition to a smaller number of civilians. <s> The end of the war resulted in neither reparations nor border changes. <s> The Iran–Iraq War was originally referred to as the "Persian Gulf War" until the Persian Gulf War of 1990 and 1991, after which it was known as the "First Persian Gulf War". <s> The Iraq–Kuwait conflict, which was known as the "Second Persian Gulf War," eventually became known simply as the "Persian Gulf War". <s> The Iraq War from 2003 to 2011 has been called the "Second Persian Gulf War". <s> At the war's conclusion, it took several weeks for the Armed Forces of the Islamic Republic of Iran to evacuate Iraqi territory to honor pre-war international borders set by the 1975 Algiers Agreement. <s> The last prisoners of war were exchanged in 2003. <s> Besides the United States and the Soviet Union, Yugoslavia also sold weapons to both countries for the entire duration of the conflict. <s> Likewise, Portugal helped both countries; it was not unusual to see Iranian and Iraqi flagged ships anchored at Setúbal, waiting their turn to dock.
simple: The Iran–Iraq War was a war between the armed forces of Iraq and Iran lasting from September 1980 to August 1988. <s> The war began when Iraq invaded Iran on 22 September 1980, after a long history of border disputes and demands for the overthrow of Saddam Hussein's regime. <s> About a million soldiers died and a similar number of civilians. <s> It was commonly called the "Persian Gulf War" until Iraq invaded Kuwait in 1990. <s> The Iraq-Kuwait war, which the United States entered, later was called the "Persian Gulf War" or the "Gulf War". <s> Despite several calls for an end to the fighting by the United Nations Security Council, the two countries fought until 20 August 1988; the last prisoners of war were exchanged in 2003. <s> The United States sold many weapons to the Shah's government. <s> The United States had sold many weapons to Iran before the war. <s> The Soviet Union sold weapons to Iran during the war.

title: Prince Bernhard of Lippe-Biesterfeld
complex: Prince Bernhard of Lippe-Biesterfeld (later Prince Bernhard of the Netherlands; German: "Bernhard Friedrich Eberhard Leopold Julius Kurt Carl Gottfried Peter Graf von Biesterfeld"; 29 June 1911 – 1 December 2004) was a Dutch prince who was the consort of Queen Juliana of the Netherlands; they were the parents of four children, including Princess Beatrix, who was Queen of the Netherlands from 1980 to 2013. <s> Bernhard was born Bernhard Leopold Friedrich Eberhard Julius Kurt Karl Gottfried Peter, Count of Biesterfeld in Jena, Saxe-Weimar-Eisenach, German Empire on 29 June 1911, the elder son of Prince Bernhard of Lippe and his wife, Armgard von Cramm. <s> He was a grandson of Ernest, Count of Lippe-Biesterfeld, who was regent of the Principality of Lippe until 1904. <s> He was also a nephew of the principality's last sovereign, Leopold IV, Prince of Lippe. <s> Prince Bernhard died of cancer at the age of 93 at University Medical Center Utrecht in Utrecht on 1 December 2004; until his death he suffered from malignant lung and intestinal tumors. <s> On 11 December 2004, he was interred with a lavish state funeral at the Nieuwe Kerk, Delft.
simple: Prince Bernhard of the Netherlands (29 June 1911 – 1 December 2004) was the prince consort of Queen Juliana of the Netherlands. <s> He was born in Jena, Saxe-Weimar-Eisenach, German Empire. <s> He died of lung cancer in Utrecht, Netherlands at the age of 93.

title: Space Shuttle Challenger
complex: Space Shuttle "Challenger" (Orbiter Vehicle Designation: OV-099) was the second orbiter of NASA's Space Shuttle program to be put into service, after "Columbia". <s> "Challenger" was built by Rockwell International's Space Transportation Systems Division, in Downey, California. <s> Its maiden flight, STS-6, began on April 4, 1983. <s> The orbiter was launched and landed nine times before breaking apart 73 seconds into its tenth mission, STS-51-L, on January 28, 1986, resulting in the death of all seven crew members including a civilian school teacher. <s> "Challenger" was named after HMS "Challenger", a British corvette that was the command ship for the "Challenger" Expedition, a pioneering global marine research expedition undertaken from 1872 through 1876. <s> The Apollo 17 Lunar Module, which landed on the Moon in 1972, is also named "Challenger".
simple: Space Shuttle "Challenger" (OV-099) was the second space shuttle used by NASA to fly into outer space. <s> The shuttle broke up 73 seconds after take-off from Cape Canaveral on 28 January 1986. <s> All seven astronauts who were on it at the time were killed. <s> The Challenger was named after a Royal Navy ship that explored the Pacific and Atlantic Oceans from 1872 to 1876. <s> Challenger was also the name of the Apollo 17 Lunar Excursion Module.

title: Gini coefficient
complex: In economics, the Gini coefficient , sometimes called Gini index, or Gini ratio, is a measure of statistical dispersion intended to represent the income or wealth distribution of a nation's residents, and is the most commonly used measurement of inequality. <s> It was developed by the Italian statistician and sociologist Corrado Gini and published in his 1912 paper "Variability and Mutability" . <s> The table below presents the estimated world income Gini coefficients over the last 200 years, as calculated by Milanovic. <s> More detailed data from similar sources plots a continuous decline since 1988.
simple: The Gini coefficient (also known as the Gini index or Gini ratio) is a measure of differences in income. <s> It was developed by the Italian statistician Corrado Gini in 1912. <s> The table below is about the "world" Gini coefficient (not by single countries). <s> The table below shows the income Gini coefficient of the United States from 1947 to 2009.

title: Denis Leary
complex: Denis Colin O'Leary (born August 18, 1957) is an American actor, comedian, singer, writer and producer. <s> Leary was the star and co-creator of "Rescue Me", which ended its seventh and final season on September 7, 2011. <s> He has starred in many films including playing Captain George Stacy in Marc Webb's film, "The Amazing Spider-Man", Cleveland Browns Head Coach Vince Penn in Ivan Reitman's film, "Draft Day", and as the voice of Francis in "A Bug's Life" and Diego in the "Ice Age" franchise.
simple: Denis Colin Leary (born August 18, 1957 in Worcester, Massachusetts) is an American actor, comedian, producer, singer and writer. <s> He is the star and co-creator of the television show "Rescue Me".

title: Pukkila
complex: Pukkila (] ) is a municipality of Finland. <s> It is located in the Uusimaa region and it is the smallest municipality in the region in relation to its population; the municipality has a population of and covers an area of km2 of which km2 is water.
simple: Pukkila is a municipality in Finland.
